)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$EDITVALUE   . EDIT IN VALUE @C@E@D          E$DTX   NR
)@@G@@                    . PRINT IT@C@G@E          JNZ       A5,DSP010       NS

)@@G@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@G@EDSP010NU
)@@G@@    . @B@G@E          E$CLOSE                     .   @C@E@D          J NV

)@@G@@        X11,DSPLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@E          J       NX

)@@G@@@D@@@ . THE 'ABORT' COMMAND DOES AN ESCAPE AND IN ADDITION  @C@@@ . SETSOE
)@@G@@ M$ABORT FOR M$EXECUTE TO RETURN IN A0.   @[@@@ .     @^@@@ M$COMABORT* OF
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@           L,U       A0,1              . SET FLAG TO   OG
)@@G@@@D@@@           S         A0,M$ABORT        . CAUSE ABORT   @[@@@ .     OH
)@@G@@@[@ @[.     @D@@@[. THE 'ESCAPE' COMMAND RETURNS TO KEYBOARD LEVEL.     OI
)@@G@@@#@@@ . (NOTE FALL-THRU)@[@@@[.     @]@]@[ESCAPE*   . @]@#@]M$CESC*   . OJ
)@@G@@@^@@@#M$COMESCAPE*        .   @B@@@]          S         X11,ESCLNK      OK
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@]          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    OL
)@@G@@@]@@@]ESC010    . @E@]@[          TNZ,H2    CRPROC            . IS THEREOM
)@@G@@ A STACK ?  @E@^@]          TNZ,H2    M$MXQT            . IS THERE A STAON
)@@G@@CK ?  @E@@@^          TNZ,H2    M$XQTMACRO        . IS THERE A STACK ?  OO
)@@G@@@D@]@[          J         COMMAND           . NO : RETURN   @D@@@]      OP
)@@G@@    J         ESC999            . NO : RETURN   @D@]@[          LMJ     OQ
)@@G@@  X11,MSPOP         . POP STACK THEN@D@#@]          LMJ       X11,M$MPOPOR
)@@G@@        . POP STACK THEN@D@^@#          LMJ       X11,M$XQTPOPSTACK . POOS
)@@G@@P STACK THEN@D@@@^          LMJ       X11,M$XQTPOPSTAK  . POP STACK THENOT
)@@G@@@F@@@]          JZ        A5,ESC010         . IF NO ERROR TRY AGAIN     OU
)@@G@@@]@@@]ESC999    . @B@@@]          L         X11,ESCLNK        .   @D@]@[OV
)@@G@@          J         ESCAPE            . AND TRY AGAIN @C@@@]          J OW
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@].     @D@@@]ESCLNK    VAR     OX
)@@G@@  'ESCLNK',1        . LINK HOME     @[@@@].     @B@@@]          END     OY
)@@G@@                    .   ___RY AGAIN @]@]@[ESC099*[S@@@*SDFF*@^@@@@@COPY,OZ
)@@G@@S MACRO.M$AMODES  @^@@@@@COPY,S MACRO.M$ASCANNER@ @@@@@COPY,S MACRO.M$ACPA

)@@G@@@E@@@@. THE 'SI' COMMAND PRINTS A LIST OF THE MACROS STACKED UP   @F@@@@PG
)@@G@@. BACK TO KEYBOARD LEVEL.  SUSPENDED MACROS ARE MARKED WITH *.    @[@@@@PH
)@@G@@.     @]@[@@SIV*      . @]@@@[M$COMSIV* . @E@@@@          S         X11,PI
)@@G@@SIVLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@@          S         X10,SIVX10PJ
)@@G@@        . SAVE POINTER REG    @E@@@@          L,H2      X10,M$XQTMACRO  PK
)@@G@@  . GET MACRO STACK     @D@@@@          E$OPEN    M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPPL
)@@G@@EN EDIT$    @]@@@@SIV010    . @D@@@@          TNZ,U     0,X10           PM
)@@G@@  . ANY MORE ?    @C@@@@          J         SIV100            . NOPE    PN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A0,CXDEFN,X10     . GET ADDRESS OF MACRO NAME PO
)@@G@@@C@@@@          E$FD2     0,A0              . EDIT IT @C@]@@          L,PP
)@@G@@U       A0,'*'            . STAR    @E@]@@          TZ        CXSUSP,X10PQ
)@@G@@        . IS IT SUSPENDED     @D@]@@          E$CHAR                    PR
)@@G@@  . YES - EDIT IT @B@@@@          E$CHAR    '('               .   @D@@@@PS
)@@G@@          E$DECV    CXLINE,X10        . EDIT LINE #   @B@@@@          E$PT
)@@G@@CHAR    ')'               .   @C@@@]          L,U       A0,'*'          PU
)@@G@@  . STAR    @E@@@]          TZ        CXSUSP,X10        . IS IT SUSPENDEPV
)@@G@@D     @D@@@]          E$CHAR                      . YES - EDIT IT @C@@@@PW
)@@G@@          E$PRT     1                 . PRINT IT@E@@@@          E$RASE  PX
)@@G@@  0                 . CLEAR EDIT$ BUFFER  @D@@@@          L         X10,PY
)@@G@@CXLINK,X10    . GET NEXT ONE  @C@@@@          J         SIV010          PZ
)@@G@@  . AND LOOP@]@@@@SIV100    . @D@@@@          E$CLOSE                   QA
)@@G@@  . CLOSE EDIT$   @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERQB
)@@G@@ROR FLAG    @]@@@@SIV999    . @D@@@@          L         X10,SIVX10      QC
)@@G@@  . GET POINTER   @E@@@@          L         X11,SIVLNK        . GET RETUQD
)@@G@@RN ADDRESS  @C@@@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@QE
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@SIVLNK    VAR       'SIVLNK',1        . LINK HOME     @C@@@@QF
)@@G@@SIVX10    VAR       'SIVX10',1        . TEMP    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      QG

)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             QJ
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. DO A TYPE AND READ.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@QK
)@@G@@M$TREADF* . @F@@@@          DSL       A4,72             . CLEAR ERROR ANQL
)@@G@@D EOF FLAGS @C@@@@          TZ        M$REOF            . EOF SEEN@E@@@@QM
)@@G@@          J         EOF010            . YES - SKIP TREAD    @D@@@@      QN
)@@G@@    ER        TREAD$            . TYPE AND READ @F@@@@          SZ      QO
)@@G@@  M$BREAK           . CLEAR REMOTE BREAK FLAG   @D@@@@          S       QP
)@@G@@  A0,M$TRA0         . SAVE A0 VALUE @D@@@@          L,U       A0,0,A0   QQ
)@@G@@        . GET WORD COUNT@E@@@@          J         0,X11             . TAQR
)@@G@@KE NORMAL RETURN  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EOF010    . @F@@@@          L,U     QS
)@@G@@  A4,1              . SET EOF FLAG FOR CALLER   @E@@@@          L,U     QT
)@@G@@  A0,0              . ZERO WORD COUNT     @C@@@@          J         0,X1QU
)@@G@@1             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                 QV
)@@G@@        .   ___^?GC9K@@_NKK^?H8KK@_+[XX=A/8KK@_-*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@      QW
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             QX
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. DO A TYPE AND READ.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@QY
)@@G@@M$TREADA* . @F@@@@          DSL       A4,72             . CLEAR ERROR ANQZ
)@@G@@D EOF FLAGS @C@@@@          TZ        M$REOF            . EOF SEEN@E@@@@RA
)@@G@@          J         EOF010            . YES - SKIP TREAD    @D@@@@      RB
)@@G@@    ER        ATREAD$           . TYPE AND READ @F@@@@          SZ      RC
)@@G@@  M$BREAK           . CLEAR REMOTE BREAK FLAG   @D@@@@          S       RD
)@@G@@  A0,M$TRA0         . SAVE A0 VALUE @D@@@@          L,U       A0,0,A0   RE
)@@G@@        . GET WORD COUNT@E@@@@          J         0,X11             . TARF
)@@G@@KE NORMAL RETURN  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. END OF FILE ADDRESSES FROM ALL TRERG
)@@G@@AD$ PACKETS SHOULD POINT HERE.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$TREOF*  . @F@@@@      RH
)@@G@@    SZ        M$BREAK           . CLEAR REMOTE BREAK FLAG   @D@@@@      RI
)@@G@@    S         A0,M$TRA0         . SAVE A0 VALUE @D@@@@          JP      RJ
)@@G@@  A0,EOF010         . IF SOFT SKIP  @E@@@@          L,U       A0,1      RK
)@@G@@        . IF HARD EOF SET     @E@@@@          S         A0,M$REOF       RL
)@@G@@  . FLAG TO INHIBIT     @]@@@@EOF010    . @F@@@@          L,U       A4,1RM
)@@G@@              . SET EOF FLAG FOR CALLER   @E@@@@          L,U       A0,0RN
)@@G@@              . ZERO WORD COUNT     @C@@@@          J         0,X11     RO
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                       RP

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@S          AXR$                        .   @D@@@T      KJ
)@@G@@    ELT$                        . GET ENAME     @B@T@S          MACROP  KK
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@T          M$APROC                     .   KL
)@@G@@@[@@@T.     @G@@@T. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO SEARCH FOR AN UNDEFINED MAKM
)@@G@@CRO.  IT SEARCHES @G@@@T. THE LIBRARY FILES DEFINED IN THE CONFIGURATIONKN
)@@G@@ ELEMENT FOR A SYMBOLIC @E@@@T. ELEMENT WITH THE SAME NAME.  IF FOUND ITKO
)@@G@@ IS RETURNED.     @[@@@T.     @D@T@S          E$FIELDS  ZAVE            KP
)@@G@@  . EDIT$ FIELDS  @B@@@S          INSTRS                      .   @]@T@SKQ
)@@G@@M$MSUM*   . @^@@@TM$XQTUNDMAC*        .   @D@@@T          S         X11,KR

)@@G@@Y FILES.    @E@@@T. IF ANY MORE FILE INFO GIVEN THEN SEARCH SPECIFIC FILKV
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@T.     @G@@@W          TNZ       CFN               . IF IMPLIKW

)@@G@@UM999         . ERROR   @E@W@T          JNZ       A4,SUM999         . IFLZ

)@@G@@T ERROR MESSAGE   @[@W@T.     @^@W@T. SEARCH LIBRARY FILES. @[@W@T.     MB

)@@G@@        . SAVE SITE TYPE@C@F@D          P$RINT    (0101,SITTYP)     . PRTI

)@@G@@  A0,M$APFFLG       . AND SET FLAG  @E@@@D          L,U       A5,0      TP

)@@G@@  X11,SITLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@D          J         0,X1TR
)@@G@@1             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@D.     @C@@@D          LITS    TS
)@@G@@                    . LITERALS@[@@@D.     @]@@@DSITTAB    . @D@@@D      TT
)@@G@@    -         1                 . -1 = SITE     @D@@@D          +       TU
)@@G@@  1                 . +1 = CSITE    @[@@@D.     @D@@@DSITLNK    VAR     TV
)@@G@@  'SITLNK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@D@@@DSITTYP    VAR       'SITTYP',1TW
)@@G@@        . SITE TYPE     @[@D@C/.    @[@@@D.     @B@@@D          INSTRS  TX
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@D.     @A@@@D. RESUME - FREE AND SYM PRINT TY
)@@G@@FILE. @[@@@D.     @^@@@DM$COMRESUME*        .   @E@@@D          S       TZ

)@@G@@. SUBROUTINE TO OBTAIN AN ALTERNATE PRINT FILE. @[@@@C.     @B@@@C.     UK

)@@G@@@^@@@[          DON       .   @E@@@[          TEP,U     A2,DBLBIT       CS
)@@G@@  . DOUBLE PRECISION    @E@@@[          LSSL      A0,1              . YECT
)@@G@@S - DOUBLE IT     @^@@@[          DOF       .   @D@@@[          J       CU
)@@G@@  LEN020            . AND RETURN    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[. ALPHA     @[@@@[CV
)@@G@@.     @]@@@[LEN010    . @E@@@[          DSL       A0,36             . PRCW
)@@G@@EPARE TO DIVIDE   @D@@@[          TOP,U     A2,ASCBIT         . IS IT FICX
)@@G@@ELDATA@D@@@[          DI,U      A0,6              . YES - DIVIDE  @D@@@[CY
)@@G@@          TEP,U     A2,ASCBIT         . IS IT ASCII   @E@@@[          LDCZ
)@@G@@SL      A0,34             . YES - DIVIDE BY 4   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. NOTEDA
)@@G@@ - THE ABOVE WORKS BECAUSE THE REMAINDER REGISTER IS ONLY   @ @@@[. TESTDB
)@@G@@ED FOR ZERO/NONZERO.    @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          JZ        A1,$+2    DC
)@@G@@        . ANY REMAINDER @D@@@[          A,U       A0,1              . YEDD
)@@G@@S - ROUND UP@]@@@[LEN020    . @E@@@]          L,U       A5,0            DE
)@@G@@  . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@]LEN999    . @E@]@[          J         1,X1DF
)@@G@@1             . TAKE NORMAL RETURN  @E@@@]          J         0,X11     DG
)@@G@@        . TAKE NORMAL RETURN  @[@@@[.     @B@ @]LENPSV    PCW       'NOTDH
)@@G@@ PSEUDO  '    .   @B@@@ LENPSV    PCM       1                 .   @B@@@ DI
)@@G@@          'DATA ITEM REQUIRED.'       .   @B@@@           ENDPCM        DJ
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@].     @B@@@[          END                       DK
)@@G@@  .   ___ ENDPCM                      .   @[@@@[.     @B@@@@          ENDL
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@S          AXR$                        .   @B@@@S      DM
)@@G@@    M$APROC                     .   @D@@@T          M$CPAR              DN
)@@G@@        . GET STKMAX    @[@@@S.     @G@@@S. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WITH DO
)@@G@@TIDE$ OPEN TO BUILD AN ARGUMENT BUFFER    @F@@@S. CONTAINING POINTERS TODP
)@@G@@ THE CALL IMAGE AND THE CALL IMAGE ITSELF.@F@@@S. THE WORD RETURNED IN ADQ
)@@G@@0 SHOULD BE PLACED IN CXARGS OF THE MACRO @F@@@S. EXECUTION ENTRY FOR SYDR
)@@G@@MBOLIC SUBSTITUTION TO WORK PROPERLY.     @[@@@S.     @A@@@S. BUILD POINDS
)@@G@@TER BUFFER IN M$STAK.   @[@@@S.     @D@@@SAPTR      EQUF      M$STAK+2*(DT
)@@G@@STKMAX-2) . POINTER     @G@@@SFRST      EQUF      APTR,,H1          . STDU
)@@G@@ART COLUMN (AND COUNTERS)     @D@@@SLAST      EQUF      APTR,,H2        DV
)@@G@@  . END COLUMN    @[@@@T.     @B@@@TSTKPTR    EQU       X8              DW
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@S.     @]@U@SM$MMCS*   . @^@@@UM$CALLSCAN*         .   @E@@@SDX
)@@G@@          S         X11,MCSLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@S      DY
)@@G@@    S         X8,MCSSIX         . SAVE INDEX REGISTERS@B@@@S          S DZ
)@@G@@        X9,MCSSIX+1       .   @B@@@S          S         X10,MCSSIX+2    EA
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@S.     @B@@@S. X8 POINTS TO THE CURRENT SUBFIELD WORD. @B@@@SEB
)@@G@@. X9 POINTS TO THE CURRENT FIELD WORD.    @C@@@S. X10 POINTS TO THE MACREC
)@@G@@O BUFFER BEING BUILT.   @[@@@S.     @E@@@S          L         STKPTR,MCSED
)@@G@@STK     . GET INITIAL STACK   @E@@@S          L,U       X10,0,X8        EE
)@@G@@  . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @F@@@S          SZ        APTR,X10          . CLEF
)@@G@@EAR COUNTER AND END     @[@@@S.     @B@@@S. SCAN PAST BLANKS UNTIL NEXT EG
)@@G@@FIELD FOUND.@[@@@S.     @]@@@SMCS010    . @E@@@S          T$NFINDA  ' ' EH
)@@G@@MCS080        . FIND NEXT NONBLANK  @D@@@S          S         A3,MCSCHR EI
)@@G@@        . SAVE CHARACTER@E@@@S          TE,U      A3,'.'            . WAEJ
)@@G@@S TERMED BY PERIOD@E@@@S          J         MCS020            . NO - NOTEK
)@@G@@ END OF CARD@F@@@S          T$CHARN   MCS080            . GET NEXT CHAR EL
)@@G@@NO LOOKAHEAD@D@@@S          L,U       A3,0,A3           . REAL CHARACTEREM
)@@G@@@E@@@S          TNE,U     A3,' '            . SPACE PERIOD SPACE  @E@@@SEN
)@@G@@          J         MCS080            . YES - DONE SCAN     @[@@@S.     EO
)@@G@@@F@@@S. NOT TERMINATION.  PUSH ANOTHER FIELD AND ITS FIRST SUBFIELD     EP
)@@G@@@C@@@S. ONTO STACK AFTER INCREMENTING FIELD COUNTER.  @[@@@S.     @]@@@SEQ
)@@G@@MCS020    . @E@@@S          PUSH      MCS090            . PUSH ONTO STACER
)@@G@@K     @G@@@S          L,U       X9,0,X8           . POINT FIELD POINTER ES
)@@G@@AT ENTRY    @E@@@S          PUSH      MCS090            . PUSH FIRST SUBET
)@@G@@FIELD @G@@@S          L,U       A0,1              . SET SUBFIELD COUNTEREU
)@@G@@ TO ONE     @B@@@S          S         A0,FRST,X9        .   @F@@@S      EV
)@@G@@    A         A0,FRST,X10       . INCREMENT FIELD COUNTER   @B@@@S      EW
)@@G@@    S         A0,FRST,X10       .   @G@@@S          T$COLN              EX
)@@G@@        . GET COLUMN NUMBER WE ARE AT     @F@@@T          AN,U      A0,1EY
)@@G@@              . GET WHERE THIS CHAR WAS   @F@@@S          S         A0,FEZ
)@@G@@RST,X8        . SET SUBFIELD START COLUMN @E@@@S          L         A3,MFA
)@@G@@CSCHR         . GET CHARACTER AGAIN @[@@@T/.    @[@@@S.     @G@T@S. WITHFB
)@@G@@IN A FIELD.  SKIP PAST DULL DRAB ARDINARY CHARACTERS WITH NEW     @G@@@TFC
)@@G@@. WITHIN A FIELD.  SKIP PAST DULL DRAB ORDINARY CHARACTERS WITH NEW     FD
)@@G@@@#@T@S. IMPROVED TIDE$. @A@@@T. IMPROVED TIDE$. (NOTE FALL-THRU). @[@@@SFE
)@@G@@.     @]@@@SMCS030    . @E@T@S          JN        A3,MSC070         . IFFF
)@@G@@ END OF CARD SKIP @E@@@S          TNE,U     A3,' '            . WAS CHARFG
)@@G@@ACTER BLANK @E@T@S          J         MSC070            . YES - END OF FFH
)@@G@@IELD  @E@@@T          J         MCS070            . YES - END OF FIELD  FI
)@@G@@@F@@@S          TNE,U     A3,''''           . WAS IT FIELDATA QUOTE     FJ
)@@G@@@E@@@S          J         MCS050            . YES - FIND ITS MATE @F@@@SFK
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A3,67             . WAS IT ASCII QUOTE (MAJIC)@E@@@SFL
)@@G@@          J         MCS060            . YES - FIND ITS MATE @E@@@S      FM
)@@G@@    TE,U      A3,','            . IS IT COMMA THEN    @E@@@S          J FN
)@@G@@        MCS040            . NO - SKIP FIELD     @[@@@S.     @D@@@S. COMMFO
)@@G@@A SEEN.  CLOSE OLD SUBFIELD AND OPEN NEW ONE.   @[@@@S.     @E@@@S      FP
)@@G@@    T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN WE ARE AT@F@T@S          ANFQ
)@@G@@U,U     A0,1              . MINUS ONE FOR OLD FIELD   @F@@@T          ANFR
)@@G@@U,U     A0,2              . MINUS TWO FOR OLD FIELD   @E@@@S          S FS
)@@G@@        A1,LAST,X8        . SAVE END OF SUBFIELD@G@@@S          PUSH    FT
)@@G@@  MCS090            . PUSH NEW SUBFIELD ONTO STACK    @G@T@S          A,FU
)@@G@@U       A0,1              . SET BEGINNING OF NEW SUBFIELD   @C@T@S      FV
)@@G@@    S         A0,FRST,X8        . ONTO    @G@@@T          S         A0,FFW
)@@G@@RST,X8        . SET BEGINNING OF SUBFIELD ONTO  @E@@@S          L       FX
)@@G@@  A0,FRST,X9        . INCREMENT COUNT OF  @E@@@S          A,U       A0,1FY
)@@G@@              . SUBFIELDS IN THE    @D@@@S          S         A0,FRST,X9FZ
)@@G@@        . FIELD ENTRY   @]@@@SMCS040    . @E@@@S          T$SCANV   0 MCGA
)@@G@@SMSK          . SKIP DULL CHARS     @E@@@T          JN        A3,MCS070 GB
)@@G@@        . IF DONE CLOSE IMAGE @E@@@T          L,U       A3,0,A3         GC
)@@G@@  . ELSE GET CHARACTER  @E@T@S          J         CAL130            . REGD
)@@G@@TURN TO CHECK     @E@@@T          J         MCS030            . RETURN TGE
)@@G@@O CHECK     @[@@@S.     @E@@@S. IF A FIELDATA QUOTE IS SEEN THIS CODE SKGF
)@@G@@IPS UNTIL MATE.   @[@@@S.     @]@@@SMCS050    . @E@T@S          T$FINDA GG
)@@G@@  '''' MSC091       . ERROR IS NOT CLOSED @E@@@T          T$FINDA   ''''GH
)@@G@@ MCS091       . ERROR IS NOT CLOSED @E@T@S          J         MCS030    GI
)@@G@@        . ELSE RETURN TO CHECK@E@@@T          J         MCS040          GJ
)@@G@@  . ELSE RETURN TO CHECK@[@@@S.     @C@@@S. IF AN ASCII QUOTE (TIDE$ 067GK
)@@G@@) SKIP UNTIL MATE.@[@@@S.     @]@@@SMCS060    . @D@@@S          T$FINDA GL
)@@G@@  67 MCS091         . FIND ITS MATE @D@T@S          J         MCS030    GM
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN    @D@@@T          J         MCS040            . ANGN
)@@G@@D RETURN    @[@@@T/.    @[@@@S.     @E@@@S. AT END OF FIELD THIS CODE CLGO
)@@G@@OSES THE SUBFIELD AND FIELD.  @[@@@S.     @]@@@SMCS070    . @D@@@S      GP
)@@G@@    S         A3,MCSCHR         . SAVE CHARACTER@E@@@S          T$COLN  GQ
)@@G@@                    . GET COLUMN NUMBER   @B@T@S          AN,U      A0,1GR
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@T          AN,U      A0,2              .   @D@@@SGS
)@@G@@          S         A0,LAST,X8        . CLOSE SUBFIELD@D@@@S          S GT
)@@G@@        A0,LAST,X9        . CLOSE FIELD   @D@@@T          S         A0,LGU
)@@G@@AST,X10       . CLOSE IMAGE   @E@@@S          L         A3,MCSCHR       GV
)@@G@@  . GET CHARACTER AGAIN @F@@@S          JP        A3,MCS010         . IFGW
)@@G@@ NOT EOC SCAN AGAIN     @[@@@S.     @D@@@S. END OF IMAGE.  CLOSE OUT ANDGX
)@@G@@ SET UP FOR RETURN.     @[@@@S.     @]@@@SMCS080    . @G@@@T          L,GY
)@@G@@U       A0,1,X8           . COMPUTE LENGTH OF PTR IMAGE     @B@@@T      GZ
)@@G@@    AN,U      A0,0,X10          .   @E@@@T          S         A0,MCSCHR HA
)@@G@@        . SAVE CORE LENGTH    @F@@@T          PGET                      HB
)@@G@@  . GET PERM CORE FOR POINTERS@C@@@T          JNZ       A5,MCS999       HC
)@@G@@  . OOPS    @E@@@T          L         R1,MCSCHR         . GET LENGTH AGAHD
)@@G@@IN    @D@@@T          LXI,U     A1,1              . SET UP TO BT  @B@@@THE
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,APTR,X10       .   @F@@@T          LXI,U     A0,1HF
)@@G@@              . POINTERS TO PERM CORE     @E@@@T          S         A1,MHG
)@@G@@CSCHR         . SAVE CORE ADDRESS   @G@@@T          BT        A1,0,*A0  HH
)@@G@@        . TRANSFER POINTERS TO PERM CORE  @F@@@T          T$COLN        HI
)@@G@@              . GET WORD COUNT FOR IMAGE  @B@@@T          A,U       A0,3HJ
)@@G@@              .   @F@@@T          SSL       A0,2              . DIVIDE BHK
)@@G@@Y 4 WITH ROUNDUP  @D@@@T          S,H1      A0,MCSCHR         . SAVE COUHL
)@@G@@NT    @F@@@T          PGET                        . GET PERM SPACE FOR IHM
)@@G@@MAGE  @D@@@T          JNZ       A5,MCS999         . IF ERROR SKIP @E@@@THN
)@@G@@          L,H1      R1,MCSCHR         . GET COUNT AGAIN     @D@V@T      HO
)@@G@@    L         A0,(1,M$MBUF)     . SET UP FOR BT @E@@@V          L       HP
)@@G@@  A0,(1,M$READBUFFER) . SET UP FOR BT     @F@@@T          LXI,U     A1,1HQ
)@@G@@              . OF IMAGE TO PERM CORE     @E@@@T          S,H1      A1,MHR
)@@G@@CSCHR         . SAVE BUFFER ADDRESS @F@@@T          BT        A1,0,*A0  HS
)@@G@@        . XFER IMAGE TO PERM CORE   @B@@@T          J         MCS999    HT
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@T.     @A@@@T. STACK OVERFLOW SCANNING IMAGE     @H@T@SHU
)@@G@@          T$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMBER OF LAST ON CARHV
)@@G@@D     @D@T@S          S         A0,LAST,X10       . CLOSE IMAGE   @E@T@SHW
)@@G@@          ER        ERR$              . SO WE CAN SNOOP     @E@T@S      HX
)@@G@@    L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @[@@@S.     @B@T@SHY
)@@G@@. BUILD ARGUMENT BUFFER AND LOAD INTO A0. @[@T@S.     @]@@@TMCS090    . HZ
)@@G@@@D@@@T          L         A5,MCSOVR         . STACK OVERFLOW@B@@@T      IA
)@@G@@    J         MCS999            .   @]@@@TMCS091    . @E@@@T          L IB
)@@G@@        A5,MCSQTC         . QUOTE NOT CLOSED    @]@@@SMCS999    . @D@@@TIC
)@@G@@          L         A0,MCSCHR         . GET POINTERS  @E@@@S          L ID
)@@G@@        X8,MCSSIX         . RESTORE INDEX REGS  @B@@@S          L       IE
)@@G@@  X9,MCSSIX+1       .   @B@@@S          L         X10,MCSSIX+2      .   IF
)@@G@@@[@@@S.     @E@@@S          L         X11,MCSLNK        . GET RETURN ADDIG
)@@G@@RESS  @D@@@S          J         0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@SIH
)@@G@@.     @^@@@T          LITS      .   @E@@@TMCSMSK    T$MASKR   ' ' ',' ''II
)@@G@@'' 067  . SKIP THE MUNDANE    @C@@@TMCSSTK    +         1,-2*(STKMAX-2) IJ
)@@G@@  . STACK   @C@W@TMCSOVR    PCW       'TOO MANY ARG','UMENTS' .   @B@@@WIK
)@@G@@MCSOVR    PCM       1                 .   @C@@@W          'ARGUMENT SCANIL
)@@G@@NER STACK OVERFLOW.' .  @C@W@TMCSQTC    PCW       'QUOTE NOT CL','OSED  IM
)@@G@@' .   @B@@@WMCSQTC    PCM       1                 .   @B@@@W          'QIN
)@@G@@UOTED STRING NOT CLOSED.' .   @B@@@W          ENDPCM                    IO
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@SMCSLNK    VAR       'MCSLNK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@D@@@SIP
)@@G@@MCSSIX    VAR       'MCSSIX',3        . SAVE X8-X10   @F@@@SMCSCHR    VAIQ
)@@G@@R       'MCSCHR',1        . CHAR THAT TERMINATED FIELD@[@@@S.     @B@@@SIR
)@@G@@          END                         .   ___       S         A0,FRST,X8IS
)@@G@@        . ONTO    @G@@@T          S         A0,F*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@F      IT
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@F          M$APROC             IU
)@@G@@        .   @B@G@F          M$ACOMP                     .   @B@@@G      IV
)@@G@@    M$ACOMPILER                 .   @[@@@F.     @F@@@F. THESE ROUTINES CIW
)@@G@@OMPILE THE ALTERNATION CONTROL STRUCTURE.  THE  @A@@@F. FORMAT OF THIS SIX
)@@G@@TRUCTURE IS :     @[@@@F.     @ @@@F.         IF <EXPRESSION>     @^@@@FIY
)@@G@@.           (BLOCK1)    @#@@@F.         ELSE    @^@@@F.           (BLOCKIZ
)@@G@@2)    @#@@@F.         ENDIF   @[@@@F.     @F@@@F. IF THE EXPRESSION EVALJA
)@@G@@UATES TO A TRUE VALUE BLOCK1 IS EXECUTED  @F@@@F. AND BLOCK2 IS SKIPPED.JB
)@@G@@  IF FALSE BLOCK1 IS SKIPPED AND BLOCK2   @E@@@F. IS EXECUTED.  THE ELSEJC
)@@G@@ AND BLOCK2 ARE OF COURSE OPTIONAL. @[@@@F.     @[@@@E.     @^@@@E. COMPJD
)@@G@@ILE 'IF' STATEMENT@[@@@E.     @D@F@ESIF       EQU       2               JE
)@@G@@  . STACK TOP - IF@]@G@EM$YIF*    . @]@@@GM$CMPIF*  . @E@@@F          S JF
)@@G@@        X11,IFLINK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@F          PUSH    JG
)@@G@@  IFF900            . PUSH ONTO STACK     @F@H@F          SDFOGA    M$MPJH
)@@G@@KT            . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT    @F@@@H          SDFOGA    M$OUJI
)@@G@@TPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT    @F@F@E          SDFOGA    M$MPJJ
)@@G@@KT            . GET ADDRESS OF IF STMT    @B@F@E          L         A0,MJK
)@@G@@$BLIN         .   @B@@@F          L         A0,M$YLIN         .   @E@F@EJL
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A0,SIF            . SET TYPE TO 'IF'    @E@@@F      JM
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,MSGIFF         . SET TYPE TO 'IF'    @E@@@F          DSJN
)@@G@@        A0,MSSTAK         . STORE ONTO STACK    @C@F@E          DS      JO
)@@G@@  A0,STACK,*X9      . STACK IT@D@F@E          SDFO      M$MPKT,CMP092   JP
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@H@F          LMJ       X11,M$YOUT        . OUTPUT IJQ
)@@G@@MAGE  @D@@@H          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@F@EJR
)@@G@@          J         CMPRET            . RETURN IT     @D@@@F          J JS
)@@G@@        IFF999            . RETURN IT     @[@@@E.     @#@@@E. COMPILE 'EJT
)@@G@@LSE'  @[@@@E.     @E@F@ESEL       EQU       3                 . STACK TOJU
)@@G@@P - ELSE    @]@G@EM$YELS*   . @^@@@GM$CMPELSE*          .   @E@@@F      JV
)@@G@@    S         X11,IFLINK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @B@F@E          L,JW
)@@G@@U       A0,SIF            .   @B@@@F          L,U       A0,MSGIFF       JX
)@@G@@  .   @E@F@E          TE,H1     A0,STACK-2,X9     . GET STACKTOP ITEM   JY
)@@G@@@E@@@F          TE        A0,MSTYPE         . GET STACKTOP ITEM   @E@F@EJZ
)@@G@@          J         CMP090            . NO - STRUCTURE ERROR@E@@@F      KA
)@@G@@    J         IFF910            . NO - STRUCTURE ERROR@F@H@E          SDKB
)@@G@@FOGA    M$MPKT            . GET ADDRESS 'ELSE' IMAGE  @F@@@H          SDKC
)@@G@@FOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS 'ELSE' IMAGE  @F@@@F          L KD
)@@G@@        A0,MSMSAD         . GET 'IF' STMT ADDRESS     @D@@@F          S KE
)@@G@@        A0,IFTEMP         . SAVE IT TEMP  @E@F@E          L         A6,SKF
)@@G@@TACK-1,X9     . SAVE STACKED ADDRESS@B@F@E          L         A0,M$BLIN KG
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@F          L         A0,M$YLIN         .   @E@F@E      KH
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,SEL            . SET STACKTOP TO ELSE@E@@@F          LXKI
)@@G@@I,U     A0,MSGELS         . SET STACKTOP TO ELSE@B@F@E          DS      KJ
)@@G@@  A0,STACK-2,X9     .   @B@@@F          DS        A0,MSSTAK         .   KK
)@@G@@@D@F@E          SDFO      M$MPKT,CMP092     . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@H@F      KL
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$YOUT        . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@@@H          LMJ     KM
)@@G@@  X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@@@F          JNZ       A5,IFF999 KN
)@@G@@        . IF ERROR SKIP @G@H@E          SDFOGA    M$MPKT            . GEKO
)@@G@@T ADDRESS IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'  @G@@@H          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET     KP
)@@G@@  . GET ADDRESS IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'  @D@F@E          L         A2,A6     KQ
)@@G@@        . RECOVER STACK @D@@@F          L         A2,IFTEMP         . REKR
)@@G@@COVER STACK @G@F@E          SDFUPD    M$MPKT,CMP092     . POINT 'IF' AT KS
)@@G@@IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'@G@H@F          LMJ       X11,M$YUPD        . POINT 'IKT
)@@G@@F' AT IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'@G@@@H          LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPDATE   . POKU
)@@G@@INT 'IF' AT IMAGE AFTER 'ELSE'@E@F@E          J         CMPRET          KV
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO COMPILER  @E@@@F          J         IFF999            . REKW
)@@G@@TURN TO COMPILER  @[@@@E.     @#@F@E. COMPILE 'END'   @#@@@F. COMPILE 'EKX
)@@G@@NDIF' @[@@@E.     @]@G@EM$YEND*   . @^@@@GM$CMPENDIF*         .   @E@@@FKY
)@@G@@          S         X11,IFLINK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @B@F@E      KZ
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,SIF            .   @B@@@F          L,U       A0,MSGELS LA
)@@G@@        .   @D@F@E          TNE,H1    A0,STACK-2,X9     . STACK TOP IF ?LB
)@@G@@@E@@@F          TNE       A0,MSTYPE         . STACK TOP ELSE ?    @C@@@ELC
)@@G@@          J         CEN010            . YES     @E@F@E          L,U     LD
)@@G@@  A0,SEL            . NO - IS IT AN ELSE  @D@@@F          L,U       A0,MLE
)@@G@@SGIFF         . STACK TOP IF ?@B@F@E          TE,H1     A0,STACK-2,X9   LF
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@F          TE        A0,MSTYPE         .   @D@F@E          J LG
)@@G@@        CMP090            . NO - OOPS     @D@@@F          J         IFF9LH
)@@G@@10            . NO - OOPS     @]@@@ECEN010    . @F@H@E          SDFOGA  LI
)@@G@@  M$MPKT            . GET ADDRESS OF 'END' STMT @F@@@H          SDFOGA  LJ
)@@G@@  M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF 'END' STMT @B@F@E          L       LK
)@@G@@  A2,STACK-1,X9     .   @B@@@F          L         A2,MSMSAD         .   LL
)@@G@@@D@F@E          SDFUPD    M$MPKT,CMP092     . UPDATE IT     @F@H@F      LM
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$YUPD        . POINT IF OR ELSE AT ENDIF @F@@@H      LN
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPDATE   . POINT IF OR ELSE AT ENDIF @D@F@E      LO
)@@G@@    AN,U      X9,2              . UNSTACK IT    @D@@@F          JNZ     LP
)@@G@@  A5,IFF999         . IF ERROR SKIP @B@@@F          POP       1         LQ
)@@G@@        .   @D@F@E          SDFO      M$MPKT,CMP092     . OUTPUT IMAGE  LR
)@@G@@@D@H@F          LMJ       X11,M$YOUT        . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@@@H      LS
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @E@F@E          J       LT
)@@G@@  CMPRET            . RETURN TO COMPILER  @E@@@F          J         IFF9LU
)@@G@@99            . RETURN TO COMPILER  @[@@@F.     @]@@@FIFF900    . @B@I@FLV
)@@G@@          L         A5,IFFOVR         .   @B@@@I          L         A5,MLW
)@@G@@$CPSOVR       .   @B@@@F          J         IFF999            .   @[@@@FLX
)@@G@@.     @]@@@FIFF910    . @F@H@F          LMJ       X11,M$YERM        . GELY
)@@G@@NERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @F@@@H          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . GELZ
)@@G@@NERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @[@@@F.     @]@@@FIFF999    . @E@@@F          L MA
)@@G@@        X11,IFLINK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@F          J       MB
)@@G@@  0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@F.     @B@@@FIFLINK    VAR     MC
)@@G@@  'IFLINK',1        .   @B@@@FIFTEMP    VAR       'IFTEMP',1        .   MD
)@@G@@@[@@@I.     @B@@@I          LITS                        .   @[@@@F.     ME
)@@G@@@C@I@FMSGIFF    ALP       'IF&ELSE\ENDI','F&    '     @B@@@IMSGIFF    'IMF
)@@G@@F&ELSE\ENDIF&'            .   @B@I@FMSGELS    ALP       'ELSE&&'        MG
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@IMSGELS    'ELSE&&'                    .   @[@@@F.     @C@I@FMH
)@@G@@IFFOVR    PCW       'MACRO STACK ','OFLO  ' .   @[@I@F.     @B@@@F      MI
)@@G@@    END                         .   ___@@F          LXI,U     A0,MSGIFF MJ
)@@G@@        . SET TYPE TO 'IF'    @E@@@F          DS        A0,MSSTAK       MK
)@@G@@  . STORE ONTO STACK    *[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@B          AXR$                ML
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@B          M$APROC                     .   @B@C@B      MM
)@@G@@    M$ACOMP                     .   @B@D@C          M$COMPILER          MN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@D          M$ACOMPILER                 .   @[@@@B.     MO
)@@G@@@F@@@B. THESE ROUTINES COMPILE THE LOOP CONTROL STATEMENTS.  THE FORMAT MP
)@@G@@@^@@@B. FOR LOOP CONTROL IS : @[@@@B.     @#@@@B.         REPEAT  @^@@@BMQ
)@@G@@.           (BLOCK1)    @ @@@B.         WHILE <EXPRESSION>  @^@@@B.     MR
)@@G@@      (BLOCK2)    @#@@@B.         LOOP    @[@@@B.     @G@@@B. BLOCK1 IS MS
)@@G@@EXECUTED, THEN THE EXPRESSION IS EVALUATED.  IF IT EVALUATES@F@@@B. TO AMT
)@@G@@ TRUE VALUE BLOCK2 IS EXECUTED, FOLLOWED BY BLOCK1 AGAIN AD @F@@@B. NAUSMU
)@@G@@EUM.  WHEN THE EXPRESSION EVALUATES TO A FALSE VALUE CONTROL@C@@@B. PASSMV
)@@G@@ES TO THE STATEMENT FOLLOWING THE LOOP.   @[@@@B.     @F@@@B. THE WHILE MW
)@@G@@MAY BE REPLACED BY AN UNTIL, WHICH HAS THE EFFECT OF  @F@@@B. REVERSING MX
)@@G@@THE SENSE OF THE TEST, I.E., EXIT WILL OCCUR WHEN THE @^@@@B. EXPRESSIONMY
)@@G@@ GOES TRUE. @[@@@B.     @ @@@A. COMPILE 'REPEAT' STATEMENT  @[@@@A.     MZ
)@@G@@@G@B@ASRP       EQU       4                 . REPEAT AND NO CONDITION SENA
)@@G@@EN    @F@B@ASWU       EQU       5                 . REPEAT AND CONDITIONNB
)@@G@@ SEEN @[@@@A.     @]@B@AM$YREP*     @]@C@BM$YREP*   . @^@@@CM$CMPREPEAT*NC
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@B          S         X11,REPLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADND
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@B          PUSH      REP900            . PUSH DATA ONTO STACKNE
)@@G@@@G@D@A          SDFOGA    M$MPKT            . GET ADDRESS OF 'REPEAT' IMNF
)@@G@@AGE   @G@@@D          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDRESS OF 'REPENG
)@@G@@AT' IMAGE   @D@B@A          L         A0,M$BLIN         . GET LINE #    NH
)@@G@@@D@@@B          L         A0,M$YLIN         . GET LINE #    @F@B@A      NI
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,SRP            . SET STACK TYPE 'REPEAT'   @F@@@B      NJ
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A0,MSGREP         . SET STACK TYPE 'REPEAT'   @D@B@A      NK
)@@G@@    DS        A0,STACK,*X9      . STACK ENTRY   @D@@@B          DS      NL
)@@G@@  A0,MSSTAK         . STACK ENTRY   @D@B@A          SDFO      M$MPKT,CMPNM
)@@G@@092     . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@D@B          LMJ       X11,M$YOUT        . OUNN
)@@G@@TPUT IMAGE  @D@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  NO
)@@G@@@E@B@A          J         CMPRET            . RETURN TO COMPILER  @E@@@BNP
)@@G@@          J         REP999            . RETURN TO COMPILER  @[@B@A.     NQ
)@@G@@@ @B@A. COMPILE 'LOOP' STATEMENT    @[@B@A.     @]@B@AM$YLOO*   . @F@B@ANR
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,SWU            . GET TYPE CONDITION SEEN   @E@B@ANS
)@@G@@          TE,H1     A0,STACK-2,X9     . WAS CONDITION SEEN  @C@B@A      NT
)@@G@@    J         CMP090            . NOPE    @G@B@A          L         A2,SNU
)@@G@@TACK-3,X9     . GET ADDRESS OF THE 'REPEAT'     @F@B@A          S       NV
)@@G@@  A2,M$BADR         . POINT 'LOOP' AT 'REPEAT'  @D@B@A          SDFO    NW
)@@G@@  M$MPKT,CMP092     . OUTPUT IMAGE  @H@B@A          SDFOGA    M$MPKT    NX
)@@G@@        . GET ADDRESS OF IMAGE AFTER 'LOOP'     @B@B@A          L       NY
)@@G@@  A2,STACK-1,X9     .   @G@B@A          SDFUPD    M$MPKT,CMP092     . PONZ
)@@G@@INT 'REPEAT' AFTER 'LOOP'     @D@B@A          AN,U      X9,4            OA
)@@G@@  . POP STACK     @E@B@A          J         CMPRET            . RETURN TOB
)@@G@@O COMPILER  @[@@@A.     @B@@@A. COMPILE 'WHILE' AND 'UNTIL' STATEMENTS  OC
)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @]@B@AM$YWHI*     @]@C@BM$YWHI*   . @^@@@CM$CMPWHILE*       OD
)@@G@@  .   @]@C@AM$YUNT*   . @^@@@CM$CMPUNTIL*         .   @E@@@B          S OE
)@@G@@        X11,REPLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @H@B@A          L,U     OF
)@@G@@  A0,SRP            . IS STACKTOP REPEAT WITHOUT CONDN ?    @G@@@B      OG
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,MSGREP         . IS STACKTOP REPEAT WITHOUT CONDN@B@B@AOH
)@@G@@          TE,H1     A0,STACK-2,X9     .   @B@@@B          TE        A0,MOI
)@@G@@STYPE         .   @D@B@A          J         CMP090            . NO - ERROJ
)@@G@@OR    @D@@@B          J         REP910            . NO - ERROR    @F@@@BOK
)@@G@@          PUSH      REP900            . PUSH WHILE ONTO STACK     @H@B@AOL
)@@G@@          SDFOGA    M$MPKT            . GET ADDRESS OF 'WHILE' OR 'UNTILOM
)@@G@@'     @G@D@B          SDFOGA    M$MPKT            . GET ADDR OF 'WHILE' ON
)@@G@@OR 'UNTIL'  @G@@@D          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET       . GET ADDR OF 'WOO
)@@G@@HILE' OR 'UNTIL'  @E@B@A          L         A0,M$BLIN         . GET IMAGOP
)@@G@@E NUMBER    @E@@@B          L         A0,M$YLIN         . GET IMAGE NUMBOQ
)@@G@@ER    @E@B@A          LXI,U     A0,SWU            . SET CONDITION SEEN  OR
)@@G@@@E@@@B          LXI,U     A0,MSGWHU         . SET CONDITION SEEN  @E@B@AOS
)@@G@@          DS        A0,STACK,*X9      . SET IT ONTO STACK   @E@@@B      OT
)@@G@@    DS        A0,MSSTAK         . SET IT ONTO STACK   @D@B@A          SDOU
)@@G@@FO      M$MPKT,CMP092     . WRITE IMATE   @D@D@B          LMJ       X11,OV
)@@G@@M$YOUT        . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOUTPUT OW
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@B@A          J         CMPRET            . AND RETUOX
)@@G@@RN    @D@@@B          J         REP999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@BOY
)@@G@@.     @ @@@B. COMPILE 'LOOP' STATEMENT    @[@@@B.     @]@C@BM$YLOO*   . OZ
)@@G@@@]@@@CM$CMPLOOP*  @E@@@B          S         X11,REPLNK        . SAVE RETPA
)@@G@@URN ADDRESS @F@@@B          L,U       A0,MSGWHU         . GET TYPE CONDIPB
)@@G@@TION SEEN   @E@@@B          TE        A0,MSTYPE         . WAS CONDITION PC
)@@G@@SEEN  @C@@@B          J         REP910            . NOPE    @G@@@B      PD
)@@G@@    L         A0,MSMSAD         . GET MASS STORAGE ADDR OF 'WHILE'@D@@@BPE
)@@G@@          S         A0,REPTMP         . SAVE IT TEMP  @E@@@B          POPF
)@@G@@P       1                 . GET TO REPEAT ENTRY @F@@@B          L       PG
)@@G@@  A2,MSMSAD         . GET ADDRESS OF REPEAT     @F@@@B          S       PH
)@@G@@  A2,M$YADR         . POINT 'LOOP' AT 'REPEAT'  @D@D@B          LMJ     PI
)@@G@@  X11,M$YOUT        . OUTPUT IMAGE  @D@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$CMPOPJ
)@@G@@UTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE  @G@D@B          SDFOGA    M$MPKT            . GEPK
)@@G@@T ADDR OF IMAGE AFTER 'LOOP'  @G@@@D          SDFOGA    M$OUTPACKET     PL
)@@G@@  . GET ADDR OF IMAGE AFTER 'LOOP'  @E@@@B          L         A2,REPTMP PM
)@@G@@        . GET ADDRESS OF WHILE@G@D@B          LMJ       X11,M$YUPD      PN
)@@G@@  . POINT 'REPEAT' AFTER 'LOOP'     @G@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$CMPUPO
)@@G@@PDATE   . POINT 'REPEAT' AFTER 'LOOP'     @D@@@B          POP       1   PP
)@@G@@              . POP STACK     @E@@@B          J         REP999          PQ
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO COMPILER  @[@@@A.     @]@@@BREP900    . @D@E@B          L PR
)@@G@@        A5,REPOVR         . STACK OFLO    @D@@@E          L         A5,MPS
)@@G@@$CPSOVR       . STACK OFLO    @B@@@B          J         REP999          PT
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@B.     @]@@@BREP910    . @F@D@B          LMJ       X11,M$YERMPU
)@@G@@        . GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @F@@@D          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMPV
)@@G@@SGCMP   . GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE    @[@@@B.     @]@@@BREP999    . @E@@@BPW
)@@G@@          L         X11,REPLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @C@@@B      PX
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@B.     @B@@@BREPLNK    VAPY
)@@G@@R       'REPLNK',1        .   @B@@@BREPTMP    VAR       'REPTMP',1      PZ
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@B.     @B@@@E          LITS                        .   @[@@@EQA
)@@G@@.     @D@E@BMSGREP    ALP       'REPEAT&WHILE','\UNTIL&     ' .   @B@@@EQB
)@@G@@MSGREP    'REPEAT&WHILE\UNTIL&'       .   @C@E@BMSGWHU    ALP       'WHIQC
)@@G@@LE\UNTIL&','LOOP& ' .   @B@@@EMSGWHU    'WHILE\UNTIL&LOOP&'         .   QD
)@@G@@@[@@@B.     @C@E@BREPOVR    PCW       'MACRO STACK ','OFLO  ' .   @[@E@BQE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@B          END                         .   ___     A0,SRP    QF
)@@G@@        . SET STACK TYPE 'REPEAT'   @F@@@B          LXI,U     A0,MSGREP QG
)@@G@@        . SET STACK TYPE 'REPEAT'   @D@B@A      *[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@X      QH
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@Y@X          PROX                QI
)@@G@@        .   @B@Y@X          MACROP                      .   @B@@@Y      QJ

)@@G@@        . GET LETAT     @B@@@Y          M$ADESCR                    .   QL
)@@G@@@B@@@Y          M$AMODES                    .   @G@Y@XCHGCMD    EQU     QM
)@@G@@  1                 . SET TO 1 FOR CHANGE COMMAND     @[@Y@X.     @[@@@YQN
)@@G@@.     @F@Y@X. THIS ELEMENT PROCESSES ALL SUBSCRIPTING OPERATORS, INCLUDIQO
)@@G@@NG    @B@@@X. THE 'LET' COMMAND, WHOSE SYNTAX IS :    @[@@@X.     @#@@@XQP
)@@G@@. LET VAR := EXPR @[@@@X.     @C@Y@X. WHERE VAR ::= IDENT ! @EXPR ! IDENQQ
)@@G@@T(EXPR)     @A@@@Y. WHERE VAR ::= IDENT !  IDENT(EXPR)@[@@@X.     @B@@@XQR
)@@G@@          INSTRS                      .   @]@Y@XLET*      . @]@@@YM$COMLQS
)@@G@@ET* . @E@@@Y          S         X11,LETLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS QT
)@@G@@@F@Y@X          SZ        INDFLG            . CLEAR INDIRECT ':' FLAG   QU
)@@G@@@F@Y@X          LMJ       X11,PRIM          . SCAN NEXT ITEM ON LINE    QV
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          LMJ       X11,M$SCANPRIM    . SCAN NEXT ITEM ON LINE    QW
)@@G@@@E@Y@X          J         COMERR            . ERROR IN COMMAND    @E@@@YQX
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,LET999         . ERROR IN COMMAND    @E@@@Y      QY
)@@G@@    S         A4,LETCOL         . SET COLUMN NUMBER   @[@@@).     @D@@@)QZ
)@@G@@. IF USER LET @ PROCESSING CALL HIM WHEN M$OPERAT SEEN@[@@@).     @B@@@)RA
)@@G@@          ON        LETAT             .   @D@@@)          TE,U      A1,MRB
)@@G@@$OPERAT       . IS IT @ OP    @D@@@)          J         LET005          RC
)@@G@@  . NO - SKIP     @F@@@)          LMJ       X11,M$USERLETAT   . YES - CARD
)@@G@@LL USER ROUTINE   @D@@@)          J         LET999            . AND RETURE
)@@G@@RN    @]@@@)LET005    . @B@@@)          OFF       LETAT             .   RF
)@@G@@@[@@@).     @A@@@). FIRST THING MUST BE IDENTIFIER    @[@@@).     @F@@@YRG
)@@G@@          L         A5,LETENI         . ERROR - NOT IDENTIFIER    @E@Y@XRH
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,MODNAM         . IS IT NAME-LABEL ?  @E@@@Y      RI
)@@G@@    TE,U      A0,MODNAM         . IS IT NAME-LABEL ?  @D@@@Y          J RJ
)@@G@@        LET090            . SYNTAX ERROR  @D@Y@X          J         LET1RK
)@@G@@00            . YES - SCAN    @E@Y@X          TE,U      A0,MODOPR       RL
)@@G@@  . IS IT AN OPERATOR ? @E@Y@X          J         ERRSYN            . NORM
)@@G@@ - SYNTAX ERROR   @E@Y@X          L         A0,CSADDR         . GET OPERRN
)@@G@@ATOR NAME   @G@Y@X          TE,U      A0,DYFDMP         . IS IT THE CORERO
)@@G@@ PICTURE OPER ?   @D@Y@X          J         ERRSYN            . NO - ERRRP
)@@G@@OR    @[@Y@X.     @A@Y@X. LET @EXPR . . .   SCAN FOR EXPR   @[@Y@X.     RQ
)@@G@@@C@Y@X          LMJ       X11,SCAN          . GET IT  @E@Y@X          J RR
)@@G@@        COMERR            . ERROR SCANNING IT   @D@Y@X          TE,U    RS
)@@G@@  A3,':'            . OPERATOR ?    @D@Y@X          J         ERRSYN    RT
)@@G@@        . SYNTAX ERROR  @G@Y@X          S         A3,INDFLG         . SERU
)@@G@@T FLAG THAT SAYS GO INTO DUMP @F@Y@X          L,U       A0,CSDESC       RV
)@@G@@  . GET INTEGER VALUE OF EXP  @E@Y@X          LMJ       X11,CVTINT      RW
)@@G@@  . CONVERT TO INTEGER  @C@Y@X          J         COMERR            . OORX
)@@G@@PS    @D@Y@X          L         A1,0,A1           . GET ITS VALUE @C@Y@XRY
)@@G@@          S         A1,INDADR         . SET IT  @F@Y@X          J       RZ
)@@G@@  LET200            . PROCESS SECOND EXPRESSION @[@Y@X.     @C@Y@X. LET SA
)@@G@@IDENT . . . SCAN FOR POSSIBLE SUBSCRIPTING@[@Y@X.     @]@Y@XLET100    . SB
)@@G@@@E@@@X          DL        A0,0,A1           . GET NAME OF IDENT   @F@@@YSC
)@@G@@          DS        A0,LETNAM         . SAVE NAME TOBE STORED INTO@G@Y@XSD
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,STLOOK        . LOOK IT UP IN THE SYMBOL TABLE  SE
)@@G@@@F@Y@X          LMJ       X11,STMAKE        . IF NO ENTRY FOUND MAKE ONESF
)@@G@@@H@Y@X          S         A2,INDADR         . SAVE ADDRESS OF ITEM TO BESG
)@@G@@ STORED     @E@Y@X          LMJ       X11,PRIM          . GET NEXT PRIMISH
)@@G@@TIVE  @E@@@Y          LMJ       X11,M$SCANPRIM    . GET NEXT PRIMITIVE  SI
)@@G@@@C@Y@X          J         COMERR            . ERROR   @C@@@Y          JNSJ
)@@G@@Z       A5,LET999         . ERROR   @E@@@Y          TNE,U     A1,M$OPEROSK

)@@G@@  .   @F@@@Y          L         A5,LETENS         . ERROR - NO STORE OPESN
)@@G@@RATION@E@@@Y          TE,U      A1,M$OPERSTORE    . IS IT STORE OPERATORSO
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          J         LET090            . NO - SYNTAX ERROR   @[@@@YSP
)@@G@@.     @F@@@Y. NORMAL (UNSUBSCRIPTED) STORE.  SCAN EXPRESSION TO BE STORESQ
)@@G@@D.    @[@@@Y.     @E@@@Y          LMJ       X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN FORSR
)@@G@@ EXPRESSION @C@@@Y          JNZ       A5,LET999         . ERROR   @[@@@YSS
)@@G@@.     @C@@@Y. LOOK UP VARIABLE.  IF NOT FOUND MAKE ONE.     @[@@@Y.     ST
)@@G@@@C@@@Y          DL        A0,LETNAM         . GET NAME@E@@@Y          LMSU
)@@G@@J       X11,M$VARSEARCH   . SEARCH SYMBOL TABLE @C@@@Y          JNZ     SV

)@@G@@KE GLOBAL THEN    @C@@@Y          JNZ       A5,LET999         . IF ERRORSY
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @C@@@Y. SET VALUE OF VARIABLE TO VALUE OF EXPRESSION. @[@@@YSZ
)@@G@@.     @]@@@YLET010    . @D@@@Y          L,U       A1,CSDESC         . GETA

)@@G@@@E@@@Y. SUBSCRIPTED STORE.  LOOK UP VARIABLE WHICH MUST BE THERE. @[@@@YTF

)@@G@@TO BE STORED INTO @F@@@Y          AN,U      A0,0,A3           . FIND REMUM
)@@G@@AINDER LENGTH     @[@@@Y.     @C@@@Y. IF SECOND SUBSCRIPT IS -0 (*) USE UN
)@@G@@REMAINDER.  @[@@@Y.     @D@@@Y          JNZ       A4,$+3            . SKUO
)@@G@@IP IF NOT -0@D@@@Y          JP        A4,$+2            . SKIP IF NOT -0UP
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          L         A4,A0             . GET REMAINDER @[@@@Y.     UQ
)@@G@@@ @@@Y. TEST SUBSCRIPT WITHIN RANGE @[@@@Y.     @D@@@Y          JN      UR

)@@G@@@[@Y@X/.    @[@Y@X.     @G@Y@X. THIS FUNCTION HANDLES THE LEFT-PAREN DYABT
)@@G@@DIC OPERATOR.  IF THE LEFTARG @H@Y@X. DATATYPE IS NULL, THEN THIS IS A SBU
)@@G@@ET OF ARITHMETIC PARENTHESIS AND THE VALUE@H@Y@X. ON THE STACK IS MERELYBV
)@@G@@ LEFT THERE.  IF THE LEFTARG IS AN ARRAY OR A STRING  @I@Y@X. THEN SUBSCBW

)@@G@@@E@Y@X. AND MUST BE SCANNED PAST AT THE END OF THE OPERATION.     @[@Y@XBY

)@@G@@U       A0,0,A2           .   @F@L@K          L         A0,M$XTRN,A0    WD
)@@G@@  . GET TRANSLATE ROUTINE     @F@@@L          L         A0,M$CONVXQT,A0 WE
)@@G@@  . GET TRANSLATE ROUTINE     @F@@@M          L         A5,M$CONVERR    WF
)@@G@@  . GET MODE ERROR MESSAGE    @C@@@M          JZ        A0,CMP999       WG
)@@G@@  . OOPS    @D@@@K          S         A0,CMPLAX         . SET TRANSLATE WH
)@@G@@@D@@@K          L         R1,LALONG         . PICK UP LENGTH@[@@@K.     WI
)@@G@@@ @@@K. SETUP POINTERS AT RIGHTARG. @[@@@K.     @E@@@K          L       WJ
)@@G@@  X10,RAADDR        . POINT INDEX AT VALUE@D@@@K          LXI,U     X10,WK
)@@G@@1             . INCREMENT     @^@@@K          DON       .   @E@@@K      WL
)@@G@@    TEP,U     A1,DBLBIT         . DOUBLE PRECISION    @D@@@K          LXWM
)@@G@@I,U     X10,2             . INCREMENT     @^@@@K          DOF       .   WN
)@@G@@@F@@@K          LSSL      A1,2              . MAKE TRANSLATION INDEX    WO
)@@G@@@B@@@K          A,U       A1,0,A2           .   @F@L@K          L       WP
)@@G@@  A1,M$XTRN,A1      . GET TRANSLATION ROUTINE   @F@@@L          L       WQ
)@@G@@  A1,M$CONVXQT,A1   . GET TRANSLATION ROUTINE   @F@@@M          L       WR

)@@G@@  .   @D@@@K          L         R2,RALONG         . GET LENGTH    @E@@@KWU
)@@G@@          LDSL      A1,36             . RESULT MODE TO A1   @[@@@K.     WV
)@@G@@@E@@@K. ACTUAL NUMERIC COMPARISON.  COMPARISON CONTINUES UNTIL ONE@E@@@KWW
)@@G@@. IS DECIDED GREATER OR BOTH ARE EXHAUSTED.  THE SHORTER IS @^@@@K. EXTEWX
)@@G@@NDED WITH ZEROS.  @[@@@K.     @]@@@KCMP010    . @E@@@K          L,U     WY
)@@G@@  A0,2              . SET TO EXIT IF DONE @F@@@K          JGD       R2,CWZ
)@@G@@MP020         . IF MORE RIGHTARG GET IT   @E@@@K          DSL       A3,7XA
)@@G@@2             . ZERO EXTEND RIGHTARG@B@@@K          J         CMP030    XB
)@@G@@        .   @]@@@KCMP020    . @F@@@K          XDL       A3,0,*X10       XC
)@@G@@  . GET RIGHTARG AND INCREMENT@D@@@K          EX        CMPRAX          XD
)@@G@@  . TRANSLATE IT  @E@@@K          L,U       A0,0              . SET FLAGXE
)@@G@@ MORE LEFT  @]@@@KCMP030    . @F@@@K          XDS       A3,CMPTMP       XF

)@@G@@  . TRANSLATE LEFTARG   @D@@@K          L,U       A0,0              . FLXL
)@@G@@AG MORE LEFT@]@@@KCMP050    . @C@@@K          EX        SUBTAB,A1       XM
)@@G@@  . SUBTRACT@D@@@K          EX        JMPTAB,A1         . JZ A3,CMP060  XN
)@@G@@@[@@@K.     @C@@@K. ONE IS GREATER HERE DEPENDING ON SIGN OF A3.  @[@@@KXO
)@@G@@.     @E@@@K          L,U       A0,4              . SET GREATER THAN    XP
)@@G@@@E@@@K          JP        A3,CMP060         . IF NEGATIVE THEN    @D@@@KXQ
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,1              . SET LESS THAN @[@@@K.     @^@@@KXR
)@@G@@. AT THIS POINT A0 =    @D@@@K. 0 - EQUAL SO FAR AND AT LEAST ONE ARG STXS
)@@G@@ILL HAS DATA@#@@@K. 1 - LESS THAN   @A@@@K. 2 - EQUAL SO FAR AND BOTH ARXT
)@@G@@GS OUT@#@@@K. 4 - GREATER THAN@[@@@K.     @]@@@KCMP060    . @E@@@K      XU
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,CMP010         . IF MORE GO DO IT    @F@@@K          J XV
)@@G@@        CMP200            . TEST IF THIS IS RIGHT ONE @[@@@K/.    @[@@@KXW
)@@G@@.     @D@@@K. STRING COMPARISON.  FOR NOW THEY MUST BE SAME MODE. @[@@@KXX
)@@G@@.     @]@@@KCMP100    . @E@@@K          AND,U     A1,ALPBIT+ASCBIT  . GEXY
)@@G@@T ALPHA MODES     @B@@@K          AND,U     A0,ALPBIT+ASCBIT  .   @E@@@KXZ
)@@G@@          TE,U      A1,0,A2           . ALPHA MODES EQUAL   @D@@@K      YA
)@@G@@    J         CMP999            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@K.     @F@@@K      YB
)@@G@@    L         A1,M$XFDL         . GET FIELDATA LOAD TABLE   @E@@@K      YC
)@@G@@    L,U       R3,05             . AND FIELDATA BLANK  @D@@@K          TOYD
)@@G@@P,U     A2,ASCBIT         . UNLESS ASCII  @D@@@K          J         CMP1YE
)@@G@@05            . THEN SKIP     @F@@@K          L         A1,M$XASL       YF

)@@G@@  . AND ASCII BLANK     @]@@@KCMP105    . @[@@@K.     @^@@@K. POINT AT LYH
)@@G@@EFTARG.     @[@@@K.     @D@@@K          L         A0,LAADDR         . GEYI
)@@G@@T ADDRESS   @D@@@K          DS        A0,CMPLAX         . SAVE INDEX    YJ
)@@G@@@D@@@K          L         R1,LALONG         . GET LENGTH    @[@@@K.     YK
)@@G@@@^@@@K. POINT AT RIGHTARG.    @[@@@K.     @D@@@K          L         A0,RYL
)@@G@@AADDR         . GET ADDRESS   @D@@@K          DS        A0,CMPRAX       YM
)@@G@@  . SAVE INDEX    @D@@@K          L         R2,RALONG         . GET LENGYN
)@@G@@TH    @[@@@K.     @ @@@K. ACTUALLY DO COMPARISON.     @[@@@K.     @]@@@KYO
)@@G@@CMP110    . @F@@@K          L,U       A3,2              . SET EQUAL AND YP
)@@G@@EXITING     @D@@@K          JGD       R2,CMP120         . COUNT RIGHTARGYQ
)@@G@@@E@@@K          L         A5,R3             . OUT - BLANKFILL     @B@@@KYR
)@@G@@          J         CMP130            .   @]@@@KCMP120    . @D@@@K      YS
)@@G@@    DL        A0,CMPRAX         . GET INDEX     @D@@@K          EX      YT
)@@G@@  0,*A1             . GET CHAR IN A5@D@@@K          DS        A0,CMPRAX YU
)@@G@@        . SAVE INDEX    @E@@@K          L,U       A3,0              . SEYV
)@@G@@T FLAG MORE HERE  @]@@@KCMP130    . @D@@@K          S         A5,CMPTMP YW

)@@G@@UNT LEFTARG @F@@@K          L         A5,R3             . NONE LEFT RETUYY
)@@G@@RN BLANK    @B@@@K          J         CMP150            .   @]@@@KCMP140YZ
)@@G@@    . @D@@@K          DL        A0,CMPLAX         . GET INDEX     @D@@@KZA
)@@G@@          EX        0,*A1             . GET CHAR IN A5@D@@@K          DSZB

)@@G@@        A5,CMPTMP         . COMPARE CHARACTERS  @C@@@K          JZ      ZE
)@@G@@  A5,CMP160         . EQUAL   @C@@@K          L,U       A3,4            ZF
)@@G@@  . GREATER @B@@@K          JP        A5,CMP160         .   @D@@@K      ZG
)@@G@@    L,U       A3,1              . LESS THAN     @]@@@KCMP160    . @E@@@KZH
)@@G@@          JZ        A3,CMP110         . IF MORE LOOK AT THEM@F@@@K      ZI
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,0,A3           . GET RESULT OF COMPARISON  @[@@@K/.    ZJ
)@@G@@@[@@@K.     @E@@@K. AT THIS POINT A0 HAS ONE OF THREE BITS SET TO THE ACZK
)@@G@@TUAL  @E@@@K. RESULT OF THE COMPARISON.  DO AND WITH MODE WANTED TO FORMZL
)@@G@@@ @@@K. BOOLEAN VALUE FOR RESULT.   @^@@@K. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@KZM
)@@G@@.     @]@@@KCMP200    . @E@@@K          AND       A0,CMPMOD         . ISZN
)@@G@@ ACTUAL ONE OF HIS@D@@@K          S         A1,CMPMOD         . SAVE IT ZO
)@@G@@AGAIN @F@@@K          TGET      1                 . GET ONE WORD ON TEMPZP
)@@G@@ STACK@C@@@K          JNZ       A5,CMP999         . OOPS    @D@@@K      ZQ
)@@G@@    L         A0,(MODSIN,0,0,0,0,0) . SET MODE  @C@@@K          DS      ZR
)@@G@@  A0,LADESC         . SAVE IT @E@@@K          L,U       A0,0            ZS
)@@G@@  . GET BOOLEAN FALSE   @E@@@K          TZ        CMPMOD            . OPZT
)@@G@@ERATION TRUE ?    @E@@@K          L,U       A0,1              . GET BOOLZU
)@@G@@EAN TRUE    @E@@@K          S         A0,0,A1           . SAVE RESULT MOZV
)@@G@@DE    @E@@@K          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    ZW

)@@G@@    . @E@@@K          L         X11,CMPLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  ZY
)@@G@@@E@@@K          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @F@K@JZZ
)@@G@@          TN        LADESC            . IS LEFTARG OR RIGHTARG    @E@K@JAA
)@@G@@          TP        RADESC            . A PSEUDOVALUE ?     @E@K@J      AB

)@@G@@  A1,RAMODE         . GET MODE OF RITEARG @F@K@J          TOP,U     A0,AAE
)@@G@@LPBIT         . IS EITHER ARG ALPHA ?     @B@K@J          TEP,U     A1,AAF
)@@G@@LPBIT         .   @D@K@J          J         MODERR            . JMP TO EAG
)@@G@@RROR  @F@K@J          OR,U      A1,0,A0           . COMPUTE MODE FOR TESAH
)@@G@@TING  @F@K@J          LMJ       X11,DYFCLA        . CONVERT AND LOAD ARGAI
)@@G@@UMENTS@D@K@J          EX        DFSTBL,A1         . SUBTRACT ARGS @E@K@JAJ
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,02             . CONDITION - EQUAL   @D@K@J      AK
)@@G@@    EX        DFCTBL,A1         . COMPARE EQUAL @F@K@J          L,U     AL
)@@G@@  A0,01             . CONDITION - LESS THAN     @D@K@J          JN      AM
)@@G@@  A2,DFT020         . LESS THAN     @F@K@J          L,U       A0,04     AN
)@@G@@        . CONDITION - GREATER THAN  @E@K@JDFT020    L,U       A2,0      AO
)@@G@@        . SET VALUE FALSE     @F@K@J          AND       A0,DYFMOD       AP
)@@G@@  . WAS CONDITION SATISFIED ? @F@K@J          JZ        A1,$+2          AQ
)@@G@@  . CONDITION SATISFIED ?     @E@K@J          L,U       A2,1            AR
)@@G@@  . YES - SET VALUE TRUE@B@K@J          LXI,U     X10,1             .   AS
)@@G@@@B@K@J          S         X10,LAVALU        .   @B@K@J          S       AT
)@@G@@  A2,0,*X10         .   @E@K@J          L,U       A0,MODSIN         . SEAU
)@@G@@T MODE TO INTEGER @C@K@J          S         A0,LAMODE         . SET MODEAV
)@@G@@@D@K@J          POP       2                 . POP STACK     @F@K@J      AW
)@@G@@    J         DYFEND            . END OF DYADIC FUNCTION    @[@@@K.     AX
)@@G@@@B@@@KSUBTAB    AN        A3,CMPTMP         .   @[@@@K.     @^@@@K      AY
)@@G@@    FON       .   @B@@@K          FAN       A3,CMPTMP         .   @^@@@KAZ
)@@G@@          FOF       .   @[@@@K.     @^@@@K          DON       .   @B@@@KBA
)@@G@@          DAN       A3,CMPTMP         .   @[@@@K.     @B@@@K          DFBB
)@@G@@AN      A3,CMPTMP         .   @^@@@K          DOF       .   @[@@@K.     BC
)@@G@@@B@@@KJMPTAB    JZ        A3,CMP060         .   @[@@@K.     @^@@@K      BD

)@@G@@          DJZ       A3,CMP060         .   @[@@@K.     @B@@@K          DJBG
)@@G@@Z       A3,CMP060         .   @^@@@K          DOF       .   @[@@@K.     BH
)@@G@@@C@N@KCMPMER    PCW       'WRONG ARG MO','DES   '     @[@N@K.     @B@@@KBI
)@@G@@CMPLNK    VAR       'CMPLNK',1        .   @F@@@KCMPMOD    VAR       'CMPBJ
)@@G@@MOD',1        . MODE HE WANTS TO TEST     @D@@@KCMPTMP    VAR       'CMPBK
)@@G@@TMP',2        . TEMP STORAGE  @F@@@KCMPLAX    VAR       'CMPLAX',2      BL
)@@G@@  . LEFT INDEX OR TRANSLATE   @F@@@KCMPRAX    VAR       'CMPRAX',2      BM
)@@G@@  . RITE INDEX OR TRANSLATE   @[@@@N.     @B@@@N          LITS          BN
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@N.     @B@@@NCMPMER    PCM       1               BO
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@N          'ARGUMENTS HAVE NON-COMPARABLE TYPES.' .    @B@@@NBP
)@@G@@          ENDPCM                      .   @[@@@N.     @[@N@K.     @B@@@KBQ
)@@G@@          END                         .   ___AX         . SAVE INDEX    BR
)@@G@@@E@@@K          L,U       A3,0              . SE*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@#      BS
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@#          M$APROC             BT
)@@G@@        .   @B@^@#          M$ADESC                     .   @B@@@^      BU
)@@G@@    M$ADESCR                    .   @B@^@#          M$ASCAN             BV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@^          M$ASCANNER                  .   @[@@@#.     BW
)@@G@@@F@@@#. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO PROCESS THE LOGICAL OPERATIONS OF AND BX
)@@G@@@F@@@#. OR AND XOR.  THE ARGUMENTS MUST BE THE SAME LENGTH AND MUST BE  BY
)@@G@@@F@@@#. BOOLEAN TRUE OR FALSE WHICH MEANS INTEGER ZERO OR ONE.  THE NOT BZ
)@@G@@@H@@@#. MONADIC OPERATOR IS PROCESSED HERE ALSO AND CONFORMS TO THE SAMECA
)@@G@@ ARGUMENT   @G@@@#. CONVENTION.  NOTE THAT LENGTHS OTHER THAN ONE ARE ALCB
)@@G@@LOWED HERE BUT THE@H@@@#. BOOLEAN VALUE MUST HAVE LENGTH ONE TO USE IN CCC
)@@G@@ONTROL STRUCTURE (IF, ETC).   @[@@@#.     @^@@@^M$OPERLOGAND*       .   CD
)@@G@@@D@^@#M$LAND*   L         A0,LOGAND         . GET AND INSTR @D@@@^      CE
)@@G@@    L         A0,LOGAND         . GET AND INSTR @B@@@#          J       CF
)@@G@@  LOG010            .   @^@@@^M$OPERLOGOR*        .   @D@^@#M$LIOR*   L CG
)@@G@@        A0,LOGIOR         . GET OR INSTR  @D@@@^          L         A0,LCH
)@@G@@OGIOR         . GET OR INSTR  @B@@@#          J         LOG010          CI
)@@G@@  .   @^@@@^M$OPERLOGXOR*       .   @D@^@#M$LXOR*   L         A0,LOGXOR CJ
)@@G@@        . GET XOR INSTR @D@@@^          L         A0,LOGXOR         . GECK
)@@G@@T XOR INSTR @F@@@#LOG010    S         A0,LOGXQT         . SAVE PROCESSINCL
)@@G@@G ROUTINE   @E@@@#          S         X11,LOGLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADCM
)@@G@@DRESS @[@@@#.     @C@@@#. ARGUMENTS MUST BE INTEGERS OF SAME LENGTH.    CN
)@@G@@@[@@@#.     @E@@@#          L         A0,LAMODE         . GET LEFTARG MOCO
)@@G@@DE    @E@@@#          L         A1,RAMODE         . GET RIGHTARG MODE   CP
)@@G@@@F@@@#          L         A5,LOGEMD         . GET MODE ERROR MESSAGE    CQ
)@@G@@@D@@@#          TNE,U     A0,MODSIN         . BOTH MUST     @D@@@#      CR
)@@G@@    TE,U      A1,MODSIN         . BE INTEGERS   @D@@@#          J       CS
)@@G@@  LOG999            . IF NOT ERROR  @E@@@#          L         A0,LALONG CT
)@@G@@        . GET LEFTARG LENGTH  @F@@@#          L         A5,LOGELN       CU
)@@G@@  . GET LENGTH ERROR MESSAGE  @E@@@#          TE        A0,RALONG       CV
)@@G@@  . ARE LENGTHS EQUAL   @D@@@#          J         LOG999            . NOCW
)@@G@@ - ERROR    @F@@@#          TGET                        . GET TEMP SPACECX
)@@G@@ FOR RESULT @E@@@#          JNZ       A5,LOG999         . IF ERROR RETURCY
)@@G@@N     @F@@@#          L         X9,LAADDR         . GET POINTERS TO LEFTCZ
)@@G@@ARG   @D@@@#          L         X10,RAADDR        . AND RIGHTARG  @B@@@#DA
)@@G@@          LXI,U     X9,1              .   @B@@@#          LXI,U     X10,DB
)@@G@@1             .   @E@@@#          S         A1,LAADDR         . SET RESUDC
)@@G@@LT ADDRESS  @B@@@#          LXI,U     A1,1              .   @G@@@#      DD
)@@G@@    L         A5,LOGELV         . GET ERROR MESSAGE FOR VALUE     @D@@@#DE
)@@G@@          J         LOG050            . AND ENTER LOOP@[@@@#.     @D@@@#DF
)@@G@@. DO OPERATION.  IF ANY ARG IS NOT ZERO OR ONE ERROR. @[@@@#.     @]@@@#DG
)@@G@@LOG020    . @D@@@#          L         A3,0,*X9          . GET LEFTARG   DH
)@@G@@@D@@@#          JZ        A3,LOG030         . IF ZERO SKIP  @E@@@#      DI
)@@G@@    TE,U      A3,1              . ELSE MUST BE ONE    @C@@@#          J DJ
)@@G@@        LOG999            . ERROR   @]@@@#LOG030    . @D@@@#          L DK
)@@G@@        A4,0,*X10         . GET RIGHTARG  @D@@@#          JZ        A4,LDL
)@@G@@OG040         . IF ZERO SKIP  @E@@@#          TE,U      A4,1            DM
)@@G@@  . ELSE MUST BE ONE    @C@@@#          J         LOG999            . ERDN
)@@G@@ROR   @]@@@#LOG040    . @E@@@#          EX        LOGXQT            . GEDO
)@@G@@T RESULT IN A4    @D@@@#          S         A4,0,*A1          . SAVE RESDP
)@@G@@ULT   @C@@@#LOG050    JGD       A0,LOG020         . COUNT IT@[@@@#.     DQ
)@@G@@@F@@@#          L         A0,(MODSIN,0,0,0,0,0) . RESULT MUST BE INTEGERDR
)@@G@@@C@@@#          S         A0,LADESC         . SAVE IT @D@@@#          PODS
)@@G@@P       2                 . POP STACK     @E@@@#          L,U       A5,0DT
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@#LOG999    . @E@@@#          L DU
)@@G@@        X11,LOGLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @C@@@#          J       DV
)@@G@@  0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@#/.    @[@@@#.     @^@@@#. THE 'NOT' DW
)@@G@@OPERATOR.   @[@@@#.     @]@^@#M$LNOT*   . @^@@@^M$OPERLOGNOT*       .   DX
)@@G@@@B@A@^          SLJ       TON$              .   @E@@@#          S       DY
)@@G@@  X11,LOGLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@#          L         A0,LDZ
)@@G@@AMODE         . LEFTARG MUST BE NULL@D@@@#          L         A5,LOGENM EA
)@@G@@        . BECASE THIS IS@E@@@#          TE,U      A0,MODNUL         . A EB
)@@G@@MONADIC OPERATOR  @D@@@#          J         NOT999            . IF NOT EEC
)@@G@@RROR  @F@@@#          L         A0,RAMODE         . RIGHTARG MUST BE LOGED
)@@G@@ICAL  @E@@@#          L         A5,LOGEMD         . WHICH MEANS INTEGER EE
)@@G@@@B@@@#          TE,U      A0,MODSIN         .   @D@@@#          J       EF
)@@G@@  NOT999            . IF NOT ERROR  @D@@@#          L         A0,RALONG EG
)@@G@@        . GET LENGTH    @F@@@#          TGET                        . GEEH
)@@G@@T TEMP SPACE FOR IT     @E@@@#          JNZ       A5,NOT999         . IFEI
)@@G@@ ERROR RETURN     @E@ @^          S         A0,LALONG         . SET RESUEJ
)@@G@@LT LENGTH   @E@ @#          S         A1,LAVALU         . SET RESULT ACCEK
)@@G@@ESS   @G@@@           S         A1,LAVALU         . SET RESULT LENGTH ANEL
)@@G@@D ADDRESS   @E@@@#          LXI,U     A1,1              . SET STORE INCREM
)@@G@@EMENT @E@@@#          L         X9,RAADDR         . GET ARGUMENT ADDRESSEN
)@@G@@@D@@@#          LXI,U     X9,1              . AND INCREMENT @G@@@#      EO
)@@G@@    L         A5,LOGELV         . GET LOGICAL VALUE ERROR MESSAGE @D@@@#EP
)@@G@@          J         NOT030            . AND ENTER LOOP@[@@@#.     @C@@@#EQ
)@@G@@. ARG MUST BE INTEGER ONE OR ZERO.  INVERT IT.  @[@@@#.     @]@@@#NOT010ER
)@@G@@    . @D@@@#          L         A3,0,*X9          . GET NEXT ARG  @D@@@#ES
)@@G@@          JZ        A3,NOT020         . IF ZERO SKIP  @E@@@#          TEET
)@@G@@,U      A3,1              . ELSE MUST BE ONE    @C@^@#          L       EU
)@@G@@  LOG999            . ERROR   @C@@@^          J         LOG999          EV
)@@G@@  . ERROR   @]@@@#NOT020    . @C@@@#          XOR,U     A3,1            EW
)@@G@@  . FLIP BIT@D@@@#          S         A4,0,*A1          . STORE RESULT  EX
)@@G@@@C@ @#NOT030    JGD       A0,NOT020         . COUNT IT@C@@@ NOT030    JGEY
)@@G@@D       A0,NOT010         . COUNT IT@[@@@#.     @ @@@ . SET TYPE OF RESUEZ
)@@G@@LT INTEGER  @[@@@ .     @E@@@#          L         A0,(MODSIN,0,0,0,0,0) FA
)@@G@@. SET TYPE INTEGER@B@@@#          S         A0,LADESC         .   @D@@@#FB
)@@G@@          POP       2                 . POP STACK     @E@@@#          L,FC
)@@G@@U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@#NOT999    . @E@@@#FD
)@@G@@          L         X11,LOGLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @C@@@#      FE
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@#.     @^@@@#          LIFF
)@@G@@TS      .   @C@@@#LOGAND    AND       A3,A4             . AND INST@C@@@#FG
)@@G@@LOGIOR    OR        A3,A4             . OR INST @C@@@#LOGXOR    XOR     FH
)@@G@@  A3,A4             . XOR INST@C@B@#LOGEMD    PCW       'ARG NOT INTE','FI
)@@G@@GER   ' .   @D@B@#LOGELN    PCW       'ARGS NOT OF ','SAME LENGTH ' .   FJ

)@@G@@@G@@@C. THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO PERFORM THE REPLICATION OPERATOR (#)NT
)@@G@@.     @F@D@C. THE EXPRESSION N # E RESULTS IN N COPIES OF E CATENATED WINU
)@@G@@TH    @G@@@D. THE EXPRESSION N # E RESULTS IN N COPIES OF E CATENATED WINV
)@@G@@TH EACH     @D@D@C. EACH OTHER.  THE LENGTH OF THE RESULT IS THE PRODUCTNW
)@@G@@@G@@@D. OTHER.  THE LENGTH OF THE RESULT IS THE PRODUCT OF N AND THE LENNX
)@@G@@GTH   @G@D@C. OF N AND THE LENGTH OF E.  THE TYPE OF THE RESULT IS THE SNY
)@@G@@AME AS THE  @E@@@D. OF E.  THE TYPE OF THE RESULT IS THE SAME AS THAT OFNZ
)@@G@@ E.   @]@D@C. TYPE OF E.@[@@@C.     @]@D@CM$ODUP*   . @^@@@DM$OPERREPLICOA
)@@G@@*       .   @E@@@C          S         X11,DUPLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADOB
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@C          S         R4,DUPSVR         . SAVE COUNT REGISTER OC
)@@G@@@[@@@C.     @B@@@C. LEFTARG MUST BE INTEGER OF LENGTH ONE.  @[@@@C.     OD
)@@G@@@E@@@C          L         A0,LAMODE         . GET LEFTARG TYPE    @E@@@COE
)@@G@@          L         A1,LALONG         . GET LEFTARG LENGTH  @F@@@C      OF
)@@G@@    L         A5,DUPLAE         . LEFTARG ERROR MESSAGE     @E@@@C      OG

)@@G@@,U      A1,1              . LENGTH ONE    @E@@@C          J         DUP9OI

)@@G@@        . PICKUP LEFTARG@F@@@C          L         R4,0,A1           . INOK
)@@G@@TO COUNTER REGISTER     @E@@@C          TP        R4                . MUOL
)@@G@@ST BE POSITIVE    @F@@@C          J         DUP999            . NO - ERROM
)@@G@@OR IN LEFTARG     @[@@@C.     @G@@@C. RIGHTARG MAY BE ANY DATA TYPE.  COON
)@@G@@MPUTE THE AMOUNT OF SPACE IT TAKES  @D@@@C. AND GET N TIMES THAT MUCH FROO
)@@G@@OM TEMP STORAGE MANAGER.@[@@@C.     @E@@@C          L         A4,RAMODE OP
)@@G@@        . GET RIGHT ARG MODE  @E@@@C          LSSL      A4,30           OQ

)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             QV
)@@G@@        .   @B@[@@          M$ASCAN                     .   @[@@@@.     QW
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO SCAN AN EXPRESSION FOR A BOOLEAN VALUEQX
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. AT THE PRESENT TIME INTEGER ZERO OR ONE, BUT NO OTHER VALUQY
)@@G@@ES,   @#@@@@. ARE ALLOWED.    @[@@@@.     @]@]@@M$SBOO*   . @^@@@]M$SCANQZ

)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@BOOLNK    VARK
)@@G@@R       'BOOLNK',1        . LINK HOME     @D@^@@ERRBOO    PCW       'ERRRL
)@@G@@OR IN BOO','LEAN VALUE  ' .   @[@@@^.     @B@@@^          LITS          RM
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@^.     @B@@@^ERRBOO    PCM       1               RN
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@^          'ERROR IN BOOLEAN EXPRESSION.' .@B@@@^          ENRO

)@@G@@          S         X10,SCFSAV        . SAVE X10 CONTENTS   @[@S@R.     YN
)@@G@@@D@S@R. THIS ROUTINE SCANS AN ADD,SPLIT ,OR COPY COMMAND    @D@S@R. CARDYO
)@@G@@ FOR THE FILENAME. IT ASSIGNS THE FILE AND DOES @D@S@R. ALL THE NECESSARYP
)@@G@@Y TABLE SETUP TO DO I/O TO THE FILE.@[@S@R.     @D@S@R. EXPECTS X9 TO POYQ
)@@G@@INT TO AREA TO BUILD PFI PACKET     @C@S@R. A0=LOCATION OF THREE WORD USYR
)@@G@@E PACKET 1ST 2    @C@S@R. WORDS ARE THE USENAME AND THE THIRD WORD WILL YS
)@@G@@@B@S@R. CONTAIN THE FIFREE FREE CODE IN H1.     @[@S@R.     @[@S@RFORM*.YT
)@@G@@@G@S@R          L,U       A0,ASUSPKT        . GET ADD-SPLIT USE PACKET AYU
)@@G@@DDRESS@F@S@R          DL        A2,ASUSNM         . GET ADD-SPLIT USE NAYV
)@@G@@ME    @F@S@R          DS        A2,0,A0           . STORE IT IN THE PACKYW
)@@G@@ET    @D@S@RFORMA*    S         A0,USEADDR        . SAVE ADDRESS  @B@S@RYX
)@@G@@          LA        A2,K10            .   @B@S@R          SA        A2,5YY
)@@G@@,X9           .   @B@S@R          SZ        4,X9              .   @B@S@RYZ
)@@G@@          DL        A2,BLANKS         .   @E@S@R          DS        A2,6ZA
)@@G@@,X9           . BLANK VERSION NAME  @D@S@R          DSL       A2,72     ZB
)@@G@@        . ZERO A0 AND A1@E@@@S          DSL       A4,72             . CLZC
)@@G@@EAR A4 AND A5     @F@S@R          DS        A2,ELTPKT         . CLEAR FLZD
)@@G@@AGS IN ELT$ PACKET@F@@@S          DS        A4,ELT$           . CLEAR FLZE
)@@G@@AGS IN ELT$ PACKET@E@@@U          T$COLN                      . GET COLUZF
)@@G@@MN NUMBER   @C@@@U          S,H2      A0,ITEM+2         . STORE IT@[@@@SZG
)@@G@@.     @E@T@S. EXAMINE FIRST NON-BLANK CHARACTER TO SEE IF ITS A PERIOD. ZH
)@@G@@@C@@@T. SKIP LEADING BLANKS BEFORE FILE NAME FIELD.   @F@T@S. THIS ALSO ZI
)@@G@@ALLOWS ANY NUMBER OF LEADING BLANKS BEFORE FILE NAME. @[@@@S.     @F@T@SZJ
)@@G@@          T$NFINDA  ' ' SCF050        . IF NOTHING JUST RETURN    @F@@@TZK
)@@G@@          T$NFINDA  ' ' SCF060        . IF NOTHING JUST RETURN    @H@@@SZL
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX        . TURN COMMA AND BLANK INTO TERM CZM
)@@G@@HAR   @G@@@S          JN        A3,SCF050         . IF ONE OF THESE THENZN
)@@G@@ RETURN     @G@T@S          L         X10,(1,NELT)      . START SCANNINGZO
)@@G@@ ELEMENT NAME     @F@@@T          L         X10,(1,NQUAL)     . START SCZP
)@@G@@ANNING FILE NAME  @F@T@S          TNE,U     A3,'.'            . IS THEREZQ
)@@G@@ A LEADING PERIOD @F@T@S          J         SCF030            . YES - SCZR
)@@G@@AN ELEMENT NAME   @[@@@S.     @F@T@S. FIRST NON-BLANK IS NOT PERIOD OR TZS
)@@G@@ERM.  SEARCH FORWARD TO SEE IF@G@@@T. LOOK AHEAD TO SEE IF THERE IS A PEZT
)@@G@@RIOD OR AN ASTERISK IN THIS SPEC.   @B@@@T. IF THERE IS WE START IN FILEZU
)@@G@@NAME MODE.  @B@@@T. IF NOT WE START IN ELEMENT NAME MODE.   @A@T@S. THERZV
)@@G@@E IS A PERIOD IN THIS SPEC.   @[@@@S.     @E@@@S          T$COLN        ZW
)@@G@@              . GET CURRENT COLUMN  @E@@@S          AN,U      A0,1      ZX
)@@G@@        . POINT AT LAST BLANK @F@T@S          S         A0,ITEM         ZY
)@@G@@  . SAVE ACROSS LOOK AHEAD    @F@@@T          S,H2      A0,ITEM+2       ZZ
)@@G@@  . SAVE ACROSS LOOK AHEAD    @[@T@S.     @C@T@S. SEARCH FOR A PERIOD BEAA
)@@G@@FORE END OF THIS SPEC.  @[@T@S.     @F@@@T          L,H1      A3,ITEM+2 AB
)@@G@@        . GET CHAR STORED BY CHRFIX @]@@@SSCF010    . @D@@@T          TEAC
)@@G@@,U      A3,'*'            . IS IT ASTERISK@D@@@T          TNE,U     A3,'AD
)@@G@@.'            . OR PERIOD     @H@@@T          J         SCF020          AE
)@@G@@  . YES - EXIT WITH X10 POINTING TO NQUAL @D@@@S          T$CHAR        AF
)@@G@@              . GET CHARACTER @F@@@S          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX      AG
)@@G@@  . TURN BLANK COMMA INTO TERM@F@T@S          JN        A3,SCF020       AH
)@@G@@  . IF TERMINATOR EXIT SEARCH @F@@@T          JP        A3,SCF010       AI
)@@G@@  . IF NOT TERMINATOR LOOP    @[@@@T.     @D@@@T. NO PERIOD OR ASTERISK AJ
)@@G@@FOUND - POINT SCAN AT ELEMENT.@[@@@T.     @E@@@T          LXM,U     X10,AK
)@@G@@NELT          . LOAD ELEMENT STATE  @[@@@T.     @A@@@T. BACK UP TO ORIGIAL
)@@G@@NAL POSITION.     @[@@@T.     @F@T@S          TE,U      A3,'.'          AM
)@@G@@  . IF PERIOD EXIT SEARCH     @E@T@S          J         SCF010          AN
)@@G@@  . ELSE SEARCH FORWARD @[@T@S.     @ @T@S. INITIALIZE SCANNER STATE.   AO
)@@G@@@[@T@S.     @]@@@SSCF020    . @E@T@S          TNE,U     A3,'.'          AP
)@@G@@  . WAS PERIOD FOUND    @F@T@S          LXM,U     X10,NQUAL         . YEAQ
)@@G@@S - START AT QUALIFIER  @F@T@S          T$COL     ITEM,,W           . ANAR
)@@G@@D MOVE TIDE$ BACKWARDS  @E@@@T          T$COL     ITEM+2,,H2        . MOAS
)@@G@@VE TIDE$ BACKWARDS@[@@@S/.    @[@@@S.     @#@@@S. MAIN SCAN LOOP. @^@@@SAT
)@@G@@. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@S.     @]@@@SSCF030    . @E@@@S          DLAU
)@@G@@        A0,BLANKS         . GET FIELDATA BLANKS @E@@@S          DS      AV
)@@G@@  A0,ITEM           . INITIALIZE ITEM     @F@@@S          L         A0,NAW
)@@G@@ODMSK,X10     . GET MASK FOR CURRENT NODE @E@@@S          DL        A2,0AX
)@@G@@,A0           . INTO DOUBLE A2-A3   @D@@@S          L,U       A0,ITEM   AY
)@@G@@        . PUT IT IN ITEM@D@@@S          L         A1,NODMAX,X10     . GEAZ
)@@G@@T MAX LENGTH@D@@@S          T$NBRKF                     . SCAN NEXT ITEMBA
)@@G@@@G@@@S          LMJ       X11,CHRFIX        . TURN BLANK COMMA INTO TERMBB
)@@G@@INATOR@E@@@S          L         A5,ERRLEN         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   BC
)@@G@@@E@@@S          JZ        A2,SCF900         . WAS TERM COUNT-DOWN @F@@@SBD
)@@G@@          DL        A0,ITEM           . NO - GET ITEM SCANNED     @[@@@SBE
)@@G@@.     @D@@@S. SEARCH ARCS FOR ONE MARKED WITH TERM CHAR FOUND.    @[@@@SBF
)@@G@@.     @]@@@SARCNUL    . @E@@@S          L         A2,NODSTO,X10     . GEBG
)@@G@@T STORE INDEX     @G@@@S          L         R1,NODARC,X10     . GET NUMBBH
)@@G@@ER OF ARCS TO SEARCH    @D@@@S          SE        A3,ARCCHR+1,*X10  . SEBI
)@@G@@ARCH ARCS   @F@@@S          J         SCF040            . NOT FOUND - CHBJ
)@@G@@ECK FOR TERM@E@@@S          L         X11,ARCRTN,X10    . GET ARC ROUTINBK
)@@G@@E     @F@@@S          LXM       X10,ARCNOD,X10    . AND MOVE TO NEXT NODBL
)@@G@@E     @E@@@S          J         0,X11             . PROCESS ARC ROUTINE BM
)@@G@@@[@@@S.     @E@@@S. TERM CHAR NOT FOUND.  IF TERMINATOR WE ARE DONE, ELSBN
)@@G@@E IT  @A@@@S. IS AN ILLEGAL CHARACTER ERROR.    @[@@@S.     @]@@@SSCF040BO
)@@G@@    . @F@@@S          JN        A3,ARCSTO         . IF TERM STORE AND GEBP
)@@G@@T OUT @E@@@S          L         A5,ERRCHR         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   BQ
)@@G@@@D@@@S          J         SCF900            . ELSE IS ILCHAR@[@@@T.     BR
)@@G@@@B@@@T. ARC ROUTINE TO HANDLE LEADING PERIOD.   @[@@@T.     @]@@@TARCFILBS
)@@G@@    . @F@@@T          JNZ       A4,ARCNUL         . IF FILENAME SKIP THIBT
)@@G@@S     @D@@@T          L,U       A5,1              . ELSE GET ONE  @G@@@TBU
)@@G@@          S         A5,CFN            . AND SET LEADING PERIOD FLAG     BV
)@@G@@@D@@@T          J         ARCNUL            . AND CONTINUE  @[@@@S.     BW
)@@G@@@ @@@S. ARC ROUTINE FOR QUALIFIER.  @[@@@S.     @]@@@SARCQUL    . @F@@@TBX
)@@G@@          JNZ       A4,ARCSTO         . IF QUAL SEEN STORE IT     @C@T@SBY
)@@G@@          L,U       A5,1              . GET ONE @D@@@T          L,U     BZ
)@@G@@  A5,1              . ELSE GET ONE  @E@T@S          TNE       A0,BLANKS CA
)@@G@@        . IS IT ALL BLANKS    @G@T@S          S         A5,IQF          CB
)@@G@@  . YES - SET IMPLIED QUALIFIER     @F@@@T          S         A5,IQF    CC
)@@G@@        . AND SET IMPLIED QUALIFIER @[@@@S.     @C@@@S. ARC ROUTINE FOR CD
)@@G@@STORING CURRENT COMPONENT.    @^@@@S. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@S.     CE
)@@G@@@]@@@SARCSTO    . @E@@@S          EX        LENSTO,A2         . STORE ITCF
)@@G@@EM LENGTH   @E@@@S          EX        DATSTO,A2         . STORE DATA ITECG
)@@G@@M     @F@@@S          JP        A3,SCF030         . IF MORE TO SCAN THENCH
)@@G@@ LOOP @[@@@S/.    @[@@@S.     @#@@@S. DONE SCANNING.  @^@@@S. (NOTE FALLCI
)@@G@@-THRU).     @[@@@S.     @]@@@SSCF050    . @F@@@T          L,H1      A3,ICJ
)@@G@@TEM+2         . RECOVER LAST CHAR SCANNED @[@@@T.     @D@@@T. NOTHING FOCK
)@@G@@UND BY T$NFINDA - A3 IS ALREADY LOADED.   @[@@@T.     @]@@@TSCF060    . CL
)@@G@@@E@@@T          L,H2      A4,ITEM+2         . LOAD COLUMN NUMBER  @E@@@SCM
)@@G@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @D@@@S      CN
)@@G@@    J         SCF999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@S.     @ @@@S. GENECO
)@@G@@RATE ERROR MESSAGE.     @[@@@S.     @]@@@SSCF900    . @F@@@S          T$CP
)@@G@@COLN                      . GET CURRENT COLUMN NUMBER @D@@@S          ANCQ
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . INCREMENTED   @F@@@S          LMJ       X11,CR
)@@G@@M$ERRMSGXQT   . AND GENERATE ERROR MESSAGE@[@@@S.     @#@@@S. RETURN TO CS
)@@G@@CALLER@[@@@S.     @]@@@SSCF999    . @D@@@S          L         X10,SCFSAVCT
)@@G@@        . RESTORE X10   @E@@@S          L         X11,SCFLNK        . GECU
)@@G@@T RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@S          J         0,X11             . RETURN TCV
)@@G@@O CALLER    @[@@@S.     @D@@@S. SUBROUTINE TO FORCE TERMINATION ON COMMACW
)@@G@@ OR BLANK.  @[@@@S.     @]@@@SCHRFIX    . @E@@@T          S,H1      A3,ICX
)@@G@@TEM+2         . STORE REAL CHARACTER@F@@@S          JN        A3,0,X11  CY
)@@G@@        . RETURN IF TERM ALREADY    @E@@@S          LXI,U     A3,0      CZ
)@@G@@        . CLEAR INCREMENT     @C@@@S          TE,U      A3,' '          DA
)@@G@@  . IF BLANK@C@@@S          TNE,U     A3,','            . IF COMMA@D@@@SDB
)@@G@@          LN,U      A3,1              . SET TERM CHAR @E@@@S          J DC
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@S.     @D@V@SBLANKSDD
)@@G@@    '            '               . FD BLANKS    @B@V@SMSGCHR    'ILLEGALDE
)@@G@@ CHARACTER'         .   @B@V@SERRCHR    +         0100+$-MSGCHR,MSGCHR .DF
)@@G@@@B@V@SMSGLEN    'COMPONENT TOO LONG'        .   @B@V@SERRLEN    +       DG
)@@G@@  0100+$-MSGLEN,MSGLEN .@[@V@S.     @D@@@SSCFLNK    VAR       'SCFLNK',1DH
)@@G@@        . RETURN ADDRESS@C@@@SSCFSAV    VAR       'SCFSAV',1        . X1DI
)@@G@@0 SAVE@D@@@SITEM      VAR       'ITEM  ',3        . SCAN BUFFER   @[@@@SDJ
)@@G@@.     @B@@@V          LITS                        .   @[@@@V.     @D@@@VDK
)@@G@@BLANKS    '            '              . FD BLANKS     @B@@@VERRCHR    PCDL
)@@G@@M       1                 .   @B@@@V          'ILLEGAL CHARACTER.'      DM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@VERRLEN    PCM       1                 .   @B@@@V          'CDN
)@@G@@OMPONENT TOO LONG.'       .   @B@@@V          ENDPCM                    DO
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@V.     @B@S@R          DS        A2,2,X9           .   @B@S@RDP
)@@G@@          DS        A2,8,X9           .   @B@S@R          DS        A2,1DQ
)@@G@@0,X9          .   @E@S@R          SZ        REL               . ZERO CYCDR
)@@G@@LE FIELD    @H@S@R          S,S4      ONE,REL           . SET FLAG FOR NDS

)@@G@@OCATION     @[@S@R.     @A@S@R. LOOK FOR FIRST NON-BLANK CHARACTER@[@S@RDW
)@@G@@.     @]@S@RSCN010.     @I@S@R          S,H2      X5,X5STRT         . INDX

)@@G@@OUNT          . ANY CHARS NOT YET SEEN    @D@S@R          J         SCN0DZ
)@@G@@20            . YES, CONTINUE @D@S@R          LMJ       X11,PSYNER      EA
)@@G@@  . NO MORE, ERROR@E@S@RSCN020    L         A2,EDIT80M1,X5    . GET NEXTEB

)@@G@@@D@S@R          J         SCN010            . YES, IGNORE IT@[@S@R.     ED

)@@G@@50            . NO, CONTINUE LOOKING FOR PERIOD @[@S@R.     @^@S@R. LEADEG
)@@G@@ING PERIOD FOUND  @[@S@R.     @F@S@R          SR,S1     ONE,X5PER       EH

)@@G@@    J         SCN100            . YES, START PARSE    @D@S@R          TEEM
)@@G@@,U      A3,'.'            . IS IT PERIOD  @F@S@R          J         SCN0EN
)@@G@@50            . NO, GET NEXT CHARACTER    @G@S@R          TZ        X5PEEO
)@@G@@R             . WAS PERIOD DETECTED ALREADY     @D@S@R          LMJ     EP

)@@G@@        . SET PERIOD FOUND FLAG     @[@S@R.     @E@S@R. DID INITIAL SCANER
)@@G@@ FOR PERIODS NOW DO PARSE OF FILENAME     @[@S@R.     @]@S@RSCN100.     ES
)@@G@@@E@S@R          LXM       X5,X5STRT         . GET START POINTER   @F@S@RET

)@@G@@          TZ        X5PER             . PERIOD NOT FOUND?   @E@S@R      EV
)@@G@@    TZ,S1     X5PER             . OR LEADING PERIOD?  @H@S@R          L,EW
)@@G@@U       X8,SELT           . YES, START WITH STATE ELEMENT NAME    @D@S@REX
)@@G@@NEWNODE   A         X8,(1,NODES)      . ADD NODE BASE @[@S@R.     @#@S@REY
)@@G@@. INITIALIZE STORE@[@S@R.     @D@S@R          DL        A4,BLANKS       EZ

)@@G@@.     @^@S@R. GET NEXT CHARACTER    @[@S@R.     @]@S@RSCN200.     @F@S@RFE

)@@G@@SCN300.     @E@S@R          L         A1,MASKADD        . GET MASK ADDREFG

)@@G@@        A4,SCN400         . JUMP IF ILLEGAL CHARACTER @[@S@R.     @B@S@RFJ
)@@G@@. GOT A LEGAL CHARACTER, NOW STUFF IT     @[@S@R.     @D@S@R          TGFK
)@@G@@        A6,ITEMAX         . ITEM TOO LONG?@D@S@R          LMJ       X11,FL

)@@G@@  . GET CHARACTER TO STORE    @E@S@R          EX        0,*A0           FN
)@@G@@  . STORE THE CHARACTER @F@S@R          A,U       A6,1              . INFO
)@@G@@CREMENT CHARACTER COUNT @F@S@R          J         SCN200            . GOFP
)@@G@@ GET NEXT CHARACTER     @[@S@R.     @F@S@R. ILLEGAL CHARACTER, SEARCH TOFQ
)@@G@@ SEE IF IT IS A TRANSITION CHARACTER@[@S@R.     @E@S@RSCN400    L       FR
)@@G@@  R1,NUMNODES       . GET NUMBER OF NODES @F@S@R          L         X7,XFS
)@@G@@8             . GET CURRENT NODE POINTER  @D@S@R          J         SCN4FT
)@@G@@20            . START LOOP    @E@S@RSCN410    TNE,S1    A3,1,*X7        FU
)@@G@@  . NODE CHARACTER?     @E@S@R          J         SCN500            . YEFV
