)@@G@@.     @#@S@R. FOUND NEW NODE  @[@S@R.     @]@S@RSCN500.     @G@S@R      FY
)@@G@@    L         A1,TRANSTATE      . GET TRANSITION STATE ADDRESS    @F@S@RFZ
)@@G@@          J         0,A1              . GO TO THE TRANSITION STATE@[@S@RGA
)@@G@@.     @^@S@R. TRANSITION STATES     @[@S@R.     @^@S@R. GO TO THE NEXT NGB
)@@G@@ODE   @[@S@R.     @]@S@RNEXTNODE.   @F@S@R          LMJ       X11,STORITGC
)@@G@@EM      . STORE THE CURRENT ITEM    @C@S@R          J         NEWNODE   GD
)@@G@@        . GO DO IT@[@S@R.     @ @S@R. QUALIFIER TERMINATION STATE @[@S@RGE
)@@G@@.     @]@S@RQUALTERM.   @F@S@R          LMJ       X11,STORITEM      . STGF
)@@G@@ORE THE CURRENT ITEM    @D@S@R          TNE       A4,BLANKS         . ALGG
)@@G@@L BLANKS?   @G@S@R          S         ONE,IQF           . YES, SET IMPLIGH

)@@G@@@G@@@P. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO SCAN THE COMMAND IMAGE IN THE MACRO INUG
)@@G@@PUT   @F@@@P. BUFFER AND RETURN A COMMAND NAME IN A0-A1.  IT ALSO RETURNUH
)@@G@@S THE @G@@@P. CHARACTER COUNT OF THE COMMAND IN A2. FOR A COMMAND WHICH UI
)@@G@@IS A FULL   @G@@@P. EXEC8 FILE/ELEMENT NAME (WHICH IS LEFT IN ELT$ BY M$UJ

)@@G@@ IS CLEARED TO ZERO.    @[@@@P.     @^@@@PM$XQTSCAN*          .   @D@@@PUL

)@@G@@A NORMAL COMMAND. @[@@@P.     @H@@@P          L,H1      A1,ELT$+1       UQ
)@@G@@  . GET ELEMENT NAME FIELDS (ENL,EVL,ECL) @F@@@P          JZ        A1,SUR
)@@G@@CN010         . IF NOT GIVEN TRY SPECIAL  @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. NOT SPECIAUS
)@@G@@L CASE - LOOK TO SEE IF FILE NAME STUFF GIVEN.  @[@@@P.     @E@@@P      UT
)@@G@@    AND,U     A1,07777          . LOOK AT EVL AND ECL @E@@@R          A UU
)@@G@@        A2,CFN            . AND LEADING PERIOD  @F@@@P          DL      UV

)@@G@@  ELT$              . IF HE GAVE FILENAME @F@@@P          JZ        A2,$UX
)@@G@@+2            . ELEMENT VERSION OR CYCLE  @F@@@P          DSL       A0,7UY

)@@G@@        . ELSE CHECK TERM CHAR@[@@@P.     @E@@@P. IF COMMAND IS NOT ELTNVC
)@@G@@AME THERE ARE SEVERAL SPECIAL CASES.@F@@@P. ONE IS THE "#&'()0 CSF COMMAVD

)@@G@@R NEVER DIE. ANOTHER IS THE END     @G@@@P. OF LINE PRIMITIVE WHICH SAYSVF

)@@G@@ ALPHA CONVERSION @[@@@L.     @ @M@L. NUMERIC MODE CONVERSION     @ @@@MYR

)@@G@@ONLY INTEGER@B@@@L          OFF       NSLEVL=0          .   @[@@@L.     YX
)@@G@@@F@@@L          ON        NSLEVL>0          . IF NUMERIC TYPES ALLOWED  YY

)@@G@@T LENGTH    @D@@@L          TOP,U     A2,ALPBIT         . IS IT ALPHA   AX
)@@G@@@G@@@L          LSSL      A0,4              . NO - ALLOW 16 CHARS PER NUAY
)@@G@@MBER  @[@@@L.     @^@@@L. COMPUTE WORD LENGTH   @[@@@L.     @E@@@L      AZ
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,3              . COMPUTE WORD LENGTH @D@@@L          SSBA

)@@G@@              . GET TEMP CORE @C@@@L          JNZ       A5,CVT999       BC

)@@G@@          L         A0,CVTTMP         . AND GET DESCR ADDRESS AGAIN     BT
)@@G@@@[@@@L.     @^@@@L. CONVERSION FINISHED   @[@@@L.     @]@@@LCVT100    . BU
)@@G@@@C@L@K          J         CVT030            . DONE    @D@L@K          DLBV

)@@G@@AMS   @[@@@L.     @F@@@L. THIS ROUTINE IS THE SIMPLEST TEMPORARY CORE MACW
)@@G@@NAGER.  IT RETURNS@F@@@L. POINTERS TO A DATA TABLE WITHIN THIS ELEMENT. CX
)@@G@@ IF THE DATA TABLE@F@@@L. IS EXAUSTED CONTROL PASSES TO 0,X11 WITH A PRICY
)@@G@@NT CONTROL WORD.  @[@@@L.     @]@M@LM$BTMP*   . @]@N@MM$BTSG*   . @^@@@NCZ
)@@G@@M$CORETMPGET*       .   @F@M@L          LXI,U     A0,0,A0           . SEDA
)@@G@@T INCREMENT WITH LENGTH @F@M@L          AU        A0,NEXTD          . FIDB
)@@G@@ND NEW LAST ADDRESS     @F@@@M          AU        A0,NEXTD          . FIDC
)@@G@@ND NEW LAST ADDRESS     @G@@@M          L         A5,TGEOVR         . GEDD
)@@G@@T ERROR - TEMP STACK OVERFLOW @D@@@M          TG        A1,LASTD        DE
)@@G@@  . WAS THERE ENUF@F@@@M          J         TSG999            . NO - TAKDF
)@@G@@E ERROR RETURN    @E@@@M          LXI       A1,NEXTD          . GET ITS DG
)@@G@@BASE ADDRESS@G@@@M          S,H2      A1,NEXTD          . SAVE NEXT AVAIDH
)@@G@@LABLE ADDRESS     @E@@@M          SSL       A1,18             . MOVE BASDI
)@@G@@E TO H2     @F@@@M          LXI,U     A1,0,A0           . SET INCREMENT DJ

)@@G@@ADDRESS     @E@@@M          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLDM

)@@G@@S THERE ENUF@D@M@L          J         1,X11             . YES - RETURN  DO
)@@G@@@[@M@L.     @ @M@L. TEMP DATA STACK OVERFLOW.   @[@M@L.     @B@M@L      DP
)@@G@@    L         A0,TGEOVR         .   @E@M@L          J         0,X11     DQ
)@@G@@        . TAKE ERROR RETURN   @C@@@M          J         0,X11           DR
)@@G@@  . RETURN  @[@@@L.     @D@P@LTGEOVR    PCW       'TEMPORARY ST','ACK OVDS
)@@G@@ERFLOW' .   @[@P@L.     @B@@@M. M$BTSA - RELEASE ALL TEMPORARY STORAGE. DT
)@@G@@@D@@@M. M$BTSR - RELEASE TEMPORARY STORAGE UP UNTIL A0.     @D@M@L. THISDU
)@@G@@ ROUTINE RELEASES ALL TEMPORARY STACK SPACE.    @[@@@L.     @]@N@MM$BTSADV
)@@G@@*   . @^@@@NM$CORETMPALL*       .   @E@@@M          L,U       A0,FRSTD  DW

)@@G@@@E@@@O. THIS TABLE IS JUMPED INTO WITH TWICE THE NUMERIC TYPE.    @[@@@OHL

)@@G@@@A@@@O. CATENATION OF STRINGS AND INTEGERS@F@@@P. THIS ELEMENT PERFORMS RX
)@@G@@THE CATENATION OPERATION.  NUMERICS MAY BE@G@@@P. CATENATED TO FORM NUMERY
)@@G@@RIC ARRAYS, ANY TYPE CONVERSION REQUIRED IS IN  @G@@@P. THE UPWARD DIRECRZ
)@@G@@TION.  NUMERICS AND CHARACTERS MAY BE CATENATED TO    @A@@@P. FORM CHARASA
)@@G@@CTER ARRAYS, OR STRINGS.@[@@@P.     @[@@@O.     @]@P@OM$OCAT*   . @^@@@PSB

)@@G@@@F@@@P. ROUTINE PERFORMS THEM ALL IN ONE SWELL FOOP BECAUSE OF TYPE     SH
)@@G@@@E@@@P. CONVERSION PROBLEMS ENCOUNTERED WHEN DOING THEM PAIRWISE. @[@@@PSI

)@@G@@        . STORE INTO ITEM COUNT OF LEFTARG@E@P@O          SSL       A0,2ZW
)@@G@@              . FORM WORD COUNT     @E@P@O          A,U       X10,2,A0  ZX
)@@G@@        . ADD IN FUDGE FACTOR @H@P@O          E$COPY    6,BLANKS        ZY
)@@G@@  . MAKE SURE LAST WORD IS BLANKED OUT    @D@P@O          E$DITX        ZZ
)@@G@@              . CLOSE EDIT$   @D@P@O          L,U       A0,ZLINE        AA
)@@G@@  . RESTORE PACKET@B@P@O          S,H2      A0,ZAVE           .   @E@P@OAB
)@@G@@          L,U       A0,ALPBIT         . SET MODE OF RESULT  @F@P@O      AC
)@@G@@    TZ        EASC              . IF OUTPUT WAS IN ASCII    @H@P@O      AD
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,ASCBIT         . BY ALL MEANS FLAG IT TO THE WORLD     AE
)@@G@@@C@P@O          S         A0,LAMODE         . SET MODE@F@P@O          L,AF
)@@G@@U       A0,1              . SET ASCII OUTPUT FLAG     @ @P@O          S AG
)@@G@@        A0,EASC   @[@P@O.     @D@P@O. UNSTACK AND RETURN TO SCANNER FOR AH
)@@G@@NEXT OPERATION    @[@P@O.     @]@P@ODFC090    . @D@P@O          POP     AI
)@@G@@  2                 . POP STACK     @B@@@P          END                 AJ
)@@G@@        .   ___     . YES CALL EDIT$@I@P@O          OR,U      A0,0,A1   AK
)@@G@@        . COMPUTE MODE OF RESULTING NUMERIC ARRA*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@      AL
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             AM
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          M$AMODES                    .   @[@@@@.     AN
)@@G@@@#@@@@. MODE TRANSLATION@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. SS ARE THE BITS FOR THE SOURAO
)@@G@@CE MODE     @B@@@@. TT ARE THE BITS FOR THE TARGET MODE     @#@@@@. L INAP
)@@G@@DEX,SSTT    @#@@@@. DL A3,VALUE     @#@@@@. EX MODTRN,INDEX @#@@@@. DS AAQ
)@@G@@3,NEW VALUE @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC                        .   AR
)@@G@@@B@@@@CG*       NAME                        .   @B@@@@OK        EQU     AS
)@@G@@  P(0,1)<NSLEVL+1   .   @F@@@@ DO OK   , +        P(1,1)            . GEAT
)@@G@@N CONVERSION ROUTINE    @D@@@@ DO 1-OK , +        0                 . BAAU
)@@G@@D CONVERSION@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     AV
)@@G@@@]@@@@$(2)      . @^@@@@M$CONVXQT*          .   @C@@@@          CG,0    AW
)@@G@@  +(NOP 0)          . SISI    @C@@@@          CG,1      +(LMJ X11,CNSISFAX
)@@G@@) . SISF    @C@@@@          CG,2      +(DSA A3,36)      . SIDI    @C@@@@AY
)@@G@@          CG,2      +(LMJ X11,CNSIDF) . SIDF    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@      AZ
)@@G@@    FON       .   @C@@@@          CG,1      +(LMJ X11,CNSFSI) . SFSI    BA
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CG,1      +(NOP 0)          . SFSF    @C@@@@          CGBB
)@@G@@,2      +(LMJ X11,CNSFDI) . SFDI    @C@@@@          CG,2      +(FEL A3,ABC
)@@G@@3)      . SFDF    @^@@@@          FOF       .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    DON       .   @C@@@@          CG,2      +(LDSL A3,36)     . DISI    BE
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CG,2      +(LMJ X11,CNDISF) . DISF    @C@@@@          CGBF
)@@G@@,2      +(NOP 0)          . DIDI    @C@@@@          CG,2      +(LMJ X11,BG
)@@G@@CNDIDF) . DIDF    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@          CG,2      +(LMJ X11,CNDFSIBH
)@@G@@) . DFSI    @C@@@@          CG,2      +(FCL A3,A3)      . DFSF    @C@@@@BI
)@@G@@          CG,2      +(LMJ X11,CNDFDI) . DFDI    @C@@@@          CG,2    BJ
)@@G@@  +(NOP 0)          . DFDF    @^@@@@          DOF       .   @[@@@@.     BK
)@@G@@@^@@@@          FON       .   @F@@@@CNSISF    DSA       A3,36           BL
)@@G@@  . CONVERT TO DOUBLE INTEGER @F@@@@CNDISF    L,U       A2,1084         BM
)@@G@@  . CONVERT TO DOUBLE FLOATING@B@@@@          DFP       A2,A3           BN
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@          FCL       A3,A3             . CONVERT BACK TO SINGBO
)@@G@@LE    @B@@@@          J         0,X11             .   @^@@@@          FOBP
)@@G@@F       .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          DON       .   @G@@@@CNSIDF    DSBQ
)@@G@@A       A3,36             . CONVERT TO DI AND FALL INTO     @F@@@@CNDIDFBR
)@@G@@    L,U       A2,1084           . DOUBLE LOAD AND CONVERT   @B@@@@      BS
)@@G@@    DFP       A2,A3             .   @B@@@@          J         0,X11     BT
)@@G@@        .   @^@@@@          DOF       .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          FOBU
)@@G@@N       .   @F@@@@CNSFSI    FEL       A3,A3             . CONVERT TO DOUBV
)@@G@@BLE FLOATING@F@@@@CNDFSI    DFU       A3,A3             . UNPACK INTO EXBW
)@@G@@P AND MANT  @E@@@@          SN        A3,A2             . SAVE BIASED EXBX
)@@G@@P     @E@@@@          LDSC      A4,11             . MOVE SIGN BIT TO 35 BY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DSA       A4,1095,A2        . NORMALIZE     @D@@@@      BZ
)@@G@@    S         A5,A3             . STORE RESULT  @B@@@@          J       CA
)@@G@@  0,X11             .   @^@@@@          FOF       .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@CB
)@@G@@          DON       .   @E@@@@CNSFDI    FEL       A3,A3             . COCC
)@@G@@NVERT TO DOUBLE   @F@@@@CNDFDI    DFU       A3,A3             . UNPACK ICD
)@@G@@NTO EXP AND MANT  @E@@@@          SN        A3,A2             . SAVE BIACE
)@@G@@SED EXP     @E@@@@          LDSC      A4,11             . MOVE SIGN BIT CF
)@@G@@TO 35 @D@@@@          DSA       A4,1095,A2        . NORMALIZE     @D@@@@CG
)@@G@@          DS        A4,A3             . STORE RESULT  @B@@@@          J CH
)@@G@@        0,X11             .   @^@@@@          DOF       .   @[@@@@.     CI
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   ___^DOR;K^H9&;@@@[&;K@@[CJ

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@E@[@@M$UMEDL$  EQU       UMEDL$            . EDITOR LOAD BAMK

)@@G@@APROC                     .   @C@@@@          ELT$                      MN
)@@G@@  . TEMP    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS CODE TO CALL THE UMO
)@@G@@OM TEXT EDITOR.   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          VARS                      MP
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CTLSAV    VAR       'CTLSAV',2        . SAVE FORMQ

)@@G@@@D@@@@EDFNOS    EQU       01                . INHIBIT SIGNON@[@@@@.     MS

)@@G@@THE TEXT EDITOR   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@INFOR     . @C@#@@          +       MY
)@@G@@  024400000000      . OPTIONS @F@@@#          +         024400000000    MZ
)@@G@@  . OPTIONS (NOW VARIABLE)    @D@@@@          +         000106000201    NA

)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          LITS                        .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NE

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          INSTRS                      .   @[@@@@/.    NJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. EDIT AN ARBITRARY FILE OR ELEMENT.@C@@@@. SCANS RESTNK
)@@G@@ OF FIELDS FOR THING TO BE EDITED.  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@M$COMEDIT* .@E@@@@NL
)@@G@@          S         X11,EDTLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@#      NM
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$SCANOPTS    . SCAN EDITOR OPTIONS @E@@@#          JNNN
)@@G@@Z       A5,EDT999         . IF ERROR RETURN     @E@@@#          L       NO
)@@G@@  A1,(0244000000000) . GET INFOR TYPE     @E@@@#          OR        A1,MNP
)@@G@@$COMOPT       . GET EDITOR OPTIONS  @E@@@#          S         A2,INFOR  NQ
)@@G@@        . SET INTO @ED INFOR  @F@@@@          DL        A1,CTLINT       NR
)@@G@@  . GET INITIAL CONTROL REGS  @]@@@@EDT010    . @F@@@@          DS      NS
)@@G@@  A1,CTLSAV         . SAVE INFOR CONTROL REGS   @D@@@@          LMJ     NT
)@@G@@  X11,M$SCANFILE    . SCAN FILE NAME@E@@@@          JNZ       A5,EDT999 NU
)@@G@@        . IF ERROR RETURN     @F@@@@          S         A3,TERMCH       NV
)@@G@@  . SAVE TERMINATOR CHARACTER @G@@@@          L,U       A0,ELT$         NW
)@@G@@  . TEMP - GET ELT$ PACKET ADDRESS  @F@@@@          DL        A1,CTLSAV NX
)@@G@@        . GET INFOR CONTROL REGS    @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,ELTINFNY
)@@G@@        . CONVERT ELT$ TO INFOR     @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,EDT999 NZ
)@@G@@        . IF ERROR RETURN     @F@@@@          A,U       A2,1            OA
)@@G@@  . BUMP TO NEXT SUBFIELD     @G@@@@          L         A3,TERMCH       OB
)@@G@@  . RECOVER TERMINATOR CHARACTER    @F@@@@          JN        A3,EDT020 OC
)@@G@@        . IF NEGATIVE IS END OF CARD@D@@@@          TNE,U     A3,','    OD
)@@G@@        . IS IT COMMA   @E@@@@          J         EDT010            . YEOE
)@@G@@S - GET NEXT FIELD@D@@@@          TNE,U     A3,' '            . IS IT BLOF
)@@G@@ANK   @E@@@@          J         EDT020            . YES - END OF SPECS  OG
)@@G@@@C@@@@          ER        ERR$              . TEMP    @]@@@@EDT020    . OH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AN,U      A1,INFOR          . COMPUTE WORD LENGTH @E@@@@OI
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A0,0,A1           . GET INFOR LENGTH    @D@@@@      OJ
)@@G@@    LXM,U     A0,INFOR          . AND LOCATION  @E@@@@          LMJ     OK
)@@G@@  X11,EDCALL        . TEMP - CALL EDITOR  @]@@@@EDT999    . @E@@@@      OL
)@@G@@    L         X11,EDTLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@@          J OM
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. EDITON
)@@G@@ SPECIFIED MACRO.  AFTER EDITING RECOMPILE.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@M$EDITOO
)@@G@@MACRO* .    @E@@@@          S         X11,EDTLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADOP
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$SCANFILE    . SCAN FOR FILENAME   OQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JNZ       A5,EDM999         . IF ERROR RETURN     @G@@@@OR

)@@G@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. PROC TO DEFINE FIELD TO BE EDITED @[@@@@.     PJ

)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. EDITPO

)@@G@@ELTLNK    VAR       'ELTLNK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@[@@@@.     @F@@@@QE
)@@G@@. EDIT INFOR FIELD.  SPECIAL HANDLING IS DONE ON QUALIFIERS AND   @C@@@@QF
)@@G@@. ON ELEMENT NAMES (TO HANDLE FUDGES IN INFOR). @[@@@@.     @]@@@@QUAL  QG
)@@G@@    . @E@@@@          TNZ       IQF               . IMPLIED QUALIFIER   QH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         NAME              . NO - HANDLE AS NAME @D@@@@QI
)@@G@@          JNZ       A0,0              . QUAL AND IQF  @E@@@@          L,QJ
)@@G@@U       A0,12             . GET 12 CHARACTERS   @D@@@@          DL      QK
)@@G@@  A3,('            ') . OF BLANKS   @E@@@@          J         NAME      QL
)@@G@@        . AND HANDLE AS NAME  @]@@@@ELTN      . @F@@@@          TZ      QM
)@@G@@  CFN               . CONTINUATION FILE NAME    @D@@@@          LXM,U   QN
)@@G@@  A2,'.@@'          . YES - SET FLAG@]@@@@NAME      . @F@@@@          AHQO
)@@G@@        A2,(1,0)          . INCREMENT SUBFIELD COUNTER@E@@@@          JZQP
)@@G@@        A0,NAM100         . IGNORE NULL FIELD   @E@@@@          TG,U    QQ
)@@G@@  A0,7              . IS IT ONE WORD FIELD@D@@@@          J         NAM0QR
)@@G@@10            . NO - DO TWO   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. ONE WORD COMPONENT    QS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              . MOVE CHAR COUNQT
)@@G@@T TO S5     @F@@@@          A,U       A2,01,A0          . SYNTHISIZE CONQU
)@@G@@TROL WORD   @D@@@@          DS        A2,0,A1           . STORE INFOR   QV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          A,U       A1,2              . ALLOW FOR TWO WORDS @D@@@@QW
)@@G@@          J         NAM020            . AND CONTINUE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@QX
)@@G@@. TWO WORD COMPONENT    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@NAM010    . @E@@@@          ANQY
)@@G@@,U      A0,6              . CHARS IN LAST WORD  @F@@@@          LSSL    QZ
)@@G@@  A0,6              . MOVE CHAR COUNT TO S2     @F@@@@          A,U     RA
)@@G@@  A2,02,A0          . SYNTHISIZE CONTROL WORD   @E@@@@          S       RB

)@@G@@,A1           . STORE DATA    @F@@@@          A,U       A1,3            RD
)@@G@@  . ALLOW FOR THREE WORDS     @]@@@@NAM020    . @F@@@@          LXM,U   RE
)@@G@@  A2,0              . CLEAR CFN FLAG, IF ANY    @]@@@@NAM100    . @E@@@@RF
)@@G@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @E@@@@      RG
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@RH
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@REPCNT    EQU       1*/15             . CONTINGENCY BIT FOR RI
)@@G@@BAD LIJ.    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. CALL EDITOR.    @E@@@@. A4 IS RETURNED 0RJ
)@@G@@ IF NO EDITING DONE, 1 IF EDITING DONE.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@EDCALL    . RK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          S         A0,EDPINF         . SAVE INFOR IN PACKET@[@]@@RL
)@@G@@.     @D@]@@          AH        A0,(0100,0)       . SET SKIP COUNT@D@]@@RM

)@@G@@. SAVE REGISTERS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          DL        A2,REGIDX       RO
)@@G@@  . INDEX INTO REGISTERS@B@@@@          L,U       R1,11             .   RP
)@@G@@@D@@@@          BT        A2,0,*A3          . SAVE X1-X11   @B@@@@      RQ
)@@G@@    LXM,U     A3,A6             .   @B@@@@          L,U       R1,12     RR
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          BT        A2,0,*A3          . SAVE A6-A15+2 RS
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LXM,U     A3,R4             .   @B@@@@          L,U     RT
)@@G@@  R1,12             .   @D@@@@          BT        A2,0,*A3          . SARU
)@@G@@VE R4-R15   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CHECK TO SEE IF EDITOR CONFIGURED.@[@@@@RV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@          TNZ,U     M$UMEDD$          . CHECK FOR EDITOR DBARW
)@@G@@NK    @D@@@@          J         EDC900            . PRINT MESSAGE @E@[@@RX
)@@G@@          TZ,U      M$EDLOAD$         . CHECK ENTRY POINT   @E@@@[      RY
)@@G@@    TZ,U      EDLOAD$           . CHECK ENTRY POINT   @E@[@@          TNRZ
)@@G@@Z,U     M$UMEDL$          . AND BDI OF LOAD BANK@E@@@[          TNZ,U   SA
)@@G@@  UMEDL$            . AND BDI OF LOAD BANK@D@@@@          J         EDC9SB
)@@G@@00            . PRINT MESSAGE @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. LINK TO EDITOR  @[@@@@SC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@          L         A0,(REPCNT,EDCONT) . REGISTER CONTINGENCSD
)@@G@@Y TO  @D@@@@          ER        IALL$             . TRAP BAD LINK$@D@@@@SE
)@@G@@          L         A0,(EDPKTL,EDPKT) . PACKET POINTER@D@[@@          LXSF
)@@G@@I,U     X11,M$UMEDL$      . LOAD BANK BDI @D@@@[          LXI,U     X11,SG

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@#          M$APROC                     .   @[@@@#.     TN
)@@G@@@F@@@#. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED BEFORE THE MAIN FIELD SCANNING IN ORDER  TO
)@@G@@@F@@@#. TO CHECK FOR AND SCAN AN OPTIONS FIELD.  A BITMASK IS BUILT IN  TP
)@@G@@@F@@@#. THE GLOBAL CELL M$COMOPT CONTAINING THE OPTIONS LETTERS SCANNED TQ
)@@G@@@F@@@#. IN UNIVAC 'MASTER-BIT' NOTATION (AS GOOD A STANDARD AS ANY).    TR
)@@G@@@[@@@#.     @B@B@#M$SCANOPTS* SUBR    'SCNOPT'          .   @B@@@BM$SCANTS
)@@G@@OPTS* .                          .  @E@@@B          S         X11,SOPLNKTT
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @B@A@^          SLJ       TON$            TU
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@#          SZ        M$COMOPT          . CLEAR OPTIONS CELL  TV
)@@G@@@[@@@#.     @G@@@#. KLUGE - UNTIL WE CAN BE PASSED THE CURRENT SCAN CHARTW
)@@G@@ACTER, WE HAVE    @A@@@#. TO BACK UP ONE TO CHECK FOR COMMA.@[@@@#.     TX
)@@G@@@C@@@#          T$SKIP    -1                . BACK ONE@D@@@#          T$TY
)@@G@@CHAR                      . GET CHARACTER @F@@@#          L,U       A3,0TZ
)@@G@@,A3           . GET FIELDATA EQUIVALENT   @D@@@#          TE,U      A3,'UA
)@@G@@,'            . IS IT COMMA   @F@@@#          J         SOP020          UB
)@@G@@  . NO - CHECK FOR BLANK/EOL  @[@@@#.     @E@@@#. COMMA FOUND - SKIP BLAUC
)@@G@@NKS UNTIL THE OPTIONS FIELD BEGINS. @[@@@#.     @E@@@#          T$NFINDAUD
)@@G@@  ' ' SOP900        . IF NOTHING ERROR    @]@@@#SOP010    . @E@ @#      UE
)@@G@@    T$CHAR                      . GET NEXT OPTION     @F@ @#          L,UF
)@@G@@U       A3,0,A3           . GET FIELDATA EQUIVALENT   @E@@@#          TGUG
)@@G@@,U      A3,'A'            . IS IT A LEGAL LETTER@E@@@#          TG,U    UH
)@@G@@  A3,'Z'+1          . FOR OPTIONS FIELD   @F@@@#          J         SOP0UI
)@@G@@20            . NO - CHECK FOR BLANK/EOL  @E@@@#          L         A0,(UJ
)@@G@@1*/('Z'-'@')) . GET '@' OPTION BIT  @E@@@#          SSL       A0,0,A3   UK
)@@G@@        . MAKE LETTER BIT     @D@@@#          OR        A0,M$COMOPT     UL
)@@G@@  . OR INTO MASK  @D@@@#          S         A1,M$COMOPT       . AND REPLUM
)@@G@@ACE   @E@@@           T$CHAR                      . GET NEXT OPTION     UN
)@@G@@@F@@@           L,U       A3,0,A3           . GET FIELDATA EQUIVALENT   UO
)@@G@@@F@@@#          J         SOP010            . AND LOOP FOR NEXT OPTION  UP
)@@G@@@[@@@#.     @F@@@#. NON-OPTION CHARACTER. ALLOW BLANK/EOL, OTHERS GENERAUQ
)@@G@@TE ERROR.   @[@@@#.     @]@@@#SOP020    . @E@@@#          L,U       A5,0UR
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @E@@@#          TE,U      A3,' '    US
)@@G@@        . IS CHARACTER BLANK  @D@@@#          TP,XU     0,A3            UT
)@@G@@  . OR END-OF-LINE@F@@@#          J         SOP999            . YES - REUU
)@@G@@TURN NORMALLY     @[@@@#.     @B@@@#. ILLEGAL CHARACTER IN OPTIONS FIELDUV
)@@G@@.     @[@@@#.     @E@@@#          T$COLN                      . GET COLUUW
)@@G@@MN NUMBER   @E@@@^          AN,U      A0,1              . FIX FOR SCANNEUX
)@@G@@R     @E@@@#          L         A5,ERRILC         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   UY
)@@G@@@G@@@#          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGXQT   . GENERATE EXECUTION-TIME MEUZ
)@@G@@SSAGE @D@@@#          J         SOP999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@#VA
)@@G@@.     @B@@@#. COMMA FOUND, BUT NO NON-BLANKS FOLLOW.  @[@@@#.     @]@@@#VB
)@@G@@SOP900    . @E@@@#          L         A5,ERROPF         . GET ERROR MESSVC
)@@G@@AGE   @]@@@#SOP999    . @C@^@#          TSNAP     'COMOPT',M$COMOPT . SNVD
)@@G@@AP    @C@@@^.         TSNAP     'COMOPT',M$COMOPT . SNAP    @B@B@#      VE
)@@G@@    RETURN                      .   @F@@@B          L         X11,SOPLNKVF
)@@G@@        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@B          J         0,X11     VG
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@^.     @#@@@^. ERROR MESSAGES  @[@@@^VH

)@@G@@HE IMAGE IS COPIED TO THE EDIT BUFFER, WHEN AN  @F@@@X. OPEN BRACKET (OBBO
)@@G@@C) IS SEEN A TEMPORARY STORAGE BUFFER IS GOTTEN @F@Y@X. AND CHAINED INTOBP
)@@G@@ THE STACK SUBSTK.  WHEN A CLOSE BRACKET IS SEEN@F@@@Y. AND CHAINED INTOBQ
)@@G@@ A STACK OFF X10.  WHEN A CLOSE BRACKET IS SEEN @F@@@X. TIDE$ IS CALLED BR
)@@G@@TO EVALUATE THE EXPRESSION, AND THE SUBSTITUTED @F@@@X. ARGUMENT IS COMPBS
)@@G@@UTED AND PASSED TO THE OUTPUT BUFFER.  WHEN THE @F@@@X. STACK IS EXHAUSTBT
)@@G@@ED THE LAST EDIT BUFFER CONTAINS THE SUBSTITUTED@G@Y@X. IMAGE. SUBSTITUTBU
)@@G@@ION IS FROM THE SRGUMENT BUFFER IN CSARGS OF M$MXQT.  @H@@@Y. IMAGE. SUBBV
)@@G@@STITUTION IS FROM THE ARGUMENT BUFFER IN CXARGS OF M$XQTMACRO.    @[@@@XBW
)@@G@@.     @C@@@YAST       EQU       052               . ASTERISK@D@@@YOBC   BX
)@@G@@    EQU       0133              . '[' CHARACTER @D@@@YCBC       EQU     BY
)@@G@@  0135              . ']' CHARACTER @[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y. TEMP STACK DEFINBZ
)@@G@@ITION.@[@@@Y.     @D@@@YTSFLAG    EQUF      0,,Q1             . * SEEN FCA
)@@G@@LAG   @F@@@YTSSTOR    EQUF      0,,Q2             . REMAINING CHARS TO SCB
)@@G@@TORE  @E@@@YTSLINK    EQUF      0,,H2             . LINK TO NEXT BUFFER CC
)@@G@@@C@@@YTSPTRS    EQUF      1                 . POINTERS@E@@@YTSLINE    EQCD
)@@G@@UF      2                 . START OF LINE BUFFER@[@@@Y.     @]@Y@XM$CSUBCE
)@@G@@*   . @^@@@YM$CALLSUBST*        .   @E@@@X          S         X11,SUBLNKCF
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @C@@@Y          S         X10,SUBSVX      CG
)@@G@@  . SAVE X10@E@Y@X          SZ        SUBSTK            . SET STACK EMPTCH
)@@G@@Y     @E@@@Y          L,U       X10,0             . SET STACK EMPTY     CI
)@@G@@@F@@@X          LSSL      A0,2              . GET INPUT CHARACTER COUNT CJ
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @C@@@X. R1 A0 A1 USED TO CONTROL CHARACTER FETCH.     @[@@@XCK
)@@G@@.     @E@@@X          L,U       R1,0,A0           . GET INPUT CHAR COUNTCL
)@@G@@@F@Y@X          L,U       A0,M$MBUF         . IMAGE IN MACRO BUFFER     CM
)@@G@@@F@@@Y          L,U       A0,M$READBUFFER   . IMAGE IN MACRO BUFFER     CN
)@@G@@@E@@@X          L         A1,M$XASL         . ASCII LOAD ROUTINE  @[@@@XCO
)@@G@@.     @C@@@X. R2 A2 A3 USED TO CONTROL CHARACTER STORE.     @[@@@X.     CP
)@@G@@@D@-@X          L,U       R2,4*20           . MAX 20 WORDS  @D@@@-      CQ
)@@G@@    L,U       R2,4*22           . MAX 22 WORDS  @E@Y@X          L,U     CR
)@@G@@  A2,M$EBUF         . TO EDIT$ BUFFER     @E@@@Y          L,U       A2,MCS
)@@G@@$EDITBUFFER   . TO EDIT$ BUFFER     @E@@@X          L         A3,M$XASS CT
)@@G@@        . ASCII STORE ROUTINE @[@@@X.     @C@@@X. TRANSFER CHARACTERS UNCU
)@@G@@TIL EOL, '[', OR ']'    @[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB010    . @F@@@X          JGCV
)@@G@@D       R1,$+2            . COUNT FETCHED CHARACTER   @E@@@X          J CW
)@@G@@        SUB210            . DONE : RETURN IMAGE @E@@@X          EX      CX
)@@G@@  0,*A1             . ELSE GET CHAR IN A5 @]@@@YSUB015    . @E@@@X      CY
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A5,OBC            . IF OPEN BRACKET     @E@@@X          J CZ
)@@G@@        SUB030            . CALL PUSH ROUTINE   @E@@@X          TNE,U   DA
)@@G@@  A5,CBC            . IF CLOSE BRACKET    @E@@@X          J         SUB0DB
)@@G@@40            . CALL POP ROUTINE    @[@@@X.     @^@@@X. STORE NORMAL CHADC
)@@G@@RACTER@[@@@X.     @E@@@X          JGD       R2,SUB020         . COUNT CHDD
)@@G@@ARACTER     @D@)@X          L         A5,SUBLER         . LENGTH ERROR  DE
)@@G@@@D@@@)          L         A5,SUBLEN         . LENGTH ERROR  @D@@@X      DF
)@@G@@    J         SUB999            . RETURN ERROR  @]@@@XSUB020    . @E@@@XDG
)@@G@@          EX        0,*A3             . STASH CHARACTER     @C@@@X      DH
)@@G@@    J         SUB010            . AND LOOP@[@@@Y/.    @[@@@X.     @D@@@XDI
)@@G@@. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN AN OPEN BRACKET IS SEEN.@[@@@X.     @]@@@XDJ
)@@G@@SUB030    . @E@@@X          DS        A0,SUBLDX         . SAVE LOAD INDIDK
)@@G@@CES   @D@@@X          S         R1,SUBLDC         . AND COUNTER   @[@@@XDL
)@@G@@.     @E@@@X. GET TEMP STORAGE BUFFER FOR EXPRESSION TO BE SCANNED.     DM
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @F@@@X          LXI,U     A3,0,A2           . SAVE STORE INDDN
)@@G@@EX IN A3    @E@@@X          TGET      22                . 2 + 20 FOR IMADO
)@@G@@GE    @E@@@X          JNZ       A5,SUB999         . IF ERROR RETURN     DP
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y. CHAIN IT INTO STACK   @[@@@Y.     @B@@@Y          S DQ
)@@G@@        X10,TSLINK,A1     .   @D@@@Y          L,U       X10,0,A1        DR
)@@G@@  . GET NEW STACK @[@@@Y.     @^@@@Y. SET UP STACK ENTRY    @[@@@Y.     DS
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          SZ        TSFLAG,X10        . CLEAR FLAG    @E@Y@X      DT
)@@G@@    S,H1      R2,0,A1           . SAVE STORE COUNT    @E@@@Y          S DU
)@@G@@        R2,TSSTOR,X10     . SAVE STORE COUNT    @D@Y@X          S       DV
)@@G@@  A3,1,A1           . AND POINTERS  @D@@@Y          S         A3,TSPTRS,DW
)@@G@@X10     . AND POINTERS  @[@@@X.     @B@@@X. SET UP NEW STORE INDEX POINTDX
)@@G@@ AT BUFFER  @[@@@X.     @D@@@X          L,U       R2,4*20           . STDY
)@@G@@ORE COUNT   @C@Y@X          L,U       A2,2,A1           . BUFFER  @C@@@YDZ
)@@G@@          L,U       A2,TSLINE,X10     . BUFFER  @E@@@X          L       EA
)@@G@@  A3,M$XASS         . ASCII STORE ROUTINE @[@Y@X.     @ @Y@X. CHAIN IT IEB
)@@G@@NTO SUBSTACK.     @[@Y@X.     @B@Y@X          L         A0,SUBSTK       EC
)@@G@@  .   @C@Y@X          S,H2      A0,0,A1           . LINK    @B@Y@X      ED
)@@G@@    S         A1,SUBSTK         .   @[@@@X.     @C@Y@X. RESTORE LOAD INDEE
)@@G@@EX AND RETURN TO FETCH LOOP.  @A@@@Y. RESTORE LOAD INDEX AND CONTINUE   EF
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @B@@@X          DL        A0,SUBLDX         .   @B@@@X      EG
)@@G@@    L         R1,SUBLDC         .   @[@@@Y.     @A@@@Y. CHECK FOR [* ...EH
)@@G@@ IF SO SET TSFLAG @[@@@Y.     @C@@@Y          JGD       R1,$+2          EI
)@@G@@  . CHECK IT@D@@@Y          J         SUB210            . OUT OF CHARS  EJ
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          EX        0,*A1             . GET NEXT CHARACTER  @D@@@YEK
)@@G@@          TE,U      A5,AST            . IS IT STAR    @F@@@Y          J EL
)@@G@@        SUB015            . NO - RETURN WITH CHAR     @E@@@Y          S EM
)@@G@@        A5,TSFLAG,X10     . SET FLAG ON STACK   @D@@@Y          J       EN
)@@G@@  SUB010            . AND ENTER LOOP@F@@@X          J         SUB010    EO
)@@G@@        . RESUME CHARACTER TRANSFER @[@@@Y/.    @[@@@X.     @D@@@X. THISEP
)@@G@@ ROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN A CLOSE BRACKET IS SEEN.@[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB040EQ
)@@G@@    . @E@@@X          DS        A0,SUBLDX         . SAVE LOAD INDEX     ER
)@@G@@@D@@@X          S         R1,SUBLDC         . AND COUNTER   @[@@@X.     ES
)@@G@@@E@@@X. IF SUBSTACK EMPTY THERE WERE TOO MANY CLOSE BRACKETS.     @[@@@XET
)@@G@@.     @D@@@X          L         A5,SUBRBR         . ERROR MESSAGE @D@Y@XEU
)@@G@@          L         A0,SUBSTK         . STACK ENTRY   @E@@@Y          TNEV
)@@G@@Z,U     0,X10             . IS THERE A STACK    @D@@@Y          J       EW
)@@G@@  SUB999            . IF NOT ERROR  @E@Y@X          JZ        A0,SUB999 EX
)@@G@@        . IF STACK EMPTY ERROR@[@@@X.     @ @@@X. SCAN EXPRESSION FOR VAEY
)@@G@@LUE.  @[@@@X.     @E@Y@X          AN,U      A2,1,A0           . COMPUTE EZ
)@@G@@WORD COUNT  @E@@@Y          L,U       A1,1,A2           . COMPUTE WORD CFA
)@@G@@OUNT  @B@@@Y          L,U       R1,3              .   @B@@@Y          L,FB
)@@G@@U       A5,040            .   @E@@@YSUB050    EX        0,*A3           FC
)@@G@@  . BLANK FILL IMAGE    @B@@@Y          JGD       R1,SUB050         .   FD
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          AN,U      A1,TSLINE,X10     . COMPUTE WORD COUNT  @E@Y@XFE
)@@G@@          LDSL      A1,18+36          . MOVE TO H1 OF A1    @E@@@Y      FF
)@@G@@    LSSL      A1,18             . MOVE TO H1 OF A1    @E@Y@X          LXFG
)@@G@@M,U     A1,2,A0           . FORM ACCESS WORD    @E@@@Y          LXM,U   FH
)@@G@@  A1,TSLINE,X10     . FORM ACCESS WORD    @E@@@X          T$OPENA   M$TPFI
)@@G@@KT            . AXW FOR IMAGE IN A1 @E@Y@X          LMJ       X11,M$SEXPFJ
)@@G@@        . SCAN FOR EXPRESSION @E@@@Y          LMJ       X11,M$SCANEXPR  FK
)@@G@@  . SCAN FOR EXPRESSION @E@@@Y          T$CLOSE                     . CLFL
)@@G@@OSE TIDE$ AGAIN   @E@Y@X          JNZ       A5,SUB060         . IF ERRORFM
)@@G@@ SKIP CHECK @E@@@Y          JNZ       A5,SUB999         . IF ERROR SKIP FN
)@@G@@CHECK @[@@@Y/.    @[@@@Y.     @A@@@Y. EXAMINE SUBSTITUTION REQUESTED    FO
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @[@Y@X.     @B@Y@X. EXPRESSION MUST BE INTEGER OR NULL.     FP
)@@G@@@[@Y@X.     @D@Y@X          TE,U      A0,MODNUL         . IS IT NULL    FQ
)@@G@@@F@Y@X          JNZ       A0,SUB050         . IF NOT NULL SET ERROR FLAGFR
)@@G@@@E@Y@X          TG,U      A2,0              . LENGTH ZERO THRU 2  @B@Y@XFS
)@@G@@          TG,U      A2,3              .   @E@Y@XSUB050    L         A5,SFT
)@@G@@UBERR         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   @]@Y@XSUB060    . @F@Y@X          S FU
)@@G@@        A5,SUBTMP         . SAVE ERROR FLAG OVER CLOSE@E@Y@X          T$FV
)@@G@@IDEX                      . CLOSE TIDE$ SCANNER @E@Y@X          L       FW
)@@G@@  A5,SUBTMP         . GET ERROR FLAG AGAIN@E@Y@X          JNZ       A5,SFX
)@@G@@UB999         . IF ERROR RETURN     @[@Y@X.     @C@Y@X. SUBSTITUTE ARGUMFY
)@@G@@ENT FROM MACRO STACK ENTRY.   @[@Y@X.     @F@Y@X          L         A0,MFZ
)@@G@@$MXQT         . GET MACRO STACK ENTRY     @F@Z@Y          L         A0,MGA
)@@G@@$XQTMACRO     . GET MACRO STACK ENTRY     @F@@@Z          L,H2      A0,MGB
)@@G@@$XQTMACRO     . GET MACRO STACK ENTRY     @F@@@Y          L         A5,SGC
)@@G@@UBARG         . GET NO ARG ERROR MESSAGE  @E@@@Y          JZ        A0,SGD
)@@G@@UB999         . IF NO ARGS GET OUT  @D@@@X          L         A2,CXARGS,GE
)@@G@@A0      . GET ARG BUFFER@E@@@Y          L         A0,CSMODE         . GEGF
)@@G@@T MODE OF ARG     @E@@@Y          L         A4,CSLONG         . AND LENGGG
)@@G@@TH OF ARG   @D@@@Y          TE,U      A0,MODNUL         . IS IT A NULL  GH
)@@G@@@E@@@Y          J         SUB060            . IF NOT SKIP AWAY    @E@Y@XGI
)@@G@@          L         A4,CSLONG         . GET ARGUMENT LENGTH @F@Y@X      GJ
)@@G@@    JNZ       A4,SUB070         . IF NONZERO CANNOT BE NULL @D@@@Y      GK
)@@G@@    TZ        TSFLAG,X10        . STAR SEEN     @D@@@Y          J       GL
)@@G@@  SUB070            . YES - DO [*]  @[@@@X.     @B@@@X. '[]' - SUBSTITUTGM
)@@G@@E NUMBER OF FIELDS.     @[@@@X.     @E@@@X          L,H1      A0,0,A2   GN
)@@G@@        . GET NUMBER OF FIELDS@E@Y@X          J         SUB120          GO
)@@G@@  . AND EDIT IN NUMBER  @E@@@Y          J         SUB110            . ANGP
)@@G@@D EDIT IN NUMBER  @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. SOMETHING OUT THERE.  GET IT.     GQ
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @]@Y@XSUB070    . @]@@@YSUB060    . @D@@@Y          TZ      GR
)@@G@@  TSFLAG,X10        . STAR SEEN     @F@@@Y          J         SUB145    GS
)@@G@@        . YES - EDIT EXPRESSION [*E]@F@)@Y          L         A5,M$ZSET GT
)@@G@@        . GET ERROR SUBSCRIPT TYPE  @E@@@)          L         A5,SUBTER GU
)@@G@@        . GET ERROR SUBST TYPE@E@@@Y          JNZ       A0,SUB999       GV
)@@G@@  . IF NOT INTEGER ERROR@F@@@)          L         A5,SUBLER         . GEGW
)@@G@@T ERROR LSUBST LENGTH   @D@@@Y          TG,U      A4,1              . LEGX
)@@G@@NGTH 1 OR 2 @B@@@Y          TG,U      A4,3              .   @D@@@Y      GY
)@@G@@    J         SUB999            . IF NOT ERROR  @E@@@X          L       GZ
)@@G@@  A0,CSADDR         . GET ITEM ADDRESS    @F@@@X          DL        A0,0HA
)@@G@@,A0           . GET ARGUMENT INTEGERS     @F@@@X          JNZ       A0,SHB
)@@G@@UB080         . IF NONZERO IS NOT '*'     @F@@@X          JP        A0,SHC
)@@G@@UB080         . IF POSITIVE IS NOT '*'    @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. '[*]' - SUHD
)@@G@@BSTITUTE ALL FIELDS.    @[@@@X.     @F@Y@X          L,U       A0,1      HE
)@@G@@        . START AT CHARACTER ONE    @]@@@YSUB070    . @G@@@Y          L,HF
)@@G@@U       A0,1              . IF NO ARGS START AT COLUMN ONE  @C@@@Y      HG
)@@G@@    TZ,H1     0,A2              . ANY ARGS@F@@@Y          L,H1      A0,2HH
)@@G@@,A2           . YES - GET FIRST ARG CHAR  @G@@@X          L,H2      A1,0HI
)@@G@@,A2           . END AT LAST CHARACTER IN IMAGE  @E@@@X          J       HJ
)@@G@@  SUB170            . EDIT CHARACTERS     @[@@@X.     @D@@@X. '[N...'  -HK
)@@G@@  FIND FIELD 'N' ENTRY IN ARG BUFFER.     @[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB080    . HL
)@@G@@@E@@@X          L         A5,SUBFEX         . FIELDS EXCEEDED     @E@@@XHM
)@@G@@          AN,U      A0,1              . SUBTRACT FOR TEST   @E@@@X      HN
)@@G@@    JN        A0,SUB999         . IF NEGATIVE ERROR   @C@@@X          TGHO
)@@G@@,H1     A0,0,A2           . WITHIN  @D@@@X          J         SUB999    HP
)@@G@@        . NO - ERROR    @F@@@X          L,U       A3,1,A2           . POHQ
)@@G@@INT A3 AT FIELD ONE     @E@@@X          J         SUB100            . ENHR
)@@G@@TRY TO SKIP LOOP  @]@@@XSUB090    . @E@@@X          A,H1      A3,0,A3   HS
)@@G@@        . SKIP PAST THIS FIELD@F@@@X          A,U       A3,1            HT
)@@G@@  . AND IT'S CONTROL WORD     @D@@@XSUB100    JGD       A0,SUB090       HU
)@@G@@  . COUNT FIELD   @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. A3 POINTS TO FIELD 'N' ENTRY.     HV
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @F@@@X          TE,U      A4,1              . LENGTH OF ARGUHW
)@@G@@MENT ONE    @E@@@X          J         SUB150            . NO - MUST BE THX
)@@G@@WO    @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. '[N]' - EDIT NUMBER OF SUBFIELDS  @[@@@X.     HY
)@@G@@@F@@@X          L,H1      A0,0,A3           . GET NUMBER OF SUBFIELDS   HZ
)@@G@@@[@@@Y/.    @[@@@X.     @ @@@X. SUBSTITUTE NUMBER IN A0.    @#@@@Y. (NOTIA
)@@G@@E FALL-THRU)@[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB110    . @G@Y@X          L         A3,SIB
)@@G@@UBSTK         . GET SUBST STACK ENTRY AGAIN     @F@Y@X          L,H1    IC
)@@G@@  R2,0,A3           . RECOVER OLD STORE INDEX   @F@@@Y          L       ID
)@@G@@  R2,TSSTOR,X10     . RECOVER OLD STORE INDEX   @D@Y@X          L,H1    IE
)@@G@@  A2,1,A3           . AND COUNTER   @D@@@Y          L,H1      A2,TSPTRS,IF
)@@G@@X10     . AND COUNTER   @B@Y@X          L,H2      A3,1,A3           .   IG
)@@G@@@B@@@Y          L,H2      A3,TSPTRS,X10     .   @F@@@X          LXI,U   IH
)@@G@@  A3,1              . SET INCREMENT OF STORE EX @F@@@X          L,U     II
)@@G@@  A4,0              . CLEAR DIGIT ACCUMULATOR   @]@@@XSUB120    . @E@@@XIJ
)@@G@@          DSL       A0,36             . FIND NEXT DIGIT     @B@@@X      IK
)@@G@@    DI,U      A0,10             .   @D@@@X          LSSL      A4,9      IL
)@@G@@        . MAKE ROOM     @F@@@X          A,U       A4,060,A1         . FOIM
)@@G@@RM NEXT ASCII DIGIT     @E@@@X          JNZ       A0,SUB120         . IFIN
)@@G@@ MORE GET THEM    @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. ASCII DIGITS FOR NUMBER IN A4.    IO
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB130    . @F@@@X          JGD       R2,SUB140       IP
)@@G@@  . IS THERE ROOM TO STORE IT @G@@@X          L         A5,SUBLEN       IQ
)@@G@@  . NO - GET LENGTH ERROR MESSAGE   @E@@@X          J         SUB999    IR
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN IN ERROR @]@@@XSUB140    . @D@@@X          DSL     IS
)@@G@@  A4,9              . DIGIT TO A5   @B@@@X          SSL       A5,27     IT
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@X          EX        0,*A3             . STORE DIGIT   IU
)@@G@@@F@@@X          JNZ       A4,SUB130         . IF MORE DIGITS DO THEN    IV
)@@G@@@F@@@X          J         SUB200            . FINISHED SUBSTITUTION     IW
)@@G@@@[@@@Y.     @ @@@Y. [*E] - SUBSTITUTE EXPRESSION@[@@@Y.     @]@@@YSUB145IX
)@@G@@    . @D@@@Y          L,U       A0,CSDESC         . GET DESCRIPTOR@E@@@YIY
)@@G@@          L,U       A1,MODASC         . CONVERT TO ASCII    @E@@@Y      IZ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,M$CONVMODE    . USING CONVERTER     @C@@@Y          JNJA
)@@G@@Z       A5,SUB999         . OOPS    @F@@@Y          LXI,U     A2,0,A1   JB
)@@G@@        . GET ADDRESS OF STRING     @E@@@Y          L,U       A1,0,A2   JC
)@@G@@        . GET NUMBER OF CHARS @E@@@Y          L,U       A0,0            JD
)@@G@@  . START AT CHAR 0     @D@@@Y          J         SUB170            . SUJE
)@@G@@BSTITUTE    @[@@@X.     @A@@@X. '[N,*]' OR '[N,M]' - CHECK IT OUT.@[@@@XJF
)@@G@@.     @]@@@XSUB150    . @F@@@X          JNZ       A1,SUB160         . IFJG
)@@G@@ NONZERO IS NOT '*'     @F@@@X          JP        A1,SUB160         . IFJH
)@@G@@ POSITIVE IS NOT '*'    @[@@@X.     @C@@@X. '[N,*]' - EDIT ALL SUBFIELDSJI
)@@G@@ OF 'N'TH FIELD   @[@@@X.     @E@@@X          L,H1      A0,1,A3         JJ
)@@G@@  . GET START OF FIELD  @E@@@X          L,H2      A1,0,A3           . ANJK
)@@G@@D END OF FIELD    @D@@@X          J         SUB170            . EDIT ARGJL
)@@G@@UMENTS@[@@@X.     @ @@@X. '[N,M]' - EDIT SUBFIELD     @[@@@X.     @]@@@XJM
)@@G@@SUB160    . @B@@@Y          AN,U      A1,1              .   @B@@@Y      JN
)@@G@@    JN        A1,SUB999         .   @E@@@X          TG,H1     A1,0,A3   JO
)@@G@@        . FIELD WITHIN RANGE  @D@@@X          J         SUB999          JP
)@@G@@  . NO - ERROR    @F@Y@X          A,U       A3,0,A1           . GET 'M' JQ
)@@G@@TH SUBFIELD ENTRY @F@@@Y          A,U       A3,1,A1           . GET 'M' JR
)@@G@@TH SUBFIELD ENTRY @D@@@X          L,H1      A0,0,A3           . GET STARJS
)@@G@@T     @C@@@X          L,H2      A1,0,A3           . AND END @[@@@Y/.    JT
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @A@@@X. SUBSTITUTE FIELD FROM CALL IMAGE. @E@Y@X. A0 - STARTJU
)@@G@@ COLUMN A1 - END COLUMN A2 - ARGUMENT BUFFER    @D@@@Y. A0 - START COLUMJV
)@@G@@N A1 - END COLUMN A2 - ARGS,POINTER @#@@@Y. (NOTE FALL-THRU)@[@@@X.     JW
)@@G@@@]@@@XSUB170    . @B@@@Y          A,U       A1,1              .   @E@@@XJX
)@@G@@          S         A1,SUBTMP         . SAVE END COLUMN     @E@@@X      JY
)@@G@@    L,U       A4,0,A0           . SAVE START COLUMN   @E@@@X          DSJZ
)@@G@@L       A0,2              . FIND LOAD INDEX     @B@@@X          SSL     KA
)@@G@@  A1,34             .   @B@Y@X<         A,U       A0,ARG BUFFER ADDRESS KB
)@@G@@@D@@@Y          SSL       A2,18             . MOVE TO H2    @F@@@Y      KC
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,0,A2           . ADD CALL IMAGE ADDRESS    @E@Y@X      KD
)@@G@@    A         A1,M$SASL         . ASCII LOAD ROUTINE  @E@@@Y          A KE
)@@G@@        A1,M$XASL         . ASCII LOAD ROUTINE  @[@@@X.     @B@@@X. RESTKF
)@@G@@ORE STORE INDEX FROM TEMP STACK.    @[@@@X.     @B@Y@X          L       KG
)@@G@@  A3,SUBSTK         .   @D@Y@X          L,H1      R2,0,A3           . LOKH
)@@G@@AD COUNT    @D@@@Y          L         R2,TSSTOR,X10     . LOAD COUNT    KI
)@@G@@@C@Y@X          L,H1      A2,1,A3           . INDEX   @C@@@Y          L,KJ
)@@G@@H1      A2,TSPTRS,X10     . INDEX   @C@Y@X          L,H2      A3,1,A3   KK
)@@G@@        . INDEX   @C@@@Y          L,H2      A3,TSPTRS,X10     . INDEX   KL
)@@G@@@D@@@X          LXI,U     A3,1              . INCREMENT     @[@@@X.     KM
)@@G@@@^@@@X. STORE CHARACTERS.     @[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB180    . @D@@@X      KN
)@@G@@    TG        A4,SUBTMP         . ARE WE DONE   @D@@@X          J       KO
)@@G@@  SUB200            . YES - DONE    @D@@@X          JGD       R2,SUB190 KP
)@@G@@        . IS THERE ROOM @E@@@X          L         A5,SUBLEN         . NOKQ
)@@G@@ - GET ERROR PCW  @D@@@X          J         SUB999            . AND RETUKR
)@@G@@RN    @]@@@XSUB190    . @C@@@X          EX        0,*A1             . GEKS
)@@G@@T CHAR@C@@@X          EX        0,*A3             . PUT CHAR@G@@@X      KT
)@@G@@    A,U       A4,1              . INCREMENT CHARACTER COUNTER     @C@@@XKU
)@@G@@          J         SUB180            . LOOP    @[@@@X.     @E@Y@X. SUBSKV
)@@G@@TITUTION DONE.  POP SUBSTK AND RETURN TO FETCH LOOP.  @E@@@Y. SUBSTITUTIKW
)@@G@@ON DONE.  POP STACK AND RETURN TO FETCH LOOP.   @[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB200KX
)@@G@@    . @E@@@Y          L,U       A0,0,X10          . GET OLD STACK ENTRY KY
)@@G@@@E@Y@X          L         A0,SUBSTK         . GET SUB STACK ENTRY @C@Y@XKZ
)@@G@@          L,H2      A1,0,A0           . UNSTACK @C@@@Y          L       LA

)@@G@@  . ENTRY   @F@@@X          TREL                        . RELEASE CORE ULC

)@@G@@@F@@@X. CONTROL PASSES HERE WHEN THE LAST CHARACTER IS FETCHED FROM THE LH
)@@G@@@F@@@X. IMAGE BEING SUBSTITUTED.  STACK MUST BE EMPTY OR NOT ENUF ']'.  LI
)@@G@@@[@@@X.     @]@@@XSUB210    . @F@@@X          L         A5,SUBLBR       LJ

)@@G@@ EMPTY@D@@@X          J         SUB999            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@XLM
)@@G@@.     @A@@@X. BLANK FILL REMAINDER OF IMAGE.    @[@@@X.     @F@@@X      LN
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,1,A2           . GET LAST WORD STORED INTO @C@@@X      LO
)@@G@@    L,U       R1,3              . DO 4    @D@@@X          L,U       A5,0LP
)@@G@@40            . ASCII BLANK   @D@@@XSUB220    EX        0,*A3           LQ
)@@G@@  . STASH CHAR    @C@@@X          JGD       R1,SUB220         . LOOP    LR
)@@G@@@E@Y@X          AN,U      A0,M$EBUF         . COMPUTE WORD COUNT  @E@@@YLS

)@@G@@UF)     .   @B@@@Y          L         A1,(1,M$EDITBUFFER) . @B@Y@X      LV

)@@G@@ADBUFFER) . @G@@@X          BT        A2,0,*A1          . MOVE IMAGE BACLX
)@@G@@K TO MACRO BUFFER @E@@@X          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERLY
)@@G@@ROR FLAG    @[@@@X.     @^@@@X. RETURN TO CALLER.     @[@@@X.     @]@@@XLZ
)@@G@@SUB999    . @D@@@Y          L         X10,SUBSVX        . RESTORE X10   MA
)@@G@@@E@@@X          L         X11,SUBLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@XMB
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@X.     MC
)@@G@@@^@@@X. FIXED DATA AREAS.     @[@@@X.     @D@@@YSUBLNK    VAR       'SUBMD
)@@G@@LNK',1        . LINK HOME     @C@@@YSUBSVX    VAR       'SUBSVX',1      ME

)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             MZ
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO 'CALL' A MACRONA
)@@G@@.  A1 IS ASSUMED TO POINT     @F@@@@. TO THE MACRO DEFINITION ENTRY, ANDNB
)@@G@@ ITS INCREMENT SHOULD BE SET  @F@@@@. TO THE VALUE TO BE SET INTO CXFLAGNC
)@@G@@.  A0 SHOULD BE SET TO THE    @D@@@@. ARGUMENT POINTERS, IT WILL BE PLACND
)@@G@@ED IN CXARGS.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$XQTCALL*          .   @B@@@@      NE
)@@G@@    S         X11,CALINK        .   @E@@@@          DS        A0,CCMACR NF
)@@G@@        . SAVE MACRO ADDRESS  @E@@@@          PGET      CXSIZE          NG
)@@G@@  . GET EXECUTION BUFFER@C@@@@          JNZ       A5,CAL999         . ERNH
)@@G@@ROR   @D@@@@          L,U       R1,11             . INITIALIZE IT @B@@@@NI
)@@G@@          L         A2,(1,M$OUTPACKET) .  @B@@@@          L,U       A0,0NJ

)@@G@@@B@@@@          S,H2      A2,7,A0           .   @D@@@@          S       NU
)@@G@@  A0,CCMACR         . SAVE PROC     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IF TRACED OR SUSNV
)@@G@@PENDED PRINT 'ENTER <MACRO-NAME> '. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          TNZ     NW
)@@G@@  CXTRAC,A0         . IS IT TRACED ?@D@@@@          TZ        CXSUSP,A0 NX
)@@G@@        . OR SUSPENDED ?@B@@@@          J         $+2               .   NY
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         CAL020            . NO@D@@@@          E$OPEN  NZ
)@@G@@  M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT     @B@@@@          E$MSG     ENMACR    OA

)@@G@@@F@@@@          PGET      4*28              . GET BUFFERS FOR INPUT     OF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          JNZ       A5,CAL999         .   @B@@@@          L       OG
)@@G@@  A0,CCMACR         .   @B@@@@          S,H2      A1,6,A0           .   OH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          PGET      4*28              .   @B@@@@          JNZ     OI
)@@G@@  A5,CAL999         .   @B@@@@          L         A0,CCMACR         .   OJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          S,H1      A1,6,A0           .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@      OK
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,4              . SET BUFFER SIZE     @D@@@@          S,OL

)@@G@@        . SET BUFFER ADDRESS  @F@@@@          SDFIO     CXPKT,CAL090    OR
)@@G@@  . OPEN INPUT FROM MACRO     @F@@@@          L,H2      A1,M$XQTMACRO   OS

)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          S,H2      A0,M$XQTMACRO     .   @E@@@@          L,OU

)@@G@@  CAL999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ERROR OPENING FROW
)@@G@@OM SCRATCH FILE (!!)    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@CAL090    L         A5,CALSDF OX
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. RETURN TO CALLER.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@OY

)@@G@@R       'CALINK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@E@@@@CCMACR    VAR       'CCMPB

)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@ENMACR    '*** ENTER & ***&'  PD

)@@G@@D                         .   ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@PH

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@A      PJ
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@A          M$APROC             PK
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@A.     @H@@@A. THIS IS THE INTERRUPT HANDLER FOR THE MAPL
)@@G@@CRO PACKAGE.  CERTAIN INTERRUPTS    @G@@@A. ARE FIELDED BY THE MACRO PACPM
)@@G@@KAGE AND RETURNED TO THE PROGRAM.  OTHERS @^@@@E. CAUSE AN EABT$ EXIT.  PN
)@@G@@@G@E@A. CANNOT.  IF THE PARAMETER REP IS SET TO ONE THE HANDLER CALLS THPO
)@@G@@E     @G@E@A. UOM ERROR HANDLER REP ERROR$.  IF THE PARAMETER IS SET TO PP
)@@G@@ZERO THEN   @H@E@A. THE CONTINGENCY PACKET IS DUMPED IN OCTAL.  IN EITHEPQ
)@@G@@R CASE AN EABT$ EXIT    @]@E@A. IS TAKEN. @[@@@A.     @B@E@AREP       EQPR
)@@G@@U       1                 .   @[@E@A.     @^@@@AM$INTERRUPTS*       .   PS
)@@G@@@D@@@A          DS        A0,ERPA01         . SAVE A0 AND A1@E@@@A      PT
)@@G@@    L         A0,INTTYP         . GET CONTINGENCY TYPE@D@@@A          TNPU
)@@G@@E,U     A0,010            . IS IT II ?    @C@@@A          J         INTEPV
)@@G@@R             . YES     @D@@@A          TE,U      A0,012            . ISPW
)@@G@@ IT EMODE ? @E@@@A          J         ERRCAL            . NO - CALL ERROPX
)@@G@@R$    @[@@@A.     @B@@@A. EMODE ERROR.  EXAMINE TO SEE WHAT TYPE. @[@@@APY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@A          L         A0,EMDTYP         . GET EMODE TYPE@E@@@APZ
)@@G@@          L         A1,EMDCOD         . GET EMODE CODE TOO  @E@@@A      QA
)@@G@@    TG,U      A0,EMDLEN+1       . IS IT IN THE TABLE  @E@@@A          J QB
)@@G@@        ERRCAL            . NO - CALL ERROR$    @E@@@A          J       QC
)@@G@@  EMDTAB,A0         . CALL ROUTINE FOR IT @[@@@A/.    @[@@@A.     @ @@@AQD
)@@G@@. SPECIFIC ERROR HANDLERS.    @[@@@A.     @]@@@AINTER     . @C@@@A      QE
)@@G@@    L         A1,EMDTYP         . GET TYPE@E@@@A          L         A0,RQF
)@@G@@BKPCW         . AND REMOTE BREAK PCW@F@@@A          TNE,U     A1,2      QG
)@@G@@        . WAS INTERRUPT REMOTE BREAK@F@@@A          S         A0,M$BREAKQH
)@@G@@        . YES - SET MACRO BREAK FLAG@E@@@A          J         CRTN      QI
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN NORMALLY @[@@@A.     @]@@@AIOERR     . @F@@@A      QJ
)@@G@@    L,H2      A0,M$CPKT+1       . GET IO PACKET ADDRESS     @F@@@A      QK
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A1,023            . IS ERROR BAD PACKET ?     @G@@@A      QL
)@@G@@    J         ERRCAL            . YES - CANNOT STORE INTO PACKET  @F@@@AQM
)@@G@@          S,S1      A1,3,A0           . STORE CODE INTO PACKET    @D@@@AQN
)@@G@@          J         CRTN              . AND RETURN    @[@@@A.     @]@@@AQO
)@@G@@SYMBI     . @E@@@A          TE,U      A1,041            . IS IT MAX PAGEQP
)@@G@@S     @D@@@A          TNE,U     A1,042            . OR MAX CARDS  @G@@@AQQ
)@@G@@          J         MAXPC             . YES - PROCESS THEM SEPARATELY   QR
)@@G@@@E@@@A          TNE,U     A1,02             . IS IT READ PAST EOF @E@@@AQS
)@@G@@          J         SRFLAG            . YES - END GRACEFULLY@E@@@A      QT
)@@G@@    TG,U      A0,010            . @ADD ERROR IN CSF$  @B@@@A          TGQU
)@@G@@,U      A0,017            .   @D@@@A          J         CSFAD           QV
)@@G@@  . YES - SET A0  @F@@@A          TE,U      A0,05             . BAD @ADDQW
)@@G@@ IN RUNSTREAM     @E@@@A          J         ERRCAL            . NO - CALQX
)@@G@@L ERROR$    @D@@@A          SZ        ERPA01            . CLEAR USER A0 QY
)@@G@@@D@@@A          J         CRTN              . AND RETURN    @[@@@A.     QZ
)@@G@@@]@E@ACSFAD     . @B@E@A          L         A0,(0600000000000) .  @G@E@ARA
)@@G@@          S         A0,ERPA01         . SET ERROR CODE INTO USER A0     RB
)@@G@@@B@E@A          J         CRTN              .   @[@E@A.     @]@@@ASRFLAGRC
)@@G@@    . @E@@@A          L,U       A0,1              . SET FLAG THAT SEZ TORD
)@@G@@@E@@@A          S         A0,M$REOF         . NOT READ ANY MORE   @D@@@ARE
)@@G@@          SZ        ERPA01            . CLEAR USER A0 @C@@@A          J RF
)@@G@@        CRTN              . RETURN  @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMAXPC     . @D@@@ARG
)@@G@@          TNZ       M$DEMAND          . IS HE DEMAND  @E@@@A          J RH
)@@G@@        ERRCAL            . NO - CALL ERROR$    @C@@@A          L       RI
)@@G@@  A0,MPGPCW-041,A1  . GET PCW @E@@@A          S         A0,M$BREAK      RJ
)@@G@@  . SET MACRO BROKEN    @D@@@A          J         CRTN              . ANRK
)@@G@@D RETURN    @[@@@A.     @]@@@AERERR     . @E@@@A          TE,U      A1,0RL
)@@G@@53            . IS ERROR BAD MCORE$ @B@@@A          TNE,U     A1,055    RM
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@A          J         MCORE             . YES     @E@@@ARN
)@@G@@          TG,U      A1,040            . IS ERROR IN CSF$    @C@@@A      RO

)@@G@@        A0,ERPA01         . IN USER A0    @D@@@A          J         CRTNRS
)@@G@@              . AND RETURN    @[@@@A.     @]@@@AMCORE     . @G@@@A      RT
)@@G@@    SZ        ERPA01            . CLEAR A0 AS FLAG TO MCORE GUY   @[@@@ARU
)@@G@@.     @B@@@A. TAKE RETURN TO USER CODE (NEXT INSTR)   @[@@@A.     @]@@@ARV
)@@G@@CRTN      . @B@@@A          L,H2      A0,M$CPKT         .   @B@@@A      RW
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              .   @B@@@A          S,H2      A0,M$CPKT RX
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@A          DL        A0,ERPA01         . GET REGISTERS RY
)@@G@@BACK AGAIN  @E@@@A          ER        CRTN$             . CONTINGENCY RERZ
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@A/.    @[@@@A.     @A@@@A. FATAL ERROR.  CALL ERROR$ REP.    SA
)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @]@@@AERRCAL    . @C@@@A          S         X11,ERPX11      SB
)@@G@@  . SAVE X11@F@@@A          DL        A0,M$CPKT         . GET CONTINGENCSC
)@@G@@Y PACKET    @E@@@A          LMJ       X11,M$ERRCONT     . LINK TO ERROR SD
)@@G@@REP   @D@@@A          DSL       A0,72             . CLEAR IALL$   @B@@@ASE
)@@G@@          ER        IALL$             .   @D@@@A          DL        A0,ESF

)@@G@@  . RECOVER X11   @D@@@A          ER        EABT$             . AND ABORSH
)@@G@@T     @[@@@A.     @]@@@AEMDTAB    . @D@@@A          J         ERRCAL    SI
)@@G@@        . 0 - UNKNOWN   @D@@@A          J         IOERR             . 1 SJ
)@@G@@- I/O ERROR @E@@@A          J         SYMBI             . 2 - SYMBIONT ESK
)@@G@@RROR  @D@@@A          J         ERRCAL            . 3 - ERR$ CALL @E@@@ASL
)@@G@@          J         ERERR             . 4 - ER CALL ERROR   @C@@@AEMDLENSM
)@@G@@    EQU       $-EMDTAB          . LENGTH  @[@@@A.     @B@@@A. DATA AREASSN
)@@G@@ USED BY INTERRUPT HANDLER    @[@@@A.     @^@@@A          VARS      .   SO
)@@G@@@B@@@AM$IALL*   +         0772700,M$CPKT    .   @[@@@A.     @F@@@AM$CPKTSP

)@@G@@  .   @[@@@A.     @B@@@ARBKPCW    +         0102,RBKMSG       .   @D@@@ASU

)@@G@@        0102,MXCMSG       . MAX CARDS     @[@@@A.     @B@@@ARBKMSG    'RSW

)@@G@@  .   @B@@@AMXCMSG    'MAX CARDS'                 .   @[@@@A/.    @E@E@ASY
)@@G@@          ON        REP               . IF ERROR$ CONFIGURED@[@@@A.     SZ
)@@G@@@E@@@A. CALL THE ERROR$ REP TO DIAGNOSE CONTINGENCY AND RETURN    @E@@@ATA
)@@G@@. TO CALLER.  THIS IS BASICALLY FOR THE CPMD CONTIN COMMAND @[@@@A.     TB
)@@G@@@B@@@A          INSTRS                      .   @[@@@A.     @^@@@AM$ERRCTC

)@@G@@RR005         . PFI$ ERROR    @D@@@BM$ERRPFD* LMJ       A1,ERR005       TQ

)@@G@@ERR005    . @D@@@C          L,U       A1,0,A1           . CLEAR UPPER   TT
)@@G@@@E@@@B          AN,U      A1,M$ERRPFX+1-20  . MAKE ERROR CODE     @C@D@BTU
)@@G@@          TSNAP     'PFCOD',A1        . TEMP    @[@@@B.     @B@@@B. ENTRTV

)@@G@@DIAGNOSTIC  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. IF TOP-OF-STACK IS ANOTHER OPERATOR WE SXU
)@@G@@TACK A NULL (TYPE MODNUL)     @G@@@@. ROUTINES CAN CHECK THEIR LEFTARGS,XV
)@@G@@ IF MODNUL THE OPERATOR WAS CALLED  @#@@@@. MONADICALLY.    @[@@@@.     XW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A4,RAMODE         . GET MODE OF STACKTOP@E@@@@XX
)@@G@@          TE,U      A4,MODOPR         . IS IT AN OPERATION ?@B@@@@      XY
)@@G@@    J         SCN020            . NO@G@@@@          PUSH      SCN090    XZ

)@@G@@  . SET ON TOP OF STACK @F@@@@          SZ        RAVALU            . VAYC
)@@G@@LUE OF NULL IS ZERO     @[@@@@/.    @E@@@@. FOR ALL OP OP WE HAVE JUST SYD
)@@G@@TACKED OP NULL, NOW STACK     @D@@@@. THE SECOND OPERATOR WITH OUT EVALUYE
)@@G@@ATING THE STACK   @C@@@@. THIS CAUSES THE OPERATORS TO BE EVALUATED FROMYF
)@@G@@@D@@@@. RIGHT TO LEFT, AND HENCE IF THE SECOND OPERATOR     @C@@@@. IS AYG
)@@G@@ MONADIC OPERATOR EVERYTHING WORKS.  IF IT@D@@@@. IS A DYADIAC OPERATOR YH
)@@G@@IT WILL SEE A NULL LEFT ARG   @A@@@@. WHEN BEING EVALUATED AND ERROR.   YI
)@@G@@@^@@@@.     TWO EXCEPTIONS    @E@@@@. EVALUATE THE STACK FOR THE END-OF-YJ
)@@G@@LINE OPERATOR RATHER    @D@@@@. THAN STACK IT.  OTHERWISE WE GET A STACKYK
)@@G@@ OVERFLOW.  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ALSO EVALUATE FOR CLOSE PAREN, TO MAKE *YL
)@@G@@ WORK.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          TE,U      A1,M$OPEREOL      . END OF LYM
)@@G@@INE OPERATOR?     @E@@@@          TNE,U     A1,M$OPERCLOSEP   . OR CLOSEYN
)@@G@@ PAREN?     @D@@@@          J         $+2               . YES - CONTINUEYO
)@@G@@@H@@@@          J         SCN050            . NO, STACK WITHOUT CHECKINGYP
)@@G@@ PRECEDENCE @]@@@@SCN020    . @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. KLUGE FOR OPEN PAREN -YQ
)@@G@@ STACK ALWAYS     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          TNE,U     A1,M$OPEROPENPA YR
)@@G@@  . OPEN PAREN OPERATOR ?     @F@@@@          J         SCN050          YS
)@@G@@  . YES - STACK IMMEDIATELY   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPARE PRIORITIES OF YT
)@@G@@OPERATOR IN STACK WITH CURRENT OPERATOR   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@SCN030    . YU
)@@G@@@H@@@@          L         A0,OPPRIO         . GET PRIORITY OF OPERATOR IYV

)@@G@@T CURRENT OP@H@@@@          J         SCN050            . NEW OP HIGHER YX
)@@G@@- STACK AND CONTINUE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE NEW OPERATION IS OF LOWEYY
)@@G@@R PRIORITY.  PERFORM THE OPERATION  @F@@@@. ON THE STACK, WHICH WILL POPYZ
)@@G@@ IT, AND RETURN ABOVE TO MAKE THE   @E@@@@. TEST AGAINST THE NEXT OPERATZA
)@@G@@ION DOWN.  THE END-OF-LINE    @F@@@@. CHARACTERS HAVE THE LOWEST PRIORITZB
)@@G@@Y, AND SO EVENTUALLY THE ONE  @F@@@@. AT THE BASE OF THE STACK WILL BE EZC
)@@G@@VALUATED.  THIS TRANSFERS     @^@@@@. CONTROL TO SCNRET.    @[@@@@.     ZD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A0,OPADDR         . GET ADDRESS OF DYADIC OP  ZE
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LMJ       X11,0,A0          . CALL OPERATOR @E@@@@      ZF

)@@G@@ OPERATOR IS FAKED.  THE STACK MANAGEMENT @G@@@@. ROUTINES ENSURE THAT TZL

)@@G@@N060          . PRIO 1 EXIT   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          SYMTAB    1   BR
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @[@]@@.     @B@@@@          END           BS
)@@G@@              .   ___IO         . COMPARE AGAINS*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@      BT
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC             BU
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          M$ADESCR                    .   @B@@@@      BV
)@@G@@    M$ACOMPILER                 .   @B@@@@          M$CPAR              BW
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO COMPILE THE MABX
)@@G@@CRO INTO THE SCRATCH    @F@@@@. FILE.  THE SECTOR ADDRESS IS IN A0 AND TBY
)@@G@@HE INTERNAL FILE NAME   @F@@@@. IS IN A1-A2.  RETURNS A0 POINTING TO THEBZ
)@@G@@ DEFINE ENTRY FOR THE   @^@@@@. FIRST MACRO FOUND.    @^@@@@. ADDRESS ISCA
)@@G@@ IN A0.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$COMPILER*         .   @E@@@@          S CB
)@@G@@        X11,CMPLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@@          S       CC
)@@G@@  STKPTR,CMPSIX     . SAVE INDEX REGISTER @F@@@@          S         A0,MCD
)@@G@@INPKT+5       . SET INPUT SECTOR ADDRESS  @E@@@@          DS        A1,MCE
)@@G@@INPKT         . SET INPUT FILE NAME @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CLOSE NORMAL TIDCF
)@@G@@E$ SCAN AND OPEN ON OUR PACKET.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          T$CLOSE CG
)@@G@@                    .   @D@@@@          L,U       A1,M$YBUF         . OUCH
)@@G@@R BUFFER    @D@@@@          T$OPENA   M$YPKT            . OPEN TIDE$    CI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. COMPUTE NEXT AVAILABLE SCRATCH FILE ADDRESS.  @[@@@@CJ
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          L         A0,M$SAVL         . GET AVAIL     @D@@@@CK
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,3              . ROUND UP TO   @D@@@@          SSCL
)@@G@@L       A0,2              . FOUR SECTOR   @C@@@@          LSSL      A0,2CM
)@@G@@              . BOUNDARY@D@@@@          S         A0,M$SAVL         . RECN
)@@G@@STORE IT    @F@@@@          S         A0,M$OUTPACKET+5  . AND SET OUTPUTCO
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. BUILD MACRO DEFINE ENTRY FOR THE STAND ACP
)@@G@@LONE PART OF THE MACRO. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          PGET      MCSIZE    CQ
)@@G@@        . GET BUFFER FOR MACRO DEF ENTRY  @E@@@@          JNZ       A5,CCR
)@@G@@MP999         . IF ERROR RETURN     @G@@@@          S         A1,CCMACR CS
)@@G@@        . SET CURRENTLY COMPILING MACRO   @E@@@@          S         A1,FCT
)@@G@@SMACR         . SET FIRST MACRO     @D@@@@          DL        A2,PFPELT CU
)@@G@@        . GET MACRO NAME@E@@@@          DS        A2,MCNAME,A1      . SECV
)@@G@@T NAME INTO PACKET@E@@@@          L         A0,M$OUTPACKET+5  . SET SECTCW
)@@G@@OR ADDRESS  @D@@@@          S         A0,MCADDR,A1      . INTO PACKET   CX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. BEGIN TO READ MACRO TEXT.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@      CY
)@@G@@    SDFIO     MINPKT,CMP090     . OPEN INPUT FROM MACRO     @E@@@@      CZ
)@@G@@    SDFOO     M$OUTPACKET,CMP090 . START MACRO OUTPUT @E@@@@          SZDA
)@@G@@        M$YLIN            . CLEAR MACRO LINE #  @F@@@@          SZ      DB
)@@G@@  MINFLG            . CLEAR ASCII MODE FLAG     @F@@@@          L       DC
)@@G@@  STKPTR,CMPSTK     . INITIALLY EMPTY STACK     @E@@@@          SZ      DD
)@@G@@  MSTYPE            . CLEAR STACKED TYPE  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. READ NEXT DE
)@@G@@IMAGE FROM MACRO AND CHECK IMAGE TYPE.    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP020    . DF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SDFI      MINPKT,CMP090,CMP070 . READ IMAGE @E@@@@      DG
)@@G@@    TN        MINPKT+10         . CONTROL IMAGE ?     @E@@@@          J DH
)@@G@@        CMP030            . NO - DATA IMAGE     @D@@@@          L,S1    DI
)@@G@@  A0,MINPKT+10      . GET IMAGE TYPE@G@@@@          L,S6      A1,MINPKT+DJ
)@@G@@10      . ASCII/FDATA SWITCH IF 042/050   @F@@@@          TE,U      A0,0DK
)@@G@@50            . ASCII/FD LABEL IMAGE ?    @F@@@@          TNE,U     A0,0DL
)@@G@@42            . ASCII/FD SWITCH IMAGE ?   @F@@@@          S         A1,MDM
)@@G@@INFLG         . YES - SET ASCII/FD FLAG   @D@@@@          J         CMP0DN
)@@G@@20            . NEXT LINE     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. DATA IMAGE@[@@@@.     DO
)@@G@@@]@@@@CMP030    . @E@@@@          TZ,S4     MINPKT+10         . CURRENT DP
)@@G@@CYCLE ?     @D@@@@          J         CMP020            . NO - IGNORE ITDQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A0,M$YLIN         . INCREMENT LINE #    @B@@@@DR
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,1              .   @B@@@@          S         A0,MDS
)@@G@@$YLIN         .   @F@@@@          SZ        M$YADR            . CLEAR STDT
)@@G@@RUCTURE ADDRESS   @D@@@@          L,S2      A0,MINPKT+10      . GET WORDDU
)@@G@@ COUNT@F@@@@          TZ        MINFLG            . IS INPUT IMAGE FIELDDV
)@@G@@ATA   @E@@@@          J         CMP040            . YES - SKIP TRANSLATEDW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CONVERT IMAGE TO ASCII@[@@@@.     @D@@@@          E$DX
)@@G@@OPENA   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT$    @D@@@@          LN,S2     A1,MDY
)@@G@@INPKT+10      . WORD COUNT    @B@@@@          L,U       A0,M$YBUF       DZ
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@          E$COPY                      . JEFF'S EDIT$ CAN DO EA
)@@G@@ANYTHING    @E@@@@          E$COLN                      . GET COLUMN NUMEB
)@@G@@BER   @D@@@@          A,U       A0,3              . GET WORD COUNT@B@@@@EC
)@@G@@          SSL       A0,2              .   @E@@@@          S         A0,CED
)@@G@@MPTMP         . SAVE WORD COUNT     @B@@@@          E$CLOSE             EE
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@          L         R1,CMPTMP         . GET WORD COUNTEF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A0,(1,M$EDITBUFFER) . @B@@@@          L       EG
)@@G@@  A1,(1,M$YBUF)     .   @E@@@@          BT        A1,0,*A0          . TREH
)@@G@@ANSFER TO JLINE   @D@@@@          L         A0,CMPTMP         . GET WORDEI
)@@G@@ COUNT@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. OPEN INPUT SCAN FOR COMMAND NAME  @[@@@@.     EJ
)@@G@@@]@@@@CMP040    . @H@@@@          S,S3      A0,M$MYPR         . SET LENGEK
)@@G@@TH IN CASE WE PRINT IMAGE     @G@@@@          AU,U      A0,2            EL
)@@G@@  . ADD TWO FOR BEGINNING WORDS     @B@@@@          SZ        M$OUTPACKEEM
)@@G@@T+10    .   @B@@@@          S,S2      A1,M$OUTPACKET+10 .   @E@@@@      EN
)@@G@@    ON        1                 . KLUGE FOR TIDE$ BUG @E@@@@          L EO
)@@G@@        A1,(040040040040) . EXTEND LAST WORD    @D@@@@          S       EP
)@@G@@  A1,M$YBUF,A0      . OF BLANKS     @F@@@@          L,U       A0,1,A0   EQ
)@@G@@        . GET CORRECT IMAGE LENGTH  @E@@@@          OFF       1         ER
)@@G@@        . KLUGE FOR TIDE$ BUG @E@@@@          L,U       A1,0,A0         ES
)@@G@@  . GET IMAGE LENGTH    @F@@@@          T$CLR                       . TEET
)@@G@@LL TIDE$ WATS HAPNIN    @B@@@@.         APRINT    M$MYPR            .   EU
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$XQTSCAN     . GET COMMAND NAME    @E@@@@EV
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,CMP060         . IF ERROR JUST COPY  @H@@@@      EW
)@@G@@    TSE       A0,M$TABLECMP,2,0,A2  . SEARCH COMPILER COMMAND TABLE     EX
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         CMP060            . JUST XFER     @E@@@@      EY
)@@G@@    L,H2      A0,1,A2           . GET ROUTINE NAME    @F@@@@          LMEZ
)@@G@@J       X11,0,A0          . CALL COMPILER ROUTINE     @E@@@@          JNFA
)@@G@@Z       A5,CMP999         . IF ERROR IN COMPILER@E@@@@          J       FB
)@@G@@  CMP020            . ELSE NEXT COMMAND   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. IMAGE IS JFC
)@@G@@UST PUT INTO FILE @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP060    . @G@@@@          LMJ     FD
)@@G@@  X11,M$CMPOUTPUT   . OUTPUT IMAGE TO SCRATCH FILE    @E@@@@          JNFE
)@@G@@Z       A5,CMP999         . IF ERROR RETURN     @D@@@@          J       FF
)@@G@@  CMP020            . NEXT IMAGE    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. END OF FILE ON CFG
)@@G@@OMPILE OF MACRO   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP070    . @B@@@@          SZ,S3   FH
)@@G@@  M$PRTAXW          .   @E@@@@          TNZ       MSTYPE            . ISFI
)@@G@@ STACK EMPTY ?    @E@@@@          J         CMP080            . YES - FIFJ
)@@G@@NISH UP     @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . BUILD ERROR MEFK
)@@G@@SSAGE @D@@@@          J         CMP999            . AND ERROR OFF @[@@@@FL
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. CHAIN IN ALL DEFINED MACROS @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP080    . FM
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A0,FSMACR         .   @B@@@@          L       FN
)@@G@@  A1,M$DEFMACRO     .   @B@@@@          S         A1,MCLINK,A0      .   FO
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A1,CCMACR         .   @B@@@@          S       FP
)@@G@@  A1,M$DEFMACRO     .   @]@@@@CMP100    . @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0FQ
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @D@@@@          J         CMP999    FR
)@@G@@        . AND RETURN    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. I/O ERRORS IN SDFS
)@@G@@FI/SDFO COME HERE @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP090    . @E@@@@          L       FT
)@@G@@  A5,CMPIOE         . COMPILER IO ERROR   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. XFER HERE FU
)@@G@@PCW IN A5   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMP999    . @C@@@@          S         A5,CFV
)@@G@@MPTMP         . SAVE PCW@D@@@@          SDFIC     MINPKT,XXXXXX     . CLFW
)@@G@@OSE INPUT   @]@@@@XXXXXX    . @D@@@@          SDFOC     M$OUTPACKET,YYYYFX
)@@G@@YY . CLOSE OUTPUT @]@@@@YYYYYY    . @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. POST SCRATCH FILFY
)@@G@@E SPACE USED.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          L         A0,M$OUTPACKET+5FZ
)@@G@@  . GET LAST SECTOR USED@E@@@@          A,U       A0,4              . ROGA
)@@G@@UND TO SECTOR BDRY@B@@@@          SSL       A0,2              .   @B@@@@GB
)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,2              .   @D@@@@          S         A0,MGC
)@@G@@$SAVL         . RESTORE IT    @E@@@@          T$CLOSE                   GD
)@@G@@  . CLOSE OUR TIDE$     @F@@@@          T$ROPN    M$TPKT            . REGE
)@@G@@OPEN ON NORMAL PACKET   @D@@@@          L         A5,CMPTMP         . GEGF
)@@G@@T ERROR FLAG@E@@@@          L         A0,FSMACR         . GET FIRST MACRGG
)@@G@@O     @F@@@@          L         STKPTR,CMPSIX     . RESTORE INDEX REGISTGH
)@@G@@ER    @D@@@@          L         X11,CMPLNK        . GET LINK HOME @C@@@@GI
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. DATAGJ
)@@G@@ FOR THE COMPILATION PROCESS  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          VARS          GK
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@CMPLNK    VAR       'CMPLNK',1      GL
)@@G@@  . RETURN ADDRESS FROM COMPILER    @E@@@@CMPSIX    VAR       'CMPSIX',1GM
)@@G@@        . SAVE FOR STKPTR     @D@@@@CMPTMP    VAR       'CMPTMP',1      GN
)@@G@@  . TEMP STORAGE  @D@@@@CCMACR    VAR       'CCMACR',1        . CURRENT GO
)@@G@@MACRO @D@@@@FSMACR    VAR       'FSMACR',1        . FIRST MACRO   @E@@@@GP
)@@G@@MINFLG    VAR       'MINFLG',1        . ASCII/FD INPUT FLAG @[@@@@.     GQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. TO AVOID GAZORCHING THE INPUT BUFFER M$MBUF WE USE A COMPILER   GR
)@@G@@@C@@@@. TEMPORARY BUFFER M$YBUF WHEN COMPILING MACROS.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@GS
)@@G@@M$MYPR    VAR       'M$MYPR',1 +(0100,M$YBUF) . PRINT INPUT BUFFER@E@@@@GT
)@@G@@M$YADR*   VAR       'M$YADR',1        . STRUCTURE ADDRESS   @F@@@@M$YLINGU
)@@G@@*   VAR       'M$YLIN',1        . LINE NUMBER WITHIN MACRO  @D@#@@M$YBUFGV
)@@G@@*   VAR       'M$YBUF',20       . INPUT BUFFER  @G@@@#M$YBUF*   VAR     GW
)@@G@@  'M$YBUF',22       . 20 +2 (BLANK KLUGE AND FD 84)   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@GX
)@@G@@. TIDE$ PACKET FOR SCANNING LINES IN MACRO.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@M$YPKTGY
)@@G@@    T$PKTGN   22,M$YBUF         ; TIDE$ PACKET  @E@@@@          'MSK',+(GZ
)@@G@@T$MASKR 'SP' *'$' *''''  *'.' *' ' *67) ; @B@@@@          'BLK',0 'DAL',HA
)@@G@@0 'NLG',12  ;     @B@@@@          'DL1',072 'DL2',072         ;   @C@@@@HB
)@@G@@          'ASC',1 'ASO',0 'FDA',M$TIDETABLE ;   @B@@@@          'MK1',+(HC
)@@G@@T$MASKR 'LET' '$')  .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MINPKT    SDFPKT    '',R$ 4,M$HD
)@@G@@MIB1,M$MIB2 20,M$YBUF   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@M$MIB1    VAR       'M$MIB1',4HE
)@@G@@*28       . @B@@@@M$MIB2    VAR       'M$MIB2',4*28       . @B@@@@M$MOB1HF
)@@G@@*   VAR       'M$MOB1',4*28       . @B@@@@M$MOB2*   VAR       'M$MOB2',4HG
)@@G@@*28       . @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          LITS      .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@HH
)@@G@@CMPSTK    +         2,-2*(STKMAX-2)   . EMPTY STACK   @B@@@@CMPIOE    PCHI
)@@G@@M       1                 .   @D@@@@          'IO ERROR READING MACRO FRHJ
)@@G@@OM SOURCE FILE.' .@B@@@@CMNAME    PCM       1                 .   @B@@@@HK
)@@G@@          'ILLEGAL MACRO NAME.'       .   @B@@@@M$CPSOVR* PCM       1   HL
)@@G@@              .   @C@@@@          'MACRO COMPILER STACK OVERFLOW.' .    HM
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ENDPCM                      .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     HN
)@@G@@@B@@@@          INSTRS                      .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPHO
)@@G@@ILE THE 'MACRO' COMMAND.  THE STACK MUST AT THIS POINT BE   @F@@@@. TYPEHP
)@@G@@ MACRO, BECAUSE THE INITIAL PUSH WAS DONE WHEN SDF INPUT    @F@@@@. WAS HQ
)@@G@@OPENED.  CREATE A MACRO DEF ENTRY AND CHAIN IT INTO THE     @B@@@@. QUEUHR
)@@G@@E POINTED TO BY CCMACR AND FSMACR.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$CMPMACRO*       HS
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@          S         X11,CMLINK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS HT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TNZ       MSTYPE            . IS STACK EMPTY ?    @D@@@@HU
)@@G@@          J         CMA010            . YES - SKIP    @E@@@@          LMHV
)@@G@@J       X11,M$ERRMSGCMP   . GEN ERROR MESSAGE   @D@@@@          J       HW
)@@G@@  CMA999            . AND ERROR     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@CMA010    . @E@@@@HX
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,M$SCANPRIM    . SCAN FOR MACRO NAME @C@@@@      HY
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,CMA999         . OOPS    @B@@@@          L         A5,CHZ
)@@G@@MNAME         .   @D@@@@          TE,U      A0,MODNAM         . NAME-LABIA
)@@G@@EL ?  @C@@@@          J         CMA999            . OOPS    @D@@@@      IB
)@@G@@    SDFOC     M$OUTPACKET,CMP090 . CLOSE OUTPUT @E@@@@          PGET    IC
)@@G@@  MCSIZE            . GET MACRO BUFFER    @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,CID
)@@G@@MA999         . ERROR   @E@@@@          L         A0,CSADDR         . GEIE
)@@G@@T MACRO NAME AGAIN@B@@@@          DL        A2,0,A0           .   @D@@@@IF
)@@G@@          DS        A2,MCNAME,A1      . SET MACRO NAME@H@@@^          L IG
)@@G@@        A0,M$OUTPACKET+5  . LAST ADDRESS USED BY PREVIOUS MACRO   @D@@@^IH
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,3              . ROUND UP TO   @D@@@^          SSII
)@@G@@L       A0,2              . FOUR SECTOR   @C@@@^          LSSL      A0,2IJ
)@@G@@              . BOUNDARY@F@@@^          S         A0,M$OUTPACKET+5  . SEIK
)@@G@@T START ADDRESS FOR SDFO@E@^@@          L         A0,M$OUTPACKET+5  . GEIL
)@@G@@T SECTOR ADDRESS  @B@@@@          S         A0,MCADDR,A1      .   @D@@@@IM
)@@G@@          L         A0,CCMACR         . CHAIN IT IN   @B@@@@          S IN
)@@G@@        A0,MCLINK,A1      .   @G@@@@          S         A1,CCMACR       IO
)@@G@@  . SET CURRENT COMPILING MACRO     @E@@@@          SDFOO     M$OUTPACKEIP
)@@G@@T,CMP090 . OPEN OUTPUT AGAIN  @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0            IQ
)@@G@@  . CLEAR ERROR FLAG    @]@@@@CMA999    . @B@@@@          L         X11,IR
)@@G@@CMLINK        .   @D@@@@          J         0,X11             . NORMAL RIS
)@@G@@ETURN @[@@@@.     @C@@@@CMLINK    VAR       'CMLINK',1        . LINK    IT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THESE ROUTINES ARE AVAILABLE TO THE MACRO COMPILERS.IU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$CMPOUTPUT*        .   @E@@@@          S         X11,IV
)@@G@@MYLINK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @D@@@@          SDFO      M$OUTPACKEIW
)@@G@@T,CMP090 . OUTPUT IMAGE @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLIX
)@@G@@EAR ERROR FLAG    @B@@@@          L         X11,MYLINK        .   @C@@@@IY
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@M$CMPUIZ
)@@G@@PDATE*        .   @E@@@@          S         X11,MYLINK        . SAVE RETJA
)@@G@@URN ADDRESS @F@@@@          SDFUPD    M$OUTPACKET,CMP090 . UPDATE IMAGE JB
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @E@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR FLJC
)@@G@@AG    @B@@@@          L         X11,MYLINK        .   @C@@@@          J JD
)@@G@@        0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MYLINK    VAR     JE
)@@G@@  'MYLINK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          SYMTAB  JF
)@@G@@  1                 .   @B@@@@          END                         .   JG
