)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   VX
)@@G@@___           .   @D@@@*          'CPMD DOES NOT SUPPORT THIS MACHINE TYVY
)@@G@@PE.' .@B@@@*ERRTRA*   PC*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         CALL DGEVZ
)@@G@@T(FILENAME,BUFFERS,ASTAT,MSTAT)     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THIS SUBWA
)@@G@@ROUTINE DETERMINES THE INITIAL RESERVE REQUIRED TO    @F@@@@.         DOWB
)@@G@@ A DGET$ FUNCTION OF THE ER MSCON$.  THEN A TEMPORARY @G@@@@.         FIWC
)@@G@@LE IS ASSIGNED WITH THAT INITIAL RESERVE.  IF THE ASSIGN    @F@@@@.     WD
)@@G@@    STATUS IS POSITIVE AND IF THE ASSIGN STATUS BITS ARE    @F@@@@.     WE
)@@G@@    ACCEPTABLE TO THE CALLER, A DGET$ FUNCTION IS PERFORMED.@[@@@@.     WF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         FILENAME IS AN ARRAY DIMENSIONED AT 2 WHICH CONTAINS THEWG
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         NAME OF THE FILE TO ASSIGN AND USE FOR THE DGET$. @[@@@@WH
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         BUFFERS IS AN ARRAY DIMENSIONED AT 3590 WHICH WILLWI
)@@G@@ BE USED    @ @@@@.         BY THIS SUBROUTINE. @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     WJ
)@@G@@    ASTAT IS A VARIABLE SET BY THE CALLER TO INDICATE WHICH @F@@@@.     WK
)@@G@@    ASSIGN STATUS BITS WILL CAUSE THE DGET$ TO BE OMITTED.  @G@@@@.     WL
)@@G@@    IF ASTAT IS SET TO 0, THE DGET$ WILL BE DONE IF THE ASSIGN    @G@@@@WM
)@@G@@.         STATUS IS POSITIVE.  IF ASTAT IS SET TO 100000000000 (OCTAL), WN
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE DGET$ WILL NOT BE DONE IF THE FILE WAS ALREADY ASSIGWO
)@@G@@NED.  @E@@@@.         ON EXIT, ASTAT WILL BE SET TO THE ASSIGN STATUS.  WP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         MSTAT IS A VARIABLE WHICH IS SET TO 0 IF THEWQ
)@@G@@ DGET$ IS NOT     @G@@@@.         DONE OR TO THE STATUS (A0) RETURNED FRWR
)@@G@@OM MSCON$ IF THE DGET$  @^@@@@.         WAS DONE.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@WS
)@@G@@.         CALL SDGET(FILENAME,BUFFERS,ASTAT,MSTAT)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WT
)@@G@@.         THIS SUBROUTINE PERFORMS EXACTLY AS DGET DOES, EXCEPT THAT    WU
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE RESULTING FILE IS CREATED BY THE UOM FUNCTION OF MSCWV
)@@G@@ON$,  @ @@@@.         SDGET$ (CODE 7).    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         CAWW
)@@G@@LL DGETP(PACKID,EQUIP,FILENAME,ASTAT,MSTAT)     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     WX
)@@G@@    THE SUBROUTINE PERFORMS A DGETP$ REQUEST ON THE PACKID NAMED  @G@@@@WY
)@@G@@.         MOUNTING THAT PACK ON THE EQUIPMENT TYPE PROVIDED.  THE FILE  WZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         IS ASIGNED ON THE PACK AS WELL. @H@@@@.         IN ALL OXA
)@@G@@THER RESPECTS, THE SUBROUTINE PERFORMS EXACTLY AS DGET DOES.@[@@@@.     XB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          AXR$,1                      .   @#@#@@      XC
)@@G@@    IOPROC  @#@@@#          COMMON  @G@@@@DGET$S    EQU       010       XD
)@@G@@        . OLD SINGLE BUFFERED VERSION     @E@@@@SDGET$    EQU       007 XE
)@@G@@              . BET MAIN ITEMS ONLY @[@@@@.     @B@@@@$(1)              XF
)@@G@@                    .   @E@@@@DGETP*                                . ENXG
)@@G@@TRY TO DO A DGETP$@G@@@@          SZ        A3                . CLEAR FOXH
)@@G@@R FORTRAN COMPATABILITY @E@@@@          LA        A4,*1,X11         . GEXI
)@@G@@T EQUIP TYPE LJSF @G@@@@          LA        A1,*0,X11         . GET PACKXJ
)@@G@@ID FOR FILE AND DGETP$  @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,DGETP$         . FUXK
)@@G@@NCTION FOR REM PACK GET @H@@@@          AX,U      X11,2             . BUXL
)@@G@@MP X11 TO LOOK LIKE NORMAL DGET     @^@@@@          LR,U      R1,5@D@@@@XM
)@@G@@EQUIPL    AND,U     A4,077            . ISOLATE A CHAR@F@@@@          TEXN
)@@G@@,U      A5,' '            . DONE IF ITS NOT BLANK     @F@@@@          J XO
)@@G@@        GETD1             . START REGULAR PROCESSING  @D@@@@          SSXP
)@@G@@C       A4,6              . GET A NEW CHAR@G@@@@          JGD       R1,EXQ
)@@G@@QUIPL         . LOOP BACK IF WE HAVE ANY LEFT   @G@@@@          J       XR
)@@G@@  GETD1             . ELSE CONTINUE WITH BLANK EQUIP  @E@@@@SDGET*    LAXS
)@@G@@,U      A0,SDGET$         . SHORT DGET FUNCTION @C@@@@          J       XT
)@@G@@  GETD              . CONTINUE@E@@@@DGET*     LA,U      A0,DGET$        XU
)@@G@@  . STOCK DGET FUNCTION @E@@@@GETD      LA        A1,('  .   ')     . TOXV
)@@G@@ TERM @ASG IMAGE  @F@@@@          LA        A4,('     F')     . EQUIP TYXW
)@@G@@PE TO @ASG ON     @F@@@@          SZ        A3                . FOR FORTXX
)@@G@@RAN COMPATABILITY @G@@@@GETD1     SA        A1,PACKID         . SET A PAXY
)@@G@@CKID OR TERM @ASG IMAGE @G@@@@          SA        A4,EQUIP          . SEXZ
)@@G@@T THE SCRATCH FILE EQUIP TYPE @E@@@@          DL        A4,*0,X11       YA
)@@G@@  . $P GET FILE NAME    @G@@@@          L         R1,*2,X11         . $PYB
)@@G@@ GET UNACCEPTABLE ASG BITS    @F@@@@          L,U       A3,*1,X11       YC
)@@G@@  . $P GET ADDRESS OF BUFFER  @F@@@@          SZ        R3              YD
)@@G@@  . $P INDICATE DGET$ NOT DONE@F@@@@          DS        A4,1,A3         YE
)@@G@@  . SET FILE NAME IN PACKET   @E@@@@          S         A0,0,A3         YF
)@@G@@  . $P PUT IT IN PACKET @F@@@@          L,U       A2,5,A3           . $PYG
)@@G@@ GET BUFFER ADDRESSES   @F@@@@          LA        A4,PACKID         . GEYH
)@@G@@T THE REM DISK PACKID   @B@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1792,A2        .   YI
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SA        A4,5,A3           . STORE IT IN THE PACKET    YJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          S         A2,4,A3           . $P PUT THEM IN PACKET     YK
)@@G@@@H@@@@          SX        A2,3,A3           . FOR SDGET$, THEY GO IN ANOYL
)@@G@@THER PLACE  @G@@@@          TNE,U     A0,SDGET$         . ARE WE DOING AYM
)@@G@@ SHORT DGET ?     @I@@@@          J         DOASG             . YES, WE YN
)@@G@@DON'T NEED TO GET DIRECTORY SIZE    @G@@@@          SZ        3,A3      YO
)@@G@@        . MAKE SURE TRACK REQUIRED CLEAR  @B@@@@GETDSZ    L,U       A0,0YP
)@@G@@,A3           .   @E@@@@          DL        A4,1,A3           . SAVE THEYQ
)@@G@@ FILE NAME  @F@@@@          SZ        1,A3              . CLEAR FILE NAMYR
)@@G@@E IN PACKET @F@@@@          SZ        2,A3              . SO WE DON'T DOYS
)@@G@@ DGET NOW   @D@@@@          ER        MSCON$            . $P ER MSCON$  YT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DS        A4,1,A3           . RESTORE FILE NAME   @F@@@@YU
)@@G@@                                      . GET INITIAL RESERVE NEEDED@F@@@@YV
)@@G@@          SSL       A0,30             . $P GET EXEC INDICATOR     @G@@@@YW
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,040            . IS THIS LEVEL 33 OR HIGHER ?    YX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         $+3               . YES, FORGET OTHER TEST    YY
)@@G@@@G@@@@          TLE,U     A0,043            . $T EXEC ALLOW DOUBLE BUFFEYZ
)@@G@@RS?   @E@@@@          J         SINGLE            . $A YES NO,SINGLE    ZA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A0,3,A3           . $P GET INITIAL RESERVE    ZB
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L         A1,A0             .   @B@@@@          SSL     ZC
)@@G@@  A1,5              .   @B@@@@          TLE,U     A1,6              .   ZD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          L,U       A1,6              .   @F@@@@          A       ZE
)@@G@@  A0,A1             . $P ADD SOME EXTRA TRACKS  @E@@@@          L,U     ZF
)@@G@@  A2,5              . $P CONVERT TO OCTAL @B@@@@LOOP      DSL       A0,3ZG
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          SSL       A1,3              .   @B@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          JGD       A2,LOOP           .   @B@@@@          A         A1,(ZI
)@@G@@'000000')     .   @E@@@@          S         A1,INRES          . $P PUT IZJ
)@@G@@N ASG IMAGE @F@@@@DOASG     DL        A0,1,A3           . $P RIGHT ADJUSZK
)@@G@@T FILE NAME @B@@@@          L,U       A4,11             .   @[@@@@NOP   ZL
)@@G@@@B@@@@NEXTCH    AND,U     A1,077            .   @B@@@@          TE,U    ZM
)@@G@@  A2,' '            .   @B@@@@          J         RIGHT             .   ZN
)@@G@@@B@@@@          DSC       A0,6              .   @B@@@@          JGD     ZO
)@@G@@  A4,NEXTCH         .   @G@@@@RIGHT     DS        A0,FNAME          . $PZP
)@@G@@ PUT FILE NAME IN ASG IMAGE   @B@@@@ASGIT     L,U       A0,ASG          ZQ
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          ER        CSF$              .   @F@@@@          L ZR
)@@G@@        R2,A0             . $P SAVE ASSIGN STATUS     @F@@@@          JNZS
)@@G@@        A0,EXIT           . $T ASSIGN SUCCESSFUL?     @D@@@@            ZT
)@@G@@                          . $A YES NO,EXIT@G@@@@          AND       A0,RZU
)@@G@@1             . $P GET UNACCEPTABLE ASG BITS    @G@@@@          JZ      ZV
)@@G@@  A1,GETDIR         . IF @ASG STAT NOT OK, GET DIR    @E@@@@          DLZW
)@@G@@        A1,1,A3           . GET THE FILE NAME   @G@@@@          LA      ZX
)@@G@@  A0,4,A3           . BUILD PACKET WHERE MSCON BUF IS @F@@@@          DSZY
)@@G@@        A1,IONAME         . SET FILE NAME IN PACKET   @D@@@@          LAZZ
)@@G@@,U      A1,IODADD+1       . ADDR OF BUFFER@E@@@@          LA,U      A2,RAA
)@@G@@$             . WE WILL DO A READ   @D@@@@          LXI,U     A1,3      AB
)@@G@@        . READ 3 WORDS  @F@@@@          SZ        IODADD            . STAC
)@@G@@ARTING AT SECTOR ZERO   @F@@@@          SA        A2,IOFUNC         . SEAD
)@@G@@T THE READ FUNCTION     @E@@@@          SA        A1,IOACW          . ANAE
)@@G@@D THE ACCESS WORD @E@@@@          ER        IOW$              . WAIT FORAF
)@@G@@ THE I/O    @D@@@@          TZ        IOSTAT            . READ GO OK ?  AG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         GETDIR            . HE GETS WHAT HE ASKED FOR AH
)@@G@@@C@@@@          LA,U      A2,1              . A FLAG  @F@@@@          TZAI
)@@G@@        1,A1              . IS THIS AN SDGET$ FILE ?  @H@@@@          LAAJ
)@@G@@,U      A2,0              . NO, IT HAS NON ZERO LOOK UP TAB LEN   @D@@@@AK
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,SDGET$         . FOR TESTING   @D@@@@          LAAL
)@@G@@,U      A1,1              . ANOTHER FLAG  @G@@@@          TE        A0,0AM
)@@G@@,A3           . DO WE WANT TO DO AN SDGET$ ?    @E@@@@          LA,U    AN
)@@G@@  A1,0              . NO, CLEAR THE FLAG  @G@@@@          TNE,U     A1,0AO
)@@G@@,A2           . ARE BOTH DGET$ OR BOTH SDGET$ ? @F@@@@          J       AP
)@@G@@  EXIT              . YES, WE GOT WHAT WE WANT  @G@@@@          LA      AQ
)@@G@@  A4,('@FREE ')     . WE WILL CHANGE @ASG,T TO @FREE  @D@@@@          LAAR
)@@G@@        A5,ASG            . SAVE @ASG,T   @F@@@@          LA,U      A2,'AS
)@@G@@ . '          . TO STOP CSI1 ON @FREE     @F@@@@          SA        A4,AAT
)@@G@@SG            . SET TO GET RID OF FILE    @D@@@@          LA        A4,FAU
)@@G@@NAME+2        . SAVE ',F/   ' @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,ASG          AV
)@@G@@  . POINT AT THE CSF IMAGE    @F@@@@          SA,H1     A2,FNAME+2      AW
)@@G@@  . PUT BLANK PERIOD BLANK IN @F@@@@          ER        CSF$            AX
)@@G@@  . START WITH A NEW FILE     @E@@@@          SA        A4,FNAME+2      AY
)@@G@@  . RESTORE ',F/   '    @D@@@@          SA        A5,ASG            . REAZ
)@@G@@STORE @ASG,T@H@@@@          JNZ       A1,ASGIT          . IF SDGET$ WANTBA
)@@G@@ED, NO SIZE COMPUTATION @F@@@@          J         GETDSZ            . NEBB
)@@G@@ED INITIAL RES FOR DGET$@B@@@@GETDIR    L,U       A0,0,A3           .   BC
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ER        MSCON$            . $P ER MSCON$ .@E@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    L         R3,A0             . $P SAVE DGET$ STATUS@B@@@@EXIT        BE
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@@          SZ        A3              BF
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@          S         R2,*2,X11         . $P RETURN ASSIGN STABG
)@@G@@TUS   @F@@@@          S         R3,*3,X11         . $P RETURN DGET STATUBH
)@@G@@S     @B@@@@          J         5,X11             . $E@F@@@@SINGLE    L,BI
)@@G@@U       A0,DGET$S         . $P GET SINGLE DGET$ CODE  @E@@@@          S BJ
)@@G@@        A0,0,A3           . $P PUT IN PACKET    @B@@@@          J       BK
)@@G@@  DOASG             .   @B@@@@$(0)                                  .   BL
)@@G@@@^@@@@ASG       '@ASG,T '     @^@@@@FNAME     +0D       .   @^@@@@      BM
)@@G@@    ',      '     @E@@@@EQUIP     +         0                 . FILL IN BN
)@@G@@AT RUN TIME @#@@@@          '/     '@#@]@@INRES     '     1'@#@@@]INRES BO
)@@G@@    '    20'@^@[@@          '//1000,'     @^@@@[          '//4000,'     BP
)@@G@@@^@@@@PACKID    '       . '   @#@@@@          END     ___@@@    DS      BQ
)@@G@@  A4,1,A3           . RESTORE FILE NAME   @F@@@@                        BR
)@@G@@              . GET INITIAL RESERVE NEEDED@F@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@F@@@UDEBUG BS
)@@G@@    EQU       0                 . ON FOR ERROR DETECTING    @H@@@USDGET BT
)@@G@@    EQU       1                 . NON-ZERO IF YOUR MSCON$ HAS SDGET$    BU
)@@G@@@F@V@UPRE33     EQU       1                 . ON IF YOU WANT TO USE     BV
)@@G@@@F@@@VPRE33     EQU       0                 . ON IF YOU WANT TO USE     BW
)@@G@@@F@@@U                                      . PRE LEVEL 33 DIRECTORIES  BX
)@@G@@@G@@@VPRE34     EQU       1                 . ON IF PRE LEVEL 34 MCT POSBY
)@@G@@SIBLE @E@@@UPOST32    EQU       1                 . ON FOR POST LEVEL 32BZ
)@@G@@@G@@@VPOST33    EQU       1                 . ON TO ACCEPT POST 33 MCT FCA
)@@G@@ORMAT @[@@@U.     @E@@@UBOTH      EQU       PRE33**POST32     . SET FOR CB
)@@G@@BOTH DISIRED@[@@@U.     @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:     LMJ  X11,FCC
)@@G@@DINTL @[@@@U.     @H@@@U.         ENTRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF 56 WORD FDSUCD
)@@G@@BS BUFFER TO BE INITIALIZED   @E@@@U.                   0-1,A3 - INTERNACE
)@@G@@L NAME OF DGET$ FILE    @G@@@U.                   7,A3 - ADDRESS OF MCT CF
)@@G@@BUFFER (1792 WORDS).  IF FIRST@G@@@U.                        WORD OF BUFCG
)@@G@@FER IS 'SYMMCT', FDINTL ASSUMES MCT @H@@@U.                        IS INCH
)@@G@@ BUFFER.  OTHERWISE, FDINTL PUTS MCT IN BUFFER. @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.     CI
)@@G@@    EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @F@@@U.                   A1 - DEFINED ONLCJ
)@@G@@Y IF POST32 AND PRE33 EQUAL 1 @D@@@U.                        0 IF A PRE CK
)@@G@@LEVEL 33 DIRECTORY@E@@@U.                        1 IF A POST LEVEL 32 DICL
)@@G@@RECTORY     @D@@@U.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER     CM
)@@G@@@G@@@U.                   9,A3 - THE NUMBER OF WORDS REQUIRED IN THE BUFCN
)@@G@@FER   @G@@@U.                        THAT WILL BE USED TO HOLD INFORMATICO
)@@G@@ON ABOUT    @H@@@U.                        EACH DIRECTORY TRACK.  THE BUCP
)@@G@@FFER WILL BE INITIALIZED@D@@@U.                        BY FDRDAS AND USECQ
)@@G@@D BY FDNDI. @E@@@U.                   10-12,A3 - FIRST 3 WORDS OF DGET$ CR
)@@G@@FILE  @G@@@U.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TOCS
)@@G@@ STATUS     @[@@@U.     @H@@@U.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    . CT
)@@G@@   .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:   CU
)@@G@@  LMJ  X11,FDRDAS @[@@@U.     @E@@@U.         ENTRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF CV
)@@G@@56 WORD FDSUBS BUFFER   @C@@@U.                   7,A3 - ADDRESS OF MCT CW
)@@G@@BUFFER@F@@@U.                   8,A3 - ADDRESS OF BUFFER TO HOLD INFORMACX
)@@G@@TION  @H@@@U.                        ABOUT DIRECTORY TRACKS.  NUMBER OF CY
)@@G@@WORDS REQUIRED    @F@@@U.                        IN BUFFER WAS STORED INCZ
)@@G@@ 9,A3 BY FDINTL.  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     DA
)@@G@@@D@@@U.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER     @G@@@U.     DB
)@@G@@              A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TO STATUS     @H@@@UDC
)@@G@@.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    . DD
)@@G@@   .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:     LMJ  X11,FDINITS@[@@@U.     DE
)@@G@@@H@@@U.         ENTRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF WORK AREA TO BE INITIALIZED BYDF
)@@G@@ FDINITS.   @H@@@U.                        FIRST TWO WORDS OF WORK AREA DG
)@@G@@MUST CONTAIN INTERNAL   @H@@@U.                        NAME OF A FILE CRDH
)@@G@@EATED BY SDGET$ FUNCTION OF MSCON$. @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         EXIT:   DI
)@@G@@  A0 - STATUS     @D@@@U.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFEDJ
)@@G@@R     @G@@@U.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TODK
)@@G@@ STATUS     @[@@@U.     @H@@@U.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    . DL
)@@G@@   .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:   DM
)@@G@@  LMJ  X11,FDNDI  @[@@@U.     @I@@@U.         ENTRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF DN
)@@G@@FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.     DO
)@@G@@    EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @D@@@U.                   A1 - ADDRESS OF DP
)@@G@@TRACK DESCRIPTOR  @C@@@U.                   A2 - CORE ADDRESS OF SECTOR DQ
)@@G@@@D@@@U.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER     @G@@@U.     DR
)@@G@@              A4 - ABSOLUTE ADDRESS OF SECTOR IN FILE DIRECTORY   @G@@@UDS
)@@G@@.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TO STATUS     DT
)@@G@@@[@@@U.     @[@@@U.     @H@@@U.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    . DU
)@@G@@   .    .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:   DV
)@@G@@  LMJ  X11,FDABR  @[@@@U.     @I@@@U.         ENTRY:    A3 - ADDRESS OF DW
)@@G@@FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     @F@@@U.                 DX
)@@G@@  A4 - ABSOLUTE ADDRESS OF DIRECTORY SECTOR     @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.     DY
)@@G@@    EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @D@@@U.                   A1 - ADDRESS OF DZ
)@@G@@TRACK DESCRIPTOR  @B@@@U.                   A2 - ADDRESS OF SECTOR@D@@@UEA
)@@G@@.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER     @G@@@U.           EB
)@@G@@        A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TO STATUS     @[@@@U.     EC
)@@G@@@H@@@U.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .ED
)@@G@@    .    .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:     LMJ  X11,FDLUT  @[@@@UEE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@U.         ENTRY:    A0,A1 - QUALIFIER     @I@@@U.           EF
)@@G@@        A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FDINIT, FDRDAS     EG
)@@G@@@B@@@U.                   A4,A5 - FILE NAME     @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.     EH
)@@G@@    EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @A@@@U.                   A4 - LUT ENTRY  EI
)@@G@@@G@@@U.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORRESPONDING TO STATUEJ
)@@G@@S     @[@@@U.     @H@@@U.    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .    .  EK
)@@G@@  .    .    .    .    .    .  @[@@@U.     @A@@@U.         CALL:     LMJ EL
)@@G@@ X11,FDHASH @[@@@U.     @B@@@U.         ENTRY:    A0,A1 - QUALIFIER     EM
)@@G@@@I@@@U.                   A3 - ADDRESS OF FDSUBS BUFFER INITIALIZED BY FEN
)@@G@@DINIT, FDRDAS     @B@@@U.                   A4,A5 - FILE NAME     @[@@@UEO
)@@G@@.     @A@@@U.         EXIT:     A0 - STATUS     @A@@@U.                 EP
)@@G@@  A1 - HASH INDEX @G@@@U.                   A5 - PRINT CONTROL WORD CORREQ
)@@G@@ESPONDING TO STATUS     @[@@@U.     @E@@@U. THE STATUS CODES RETURNED INER
)@@G@@ A0 INDICATE THE FOLLOWING    @[@@@U.     @C@@@U.          0      REQUESES
)@@G@@T COMPLETED NORMALLY    @E@@@U.          1      ALL SECTORS HAVE BEEN REET
)@@G@@TURNED BY FDNDI   @F@@@U.          2      FDINIT I/O ERROR READING FIRSTEU
)@@G@@ 3 WORDS OF FILE  @G@@@U.          3      FDINIT I/O ERROR READING A DIREV
)@@G@@ECTORY ALLOCATION SECTOR@F@@@U.          4      MORE DIRECTORY TRACKS THEW
)@@G@@AN ROUTINE CAN HANDLE. ;@F@@@U.                    REASSEMBLE ROUTINE WIEX
)@@G@@TH MAXTRK SET HIGHER.   @B@@@U.          5      ERROR OBTAINING MCT     EY
)@@G@@@E@@@U.          6      ERROR CALCULATING UNIT OR EQUIPMENT TYPE  @E@@@UEZ
)@@G@@.          7      FDNDI I/O ERROR READING A DIRECTORY TRACK @F@@@U.     FA
)@@G@@     8      SECTOR ON DIRECTORY TRACK, BUT NOT ALLOCATED    @F@@@U.     FB
)@@G@@     9      ADDRESS IS ON WAD UNIT, BUT NOT A SECTOR BOUNDRY@E@@@U.     FC
)@@G@@     10     FDABR ADDRESS IS NOT ON DIRECTORY TRACK   @C@@@U.          1FD
)@@G@@1     FDABR I/O ERROR READING SECTOR@D@@@U.          12     I/O ERROR REFE
)@@G@@ADING LOOK-UP TABLE     @D@@@U.          13     FUNCTION NOT ALLOWED FORFF
)@@G@@ SDGET$ FILE@E@@@U.          14     DIRECTORY FILE NOT PROPERLY FORMATTEFG

)@@G@@S IN UNIT TABLE   @[@@@U.     @E@@@U.         THERE ARE MAXTRK/256 ONE WIS
)@@G@@ORD ENTRIES PER UNIT    @G@@@U.         THESE MAKE UP A UNIT ENTRY, AND IT
)@@G@@THERE IS ONE UNIT ENTRY PER   @E@@@U.         UNIT IN THE CONFIGURATION IU
)@@G@@AS DESCRIBED BY THE MCT.@[@@@U.     @G@@@U.         EACH ONE WORD ENTRY IV
)@@G@@POINTS TO A SET OF DIRECTORY TRACK ENTRIES@G@@@U.         THE FIRST 4 BIIW
)@@G@@TS OF THE DAS RELATIVE ADDRESS IS CONTAINED     @F@@@U.         IN THE OIX
)@@G@@NE WORD UNIT TABLE ENTRY.  THE OTHER EIGHT BITS @C@@@U.         ARE IN TIY
)@@G@@HE DIRECTORY TRACK ENTRY.     @[@@@U.     @E@@@U.         A LOOK-UP OF AIZ
)@@G@@ PARTICULAR ADDRESS CONSISTS OF     @F@@@U.         INDEXING INTO THE TAJA
)@@G@@BLE BASED ON THE LDAT INDEX TIMES   @E@@@U.         THE NUMBER OF ENTRIEJB
)@@G@@S PER UNIT (MAXTRK/256).  THIS@F@@@U.         GIVES THE BASE ADDRESS OF JC
)@@G@@THE TABLE AREA FOR THAT UNIT. @F@@@U.         THE FIRST FOUR BITS OF THEJD
)@@G@@ DAS RELATIVE ADDRESS IS ADDED@F@@@U.         TO THAT TO GIVE THE ADDRESJE
)@@G@@S OF THE ONE WORD ENTRY OF    @G@@@U.         INTEREST.  THE SET OF DIREJF
)@@G@@CTORY TRACK ENTRIES POINTED TO BY   @F@@@U.         THAT UNIT ENTRY IS TJG
)@@G@@HEN SEARCHED FOR THE MATCHING LOWER @D@@@U.         EIGHT BITS OF THE DAJH
)@@G@@S RELATIVE ADDRESS.     @[@@@U.     @[@@@U.     @E@@@UUNITENT   EQUF    JI
)@@G@@  0                 . THE WHOLE ENTRY     @E@@@ULDAT      EQUF      0,0,JJ

)@@G@@        . FIRST FOUR BITS OF DAS REL ADDR @F@@@UUNTDT     EQUF      0,0,JL
)@@G@@H2            . POINTS TO DT ENTRY SET    @[@@@U.     @G@@@U.         THJM

)@@G@@        . GET THE FIRST DESCRIPTOR  @E@@@V          TEP,U     A1,1*/9   OS

)@@G@@1             . RETURN  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. THIS SUBROUTINE SETS UP FOR RD
)@@G@@THE BEGINNING OF A LOOP @E@@@[. A0 CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF WORDS PER LINERE
)@@G@@ TO BE PRINTED    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[. CALLED    @A@@@[.       L,U A0,<WORF

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PROCEDURE TO GENERATE CALLS TO TRACING RBG
)@@G@@OUTINE TRACE$.    @]@@@@. CALLED:   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         TRACE   BH
)@@G@@  'MESSAGE'         .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WHERE MESSAGE IS UP TO 12 CHBI
)@@G@@ARACTERS AND WILL BE LEFT JUSTIFIED @C@@@@. BY THIS PROCEDURE.  THE CODEBJ
)@@G@@ GENERATED IS:    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SLJ       TRACE$          BK
)@@G@@  . CALL ROUTINE  @E@@@@.         'MESSAGE'                   . GENERATEBL
)@@G@@ MESSAGE    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC                        .   BM
)@@G@@@B@@@@TRACE*    NAME                        .   @D@@@@MSG(0)    EQU     BN
)@@G@@  P(1,1)++0D        . GET MESSAGE   @F@@@@I DO 11 , DO (MSG(0)*/-66)=0 ,BO
)@@G@@MSG(0) EQU (MSG(0)*/6)++05 . LJSF   @B@@@@          SLJ       TRACE$    BP
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         MSG(0)            .   @B@@@@      BQ
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURE TO GENBR
)@@G@@ERATE CALLS TO SNAP ROUTINE TSNAP$. @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. CALLED:   @[@@@@BS
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.         TSNAP     'SNAPID',PLACE    .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@BT
)@@G@@. WHERE SNAPID IS UP TO 6 CHARACTERS AND WILL BE LEFT JUSTIFIED   @F@@@@BU
)@@G@@. BY THIS PROCEDURE.  PLACE IS AN ARBITRARY EQUF AND AS SUCH MAY  @E@@@@BV
)@@G@@. BE ANY REGISTER, ANY CORE LOCATION, OR ANY PARTIAL WORD.  @[@@@@.     BW
)@@G@@@^@@@@. THE CODE GENERATED IS:@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         SLJ       TSNABX
)@@G@@P$            . CALL ROUTINE  @E@@@@.         L         A0,PLACE        BY
)@@G@@  . EXECUTED TO GET DATA@D@@@@.         'SNAPID'                    . IDBZ
)@@G@@ FOR SNAP   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC                        .   CA
)@@G@@@B@@@@TSNAP*    NAME                        .   @C@@@@MSG(0)    EQU     CB
)@@G@@  P(1,1)            . SNAP ID @F@@@@I DO 5 , DO (MSG(0)*/-30)=0 ,MSG(0) CC
)@@G@@EQU (MSG(0)*/6)++05 . LJSF    @C@@@@PLACE     EQUF      P(1,2),P(1,3),P(CD
)@@G@@1,4) . TEMP @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          SLJ       TSNAP$            . CACE
)@@G@@LL SNAP ROUTINE   @E@@@@          LA        A0,PLACE          . GET WORDCF
)@@G@@ TO DUMP    @C@@@@          +         MSG(0)            . SNAP ID @B@@@@CG
)@@G@@          END                         .   ___ER#THAN^CHECK^POINT]HASAENACH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@@$(2)      AXR$                        .   @[@@@@.     CI
)@@G@@@E@@@@. DIDDLY TRACE ROUTINE TO PRINT UP TO 12 CHARACTERS WITHOUT @A@@@@CJ
)@@G@@. DESTROYING ANY REGISTERS. CALLED: @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         SLJ     CK
)@@G@@  TRACE$            .   @B@@@@.         'MESSAGE (2W)'              .   CL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. WHICH IS GENERATED BY PROCEDURE IN ELEMENT TRACE$P  CM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@TRACE$*   J         0                 . SLJ ENTRY     CN
)@@G@@@C@@@@          S         A0,SAVREG         . SAVE A0 @E@@@@          L,CO
)@@G@@H2      A0,TRACE$         . GET CALL ADDRESS    @F@@@@          LXI,U   CP
)@@G@@  A0,0102           . SKIP COUNT AND LOCATION   @E@@@@          ER      CQ
)@@G@@  PRINT$            . PRINT MESSAGE GIVEN @F@@@@          A,U       A0,2CR
)@@G@@              . COMPUTE RETURN LOCATION   @E@@@@          S,H2      A0,TCS
)@@G@@RACE$         . AND SET IT BACK     @D@@@@          L         A0,SAVREG CT
)@@G@@        . RESTORE A0    @D@@@@          J         *TRACE$           . SLCU
)@@G@@J RETURN    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. EXECUTION TIME ROUTINE FOR TCV
)@@G@@RANSPARENT SNAP.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CALLED VIA SEQUENCE:  @[@@@@.     CW
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         SLJ       TSNAP$            . CALL SNAPPER  @G@@@@.     CX
)@@G@@    L         A0,DATA           . ARB INSTRUCTION TO LOAD DATA    @F@@@@CY
)@@G@@.         'IDLJSF'                    . DUMP ID ONE WORD LJSF     @^@@@@CZ
)@@G@@.         <RETURN POINT>@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. DESTROYS NO REGISTERS @[@@@@DA
)@@G@@.     @E@[@@TSNAP$*   EX        0                 . SLJ ENTRY/GET ARG   DB
)@@G@@@E@@@[TSNAP$*   J         0                 . SLJ ENTRY/GET ARG   @F@@@@DC
)@@G@@          DS        A0,SAVREG+0       . SAVE REGISTERS WE USE     @F@@@@DD
)@@G@@          DS        A2,SAVREG+2       . SAVE REGISTERS WE USE     @[@@@@DE
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@. GET THE VALUE TO BE EDITED.  NOTE THAT ADDRESS OF LOAD A0 DF
)@@G@@@F@@@@. INSTRUCTION HAS BEEN STUFFED INTO H2 OF TSNAP$ BY ENTRY SLJ (!).DG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@[@@          EX        TSNAP$            . GET DATA TO BEDH
)@@G@@ DUMPED     @F@@@[          EX        *TSNAP$           . GET DATA TO BEDI
)@@G@@ DUMPED     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. TRANSLATE DATA TO FIELDATA OCTAL  @[@@@@DJ
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          DL        A2,('            ') . GET BLANKS  @]@@@@DK
)@@G@@TSN010    . @E@@@@          DSL       A0,3              . NEXT DIGIT TO DL
)@@G@@A1    @E@@@@          SSL       A1,36-3           . AND RIGHT JUSTIFY   DM
)@@G@@@E@@@@          A,U       A3,'0'-' ',A1     . NEXT CHAR TO A3     @D@@@@DN
)@@G@@          DSC       A2,6              . TO S1 OF A2   @E@@@@          JNDO
)@@G@@Z       A0,TSN010         . LOOP IF MORE TO DO  @F@@@@          DS      DP
)@@G@@  A2,PVAL           . STORE VALUE TO BE PRINTED @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. GET DQ
)@@G@@DUMP ID AND INCREMENT RETURN POINT. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          L,H2    DR
)@@G@@  A0,TSNAP$         . GET RETURN POINTER  @D@@@@          L         A1,1DS
)@@G@@,A0           . LOAD DUMP ID  @F@@@@          S         A1,PDID         DT
)@@G@@  . SET DUMP ID IN PRINT LINE @F@@@@          A,U       A0,2            DU
)@@G@@  . INCREMENT RETURN POINT    @E@@@@          S,H2      A0,TSNAP$       DV
)@@G@@  . AND REPLACE ADDRESS @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. PRINT DUMP LINE.@[@@@@.     DW
)@@G@@@C@@@@          L         A0,PCW            . GET PCW @D@@@@          ERDX
)@@G@@        PRINT$            . PRINT THE LINE@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. RESTORE REDY
)@@G@@GISTERS AND RETURN@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          DL        A0,SAVREG+0     DZ
)@@G@@  . RESTORE REGISTERS WE USE  @F@@@@          DL        A2,SAVREG+2     EA
)@@G@@  . RESTORE REGISTERS WE USE  @E@@@@          J         *TSNAP$         EB
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SAVREG    RES       4         EC
)@@G@@        . A0-A3   @]@@@@PBUF      . @E@@@@PDID      RES       1         ED
)@@G@@        . DUMP IDENTIFIER     @B@@@[          '  =  0'                  EE
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@PVAL      RES       2                 . OCTAL VALUE EDITED HEF
)@@G@@ERE   @E@@@@PCW       +         0100+$-PBUF,PBUF  . PRINT CONTROL WORD  EG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   ___@@0[)K^J(EH
)@@G@@C@@[PD'=@@@IC@@@[#'=@@@I/K@[W0C@@^+S'=@@@I/K@[W0'=@@@J/CC@@@+@@^KIA#K^H2EI
)@@G@@C@@^+9'=@@@I/,0@/2/#)[W0R;@^->'=@@@J @@@@U/K@^L.*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@#      EJ
)@@G@@    AXR$                        .   @B@@@#          M$APROC             EK
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@#.     @A@B@#. FORMAT ROUTINE FOR OCTAL DUMPING. @B@@@BEL
)@@G@@. FORMAT ROUTINE FOR HEXADECIMAL DUMPING. @[@@@#.     @D@^@#FOCTAL*   + EM
)@@G@@        4,EOCTAL          . OCTAL FORMAT  @D@B@^FOCTAL*   DFMT      4,EOEN
)@@G@@CTAL          . OCTAL FORMAT  @E@@@BFHEXAD*   DFMT      4,EDHEX         EO
)@@G@@  . HEX WORD FORMAT     +@@@@[@I@B@#C1CC(SCD^ K)^@)C-AD(O^@)^@)^@)A)?C(^EP
)@@G@@D[ F@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@) 0)D[ F@)E9JEL^^[AD9MD([E))+@@@@@@F@@@BFHEXQW*   DFEQ
)@@G@@MT      4,EDHQW           . HEX QUARTER-WORD FORMAT   @[@@@B.     @]@@@BER
)@@G@@EDHEX     . @E@@@B          L,U       A1,9              . DO 9 DIGIT WORES
)@@G@@D     @B@@@B          J         EHEXF$            .   @[@@@B.     @[@B@#ET
)@@G@@.     @]@B@#EOCTAL    . @]@@@BEDHQW     . @E@@@^          S         X11,EU
)@@G@@DMPFLG        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @F@@@^          S         A0,DMPTMP EV
)@@G@@        . SAVE WORD FOR EDITING     @C@ @^          E$OCTF    6,DMPTMP,HEW
)@@G@@1       . EDIT H1 @C@B@           E$OCTF    6,DMPTMP,,H1      . EDIT H1 EX
)@@G@@@C@@@B          E$HEXF    3,DMPTMP,,Q1      . EDIT Q1 @B@@@^          E$EY
)@@G@@SKIP    1                 .   @C@ @^          E$OCTF    6,DMPTMP,H2     EZ
)@@G@@  . EDIT H2 @C@B@           E$OCTF    6,DMPTMP,,H2      . EDIT H2 @C@@@BFA
)@@G@@          E$HEXF    3,DMPTMP,,Q2      . EDIT Q2 @F@B@A          E$SKIP  FB
)@@G@@  1                 . SKIP TOTAL OF 2 BETWEEN!  @G@@@B          E$SKIP  FC
)@@G@@  1                 .                                 @C@@@B          E$FD
)@@G@@HEXF    3,DMPTMP,,Q3      . EDIT Q3 @B@@@B          E$SKIP    1         FE
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@B          E$HEXF    3,DMPTMP,,Q4      . EDIT Q4 @F@@@BFF
)@@G@@          E$SKIP    1                 . SKIP TOTAL OF 2 BETWEEN!  @F@@@^FG
)@@G@@          L         X11,DMPFLG        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@^FH
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @E@^@#      FI
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,12             . EDIT 12 COLUMNS     @C@^@#          J FJ
)@@G@@        EOCTF$            . OF OCTAL@[@@@#.     @B@@@#          END     FK
)@@G@@                    .   ___@@@@F@G@E          S *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@@ .   FL
)@@G@@@F@@@@@ . THIS ADD STREAM SCANS ALL ASM ELEMENTS IN TPF$ FOR USES OF    FM
)@@G@@@D@@@@@ . THE MAJOR REGISTER SET (X1-X10,A6-A15,R4-R15).    @[@@@@@ .   FN
)@@G@@@#@[@@@CULL,CM PLUS/80  @#@]@[@CULL,CM ASM/72   @#@@@]@CULL,CME ASM/72  FO

)@@G@@DE IS OFF   @B@@@@          AXR$                        .   @[@@@@.     HU
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS SUBROUTINES TO IMPLEMENT A HIGHER-LEVEL USHV
)@@G@@ER    @G@@@@. INTERFACE.  THE MACROS PROVIDED IN ANOTHER ELEMENT PROVIDEHW
)@@G@@ A MENU     @G@@@@. SELECT CAPABILITY, A DATA-ENTRY FACILITY, AND PROVIDHX
)@@G@@E USEFUL STATUS   @E@@@@. INFORMATION SUCH AS EOF FLAGS AND A0 AFTER THEHY
)@@G@@ TREAD.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. ALL CALLS TO TREAD AND PRINT ARE VIA A PHZ
)@@G@@ACKAGE CALLED H$UIO WHICH     @G@@@@. PROVIDES THE CAPABILITY TO USE THEIA
)@@G@@SE ROUTINES WITH ANOTHER INTERFACE  @G@@@@. BESIDES THE DEMAND SYMBIONTSIB
)@@G@@.  THE VERSION OF H$UIO ASSEMBLED HERE MAY@G@@@@. BE TURNED OFF UNDER COIC
)@@G@@NFIGURATION CONTROL.  IF THIS IS DONE, THE USER @A@@@@. MUST PROVIDE THEID
)@@G@@ H$UIO ROUTINES.  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@MAXRIN    EQU       33              IE
)@@G@@  . MAX LENGTH OF READ$ @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. PROVIDE RAW DATAIF
)@@G@@ ENTRY CAPABILITY.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         L         A0,<PROMPT STRINIG
)@@G@@G> .  @E@@@@.         LMJ       X11,H$ASK         . ASK USER FOR DATA   IH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. A0 = -1 => END-OF-FILE RETURNED FROM USER     @A@@@@II
)@@G@@. A0 = 0  => NO RESPONSE WAS FOUND  @B@@@@. A0 > 0  => A0 CONTAINS RESPOIJ
)@@G@@NSE STRING  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. DESTROYS X11,A0-A5,R1 @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IK
)@@G@@. PROMPT AND RESPONSE STRINGS ARE A 36 BIT WORD WITH THE NUMBER   @D@@@@IL
)@@G@@. OF CHARACTERS IN H1 AND THE BUFFER ADDRESS IN H2.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@IM
)@@G@@$(2)      . @D@@@@ASKRET    +         0                 . RETURN ADDRESSIN
)@@G@@@D@@@@ASKPRO    +         0                 . PROMPT STRING @D@@@@ASKBUFIO
)@@G@@    +         0,BUFFER          . BUFFER CONTROL@E@@@@ASKREM    +       IP
)@@G@@  0                 . REMAINDER IN BUFFER @[@@@@.     @D@@@@H$ASKBUF* EQIQ
)@@G@@U       ASKBUF            . BUFFER CONTROL@E@@@@H$ASKREM* EQU       ASKRIR
)@@G@@EM            . REMAINDER IN BUFFER @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BUFCUR    RES     IS
)@@G@@  2                 . CURRENT LOAD INDICES@D@@@@BUFFER    RES       MAXRIT
)@@G@@IN            . INPUT BUFFER  @E@@@@RESBUF    RES       MAXRIN          IU
)@@G@@  . RESPONSE BUFFER     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@$(1)      LIT                 IV
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@[AS]H$AKAS* .     @#@@@@[FD]H$AKFD* .     IW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          S         X11,ASKRET        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@@IX
)@@G@@          S         A0,ASKPRO         . SAVE PROMPT STRING  @]@@@@ASK020IY
)@@G@@    . @F@@@@          L         A5,ASKREM         . GET REMAINING CHARACIZ
)@@G@@TERS  @F@@@@          JZ        A5,ASK060         . IF ZERO, JUST READ NJA
)@@G@@OW    @F@@@@          DL        A2,BUFCUR         . ELSE SCAN CURRENT BUJB
)@@G@@FFER  @]@@@@ASK030    . @F@@@@          JGD       A5,$+2            . COJC
)@@G@@UNT FETCHED CHARACTERS  @D@@@@          J         ASK060            . IFJD
)@@G@@ EMPTY, READ@E@@@@          EX        0,*A3             . GET NEXT CHARAJE
)@@G@@CTER  @D@@@@[AS]      TNE,U     A4,040            . IS IT BLANK   @D@@@@JF
)@@G@@[FD]      TNE,U     A4,05             . IS IT BLANK   @D@@@@          J JG
)@@G@@        ASK030            . YES - SKIP IT @E@@@@          DL        A0,RJH
)@@G@@ESIDX         . ELSE GET STORE INDEX@]@@@@ASK040    . @E@@@@          EXJI
)@@G@@        0,*A1             . STORE CHARACTER     @E@@@@          EX      JJ
)@@G@@  0,*A3             . LOAD NEXT CHARACTER @F@@@@          JGD       A5,$JK
)@@G@@+2            . COUNT FETCHED CHARACTERS  @F@@@@          J         ASK0JL
)@@G@@50            . NO MORE - RETURN RESPONSE @D@@@@[AS]      TE,U      A4,0JM
)@@G@@40            . IS IT BLANK   @D@@@@[FD]      TE,U      A4,05           JN
)@@G@@  . IS IT BLANK   @E@@@@          J         ASK040            . NO - SCAJO
)@@G@@N RESPONSES @]@@@@ASK050    . @F@@@@          DS        A2,BUFCUR       JP
)@@G@@  . SAVE CURRENT POINTERS     @E@@@@          JP        A5,$+2          JQ
)@@G@@  . IF NEGATIVE THEN    @C@@@@          L,U       A5,0              . GEJR
)@@G@@T ZERO@F@@@@          S         A5,ASKREM         . SAVE REMAINDER IN BUJS
)@@G@@FFER  @F@@@@          AN,U      A0,RESBUF         . COMPUTE CHARACTER LEJT
)@@G@@NGTH  @D@@@@          AN,U      A1,STB020         . OF RESPONSE   @F@@@@JU
)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,2              . CONVERT WORD COUNT TO CHAR@F@@@@JV
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,0,A1           . ADD IN RESIDUAL (1-4)     @F@@@@JW
)@@G@@          AN,U      A2,BUFFER         . COMPUTE CHARACTER POSITION@F@@@@JX
)@@G@@          AN,U      A3,LTB020         . OF LAST CHARACTER SCANNED @F@@@@JY
)@@G@@          LSSL      A2,2              . CONVERT WORD COUNT TO CHAR@F@@@@JZ
)@@G@@          A,U       A2,0,A3           . ADD IN RESIDUAL (1-4)     @D@@@@KA
)@@G@@          L,U       A1,0,A2           . ELIMINATE H1  @G@@@@          ANKB
)@@G@@,U      A1,0,A0           . COMPUTE START INDEX OF WORD     @E@@@@      KC
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,18             . MAKE ACCESS WORD    @D@@@@          A,KD
)@@G@@U       A0,RESBUF         . FOR RESPONSE  @D@@@@          J         ASK1KE
)@@G@@00            . RETURN FIND   @]@@@@ASK060    . @D@@@@          SZ      KF
)@@G@@  ASKREM            . SET NO BUFFER @F@@@@          L,U       A1,0      KG
)@@G@@        . CLEAR RETURN PARAMETERS   @E@@@@          L         A0,ASKPRO KH
)@@G@@        . GET PROMPT STRING   @F@@@@          JZ        A0,ASK100       KI
)@@G@@  . IF NOT PASSED THEN NOFIND @F@@@@          L,U       A1,BUFFER       KJ
)@@G@@  . ELSE GET BUFFER ADDRESS   @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,H$UIQ       KK
)@@G@@  . PROCESS USER IO QUERY     @E@@@@          SZ        ASKPRO          KL
)@@G@@  . INHIBIT ANOTHER READ@E@@@@          JZ        A0,ASK070         . IFKM
)@@G@@ END-OF-FILE JUMP @E@@@@          SSL       A0,18             . GET CHARKN
)@@G@@ACTER COUNT @D@@@@          S,H1      A0,ASKBUF         . SET LENGTH ANDKO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          S         A0,ASKREM         . REMAINDER OF BUFFER @D@@@@KP
)@@G@@          DL        A0,BUFIDX         . SET UP TO SCAN@D@@@@          DSKQ
)@@G@@        A0,BUFCUR         . CURRENT BUFFER@C@@@@          J         ASK0KR
)@@G@@20            . AND LOOP@]@@@@ASK070    . @F@@@@          LN,U      A0,1KS
)@@G@@              . SET EOF FLAG (A0 NEGATIVE)@]@@@@ASK100    . @F@@@@      KT
)@@G@@    L         X11,ASKRET        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@@      KU
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@KV
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. EXECUTE TABLES FOR ABOVE.   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@BUFIDX    + KW
)@@G@@        1,BUFFER-1        .   @B@@@@          +         1,LTB030        KX
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@[AS]LTB010. @E@@@@[AS]      L,Q1      A4,1,*A2  KY
)@@G@@        . GET NEXT CHARACTER  @]@@@@[AS]LTB020. @C@@@@[AS]      LMJ     KZ
)@@G@@  A3,0,A3           . RETURN  @C@@@@[AS]      L,Q2      A4,0,A2         LA
)@@G@@  . GET CHAR@C@@@@[AS]      L,Q3      A4,0,A2           . GET CHAR@C@@@@LB

)@@G@@[FD]LTB010. @E@@@@[FD]      L,S1      A4,1,*A2          . GET NEXT CHARALE

)@@G@@.     @B@@@@RESIDX    +         1,RESBUF-1        .   @B@@@@          + LL
)@@G@@        1,STB030          .   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@[AS]STB010. @D@@@@[AS]  LM
)@@G@@    LSSL      A4,36-9           . LEFT JUSTIFY  @D@@@@[AS]      A       LN
)@@G@@  A4,(040040040)    . SPACE FILL    @D@@@@[AS]      S         A4,1,*A0  LO
