)@@G@@IZED? @D@@@^          J         FDA030            . YES, SKIP THIS@G@@@^PF
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,INITSUBS      . INITIALIZE DIRECTORY SUBROUTINESPG
)@@G@@@C@@@^          JNZ       A5,FDA999         . ERROR   @]@@@^FDA030    . PH
)@@G@@@E@@@^          L         A0,COMTMP         . GET ABSOLUTE ADDRESS@E@@@^PI
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,READITEM      . SIMULATE MFDF READ  @E@@@^      PJ
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,FDA999         . RETURN ON ERROR     @F@@@^          LMPK
)@@G@@J       X11,WHATKIND      . FIND OUT WHAT KIND IT IS  @]@@@^FDA999    . PL
)@@G@@@F@@@^          L         X11,COMLNK        . RECOVER RETURN ADDRESS    PM
)@@G@@@E@@@^          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@^PN
)@@G@@/.    @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. PERFORM LOOKUP ALGORITHM ON SPECIFIED QUALIFIEPO
)@@G@@R AND FILENAME.   @F@@@^. READ FIRST DIRECTORY SECTOR (SEARCH OR LEAD) IPP
)@@G@@N LOOKUP PATH.    @[@@@^.     @C@@@^.         FDLUT     <QUALIFIER>*<FILPQ
)@@G@@ENAME>.     @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. IF FILENAME NOT GIVEN, DOES TREADS FOR QPR
)@@G@@UALIFIER AND FILENAME.  @F@@@^. QUALIFIER AND FILENAME ARE HASHED TO GETPS
)@@G@@ LOOKUP TABLE INDEX.    @E@@@^. READ THE MFDF SECTOR IMPLICATED BY LOOKUPT
)@@G@@P TABLE WORD.     @[@@@^.     @B@@@^FDLMSQ    'QUALIFIER? %'            PU
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@^FDLTRQ    PF        1,$-FDLMSQ,FDLMSQ . ASK FOR QUAL  @C@@@^PV
)@@G@@          +         M$TREOF,FQUAL     . QUAL    @[@@@^.     @B@@@^FDLMSFPW
)@@G@@    'FILE NAME? %'               .  @D@@@^FDLTRF    PF        1,$-FDLMSFPX
)@@G@@,FDLMSF . ASK FOR FILE  @C@@@^          +         M$TREOF,FNAME     . FIPY
)@@G@@LE    @[@@@^.     @]@@@^CFDLUT*   . @E@@@^          SX        X11,COMLNKPZ
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @G@@@^          LMJ       X11,M$SCANFILE  QA
)@@G@@  . SCAN FILENAME INTO ELT$ PACKET  @E@@@^          JNZ       A5,FDL999 QB
)@@G@@        . RETURN ON ERROR     @[@@@^.     @E@@@^. IF TRADITIONAL FILENAMQC
)@@G@@E PRESENT (F. OR Q*F.) TAKE IT.     @[@@@^.     @F@@@^          TZ      QD
)@@G@@  FNL               . UNLESS FILENAME ABSENT    @F@@@^          J       QE
)@@G@@  FDL030            . TAKE TRADITIONAL FILENAME @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. IF SQF
)@@G@@INGLE NAME WITHOUT TRAILING PERIOD TAKE ELEMENT AS FILENAME.@[@@@^.     QG
)@@G@@@F@@@^          L         A0,ENL            . GET 'ELEMENT NAME' LENGTH QH
)@@G@@@G@@@^          JZ        A0,FDL020         . IF NONE, MUST TREAD FOR NAQI
)@@G@@MES   @F@@@^          S         A0,FNL            . ELSE SET FILE NAME LQJ
)@@G@@ENGTH @E@@@^          DL        A0,ENAME          . GET ELEMENT NAME    QK
)@@G@@@D@@@^          DS        A0,FNAME          . SET FILE NAME @D@@@^      QL
)@@G@@    J         FDL030            . AND CONTINUE  @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. FILEQM
)@@G@@NAME NOT SPECIFIED ON COMMAND LINE SO WE MUST ASK FOR IT.   @E@@@^. NOTEQN
)@@G@@ THAT # AS FIRST CHARACTER OF QUALIFIER OR FILENAME IS@E@@@^.  A SPECIALQO
)@@G@@ FLAG THAT THE FIRST CHARACTER IS REALLY @.     @E@@@^.  THIS IS FOR LOOQP
)@@G@@KING UP VERY UGLY LOOKING FILENAMES....   @[@@@^.     @]@@@^FDL020    . QQ
)@@G@@@E@@@^          DL        A0,BLANKS         . FIELDATA BLANKS     @D@@@^QR
)@@G@@          DS        A0,FQUAL          . CLEAR QUAL    @C@@@^          DSQS
)@@G@@        A0,FNAME          . AND FILE@[@@@^.     @E@@@^          L,U     QT
)@@G@@  A0,FDLTRQ         . ASK FOR QUALIFIER   @C@@@^          LMJ       X11,QU
)@@G@@M$TREADF      . ASK HIM @D@@@^          JNZ       A4,FDL100         . EOQV
)@@G@@F RETURN    @D@@@^          S         A0,FQL            . SET LENGTH    QW
)@@G@@@E@@@^          L,S1      A0,FQUAL          . GET FIRST CHARACTER @D@@@^QX
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,'#'            . FUNNY THING?  @E@@@^          SZQY
)@@G@@,S1     FQUAL             . YES, CHANGE TO @    @[@@@^.     @E@@@^      QZ
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,FDLTRF         . ASK FOR FILENAME    @C@@@^          LMRA
)@@G@@J       X11,M$TREADF      . ASK HIM @D@@@^          JNZ       A4,FDL100 RB
)@@G@@        . EOF RETURN    @D@@@^          S         A0,FNL            . SERC
)@@G@@T LENGTH    @E@@@^          L,S1      A0,FNAME          . GET FIRST CHARRD
)@@G@@ACTER @D@@@^          TNE,U     A0,'#'            . FUNNY THING?  @E@@@^RE
)@@G@@          SZ,S1     FNAME             . YES, CHANGE IT TO @ @[@@@^/.    RF
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @E@@@^. IF QUALIFIER NOT GIVEN, TEST AND GET PROJECT OR @QUARG
)@@G@@L.    @^@@@^. (NOTE FALL-THRU).     @[@@@^.     @]@@@^FDL030    . @E@@@^RH
)@@G@@          TZ        FQL               . WAS QUALIFIER GIVEN?@E@@@^      RI
)@@G@@    J         FDL050            . YES, SKIP THIS MESS @G@@@^          TZRJ
)@@G@@        IQF               . WAS LEADING * (@QUAL) GIVEN?    @E@@@^      RK
)@@G@@    J         FDL040            . YES, GO FETCH QUAL  @[@@@^.     @ @@@^RL
)@@G@@. FETCH RUN'S PROJECT ID.     @[@@@^.     @E@@@^          L,U       A0,FRM
)@@G@@QUAL          . GET SCRATCH SPACE   @F@@@^          L         A1,(1,5)  RN
)@@G@@        . GET WORD 5 OF THE PCT     @F@@@^          ER        PCT$      RO
)@@G@@        . POINTER TO QUAL CHAIN     @G@@@^          LXM,H1    A1,FQUAL  RP
)@@G@@        . GET POINTER TO FIRST QUAL BUFF  @E@@@^          AH        A1,(RQ
)@@G@@1,1)          . WORD 1 LENGTH 2     @G@@@^          ER        PCT$      RR
)@@G@@        . PROJECT IS FIRST QUAL ON CHAIN  @C@@@^          J         FDL0RS
)@@G@@50            . CONTINUE@[@@@^.     @ @@@^. FETCH CURRENT @QUAL VALUE.  RT
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @]@@@^FDL040    . @E@@@^          L,U       A0,FQUAL        RU
)@@G@@  . GET PLACE TO PUT IT @E@C@^          L         A1,(2,021)        . GERV
)@@G@@T PLACE IT LIVES  @E@@@C          L         A1,(2,023)        . GET PLACRW
)@@G@@E IT LIVES  @E@@@^          ER        PCT$              . GET @QUAL VALURX
)@@G@@E     @[@@@^.     @D@@@^. IF FILENAME NOT GIVEN, GET A REASONABLE (?) DERY
)@@G@@FAULT.@[@@@^.     @]@@@^FDL050    . @E@@@^          TZ        FNL       RZ
)@@G@@        . WAS FILENAME GIVEN  @E@@@^          J         FDL060          SA
)@@G@@  . YES, SKIP THIS MESS @C@@@^          DL        A0,('TPF$        ') . SB
)@@G@@HA    @E@@@^          DS        A0,FNAME          . SET TO ONE WE KNOW  SC
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @F@@@^. QUALIFIER AND FILENAME ARE IN ELT$ PACKET BY HOOK ORSD
)@@G@@ BY CROOK.  @D@@@^. PERFORM HASH, READ LOOKUP TABLE, READ FILE ITEM.    SE
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @]@@@^FDL060    . @E@@@^          TZ        INITDR          SF
)@@G@@  . HAVE WE INITIALIZED?@D@@@^          J         FDL070            . YESG
)@@G@@S, SKIP THIS@G@@@^          LMJ       X11,INITSUBS      . INITIALIZE DIRSH
)@@G@@ECTORY SUBROUTINES@C@@@^          JNZ       A5,FDL999         . ERROR   SI
)@@G@@@]@@@^FDL070    . @D@@@^          DL        A0,FQUAL          . GET THE SJ
)@@G@@QUAL  @D@@@^          DL        A4,FNAME          . AND THE FILE  @E@@@^SK
)@@G@@          L,U       A3,FDSPKT         . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @D@@@^      SL
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,FDLUT         . DO THE LOOK UP@D@@@^          JNZ     SM
)@@G@@  A0,FDL999         . JUMP ON ERROR @F@@@^          S         A4,COMTMP SN
)@@G@@        . SAVE ABSOLUTE ADDRESS     @D@@@^          E$OPEN    M$EPKT M$ISO
)@@G@@MAGE    . BEGIN EDIT    @E@@@^          E$OCTF    12,COMTMP         . EDSP
)@@G@@IT THE NUMBER     @C@@@^          E$PRTX                      . PRINT ITSQ
)@@G@@@G@@@^          L         A0,COMTMP         . RESTORE MFDF ADDRESS ADDRESR
)@@G@@SS    @E@@@^          LMJ       X11,READITEM      . SIMULATE MFDF READ  SS
)@@G@@@C@@@^          JNZ       A5,FDL999         . ERROR   @F@@@^          LMST
)@@G@@J       X11,WHATKIND      . FIND OUT WHAT KIND IT IS  @C@@@^          JNSU
)@@G@@Z       A5,FDL999         . ERROR   @]@@@^FDL100    . @E@@@^          L,SV
)@@G@@U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @]@@@^FDL999    . @E@@@^SW
)@@G@@          L         X11,COMLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@^      SX
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@^/.    @[@@@^SY
)@@G@@.     @C@@@^. INTERNAL SUBROUTINE TO SIMULATE MFDF$$ READ.  @[@@@^.     SZ
)@@G@@@B@@@^.         L         A0,<ADDRESS>      .   @D@@@^.         LMJ     TA
)@@G@@  X11,READITEM      . READ THE ITEM @B@@@^.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>TB
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@^.     @D@@@^. IF FDSUBS ERROR OCCURS CAN GENERATE ERROTC
)@@G@@R MESSAGE.  @C@@@^. IF FDSUBS ERROR 8 CAN PRINT WARNING MESSAGE.  @[@@@^TD
)@@G@@.     @]@@@^READITEM  . @E@@@^          S         X11,SUBLNK        . SATE
)@@G@@VE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@^          L         A4,A0             . GET ABSOTF
)@@G@@LUTE ADDRESS@G@@@^          TRDMODE                     . GO TO THIRD WOTG
)@@G@@RD MODE FOR FDSUBS@F@@@^          L,U       A3,FDSPKT         . GET THE TH
)@@G@@PACKET ADDRESS    @G@@@^          LMJ       X11,FDABR         . DO THE STI
)@@G@@IMULATION OF A ABREAD   @F@@@^          L,U       A4,0,A0           . SATJ
)@@G@@VE ERROR CODE (IF ANY)  @F@@@^          QTRMODE                     . GOTK
)@@G@@ TO QUARTER WORD MODE   @E@@@^          TE,U      A4,8              . COTL
)@@G@@NTINUE ON STATUS 8@H@@@^          JNZ       A4,IAB999         . OTHERWISTM
)@@G@@E EXIT ON NON ZERO STATUS     @[@@@^.     @E@@@^. IF NO ERROR A2 CONTAINTN
)@@G@@S THE CORE ADDRESS OF THE SECTOR    @[@@@^.     @E@@@^          LXI,U   TO
)@@G@@  A2,1              . GET INCREMENT BIT   @F@@@^          L         A0,BTP
)@@G@@UFADR         . GET THE BUFFER ADDRESS    @F@@@^          LXI,U     A0,1TQ
)@@G@@              . SET INCREMENT FOR TRANSFER@D@@@^          L,U       R1,2TR
)@@G@@8             . GET COUNT     @F@@@^          S         R1,BUFWDS       TS
)@@G@@  . SET AS NUMBER OF WORDS    @D@@@^          BT        A0,,*A2         TT
)@@G@@  . TRANSFER IT   @[@@@^.     @F@@@^. FDSUBS ERROR 8 (SECTOR ON DIRECTORTU
)@@G@@Y TRACK, NOT ALLOCATED) IS    @F@@@^. TREATED AS A WARNING.  A MESSAGE ITV
)@@G@@S PRINTED AND OPERATION OF    @E@@@^. FILEDIT CONTINUES NORMALLY.  ON BRTW
)@@G@@IEF INHIBITS MESSAGE.   @[@@@^.     @F@@@^          JZ        A4,IAB010 TX
)@@G@@        . IF NO ERROR, SKIP THIS    @E@@@^          TZ        M$BRIEF   TY
)@@G@@        . UNLESS BRIEF FLAG   @E@@@^          J         IAB010          TZ
)@@G@@  . INHIBITS MESSAGES   @F@@@^          PRINT     A5                . PRUA
)@@G@@INT THE WARNING MESSAGE @]@@@^IAB010    . @E@@@^          L,U       A5,0UB
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @]@@@^IAB999    . @E@@@^          L UC
)@@G@@        X11,SUBLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@^          J       UD
)@@G@@  0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@^/.    @[@@@^.     @G@@@^UE
)@@G@@. EXAMINE DIRECTORY BITS TO FIND OUT WHAT KIND OF FILE ITEM WE GOT.     UF
)@@G@@@F@@@^. ALSO SETS NOMORE FLAG (WHICH SEE) TO INHIBIT AUTOMATIC READING. UG
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @H@@@^.         LMJ       X11,WHATKIND      . FIND OUT WHAT UH
)@@G@@KIND OF ITEM WE GOT     @B@@@^.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>        .   UI
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @G@@@^. IF ITEM IS KNOWN FROM TYPE BITS (SECTOR ZERO OF SEARUJ
)@@G@@CH, LEAD, MAIN)   @G@@@^. AND UNLESS INHIBITED BY BRIEF FLAG, PRINTS WHAUK
)@@G@@T KIND OF ITEM GOTTEN.  @[@@@^.     @]@@@^WHATKIND  . @E@@@^          S UL
)@@G@@        X11,SUBLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@^          L       UM
)@@G@@  A0,BUFADR         . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  @D@@@^          L         A1,0UN
)@@G@@,A0           . GET FIRST WORD@E@@@^          LSSL      A1,1            UO
)@@G@@  . GET RID OF TOP BIT  @C@@@^          SSL       A1,33             . GEUP
)@@G@@T BITS@D@@@^          L,U       A4,0              . UNKNOWN ITEM  @E@@@^UQ
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A1,1              . IS IT SEARCH ITEM   @C@@@^      UR
)@@G@@    L         A4,SRCITM         . YES     @E@@@^          TNE,U     A1,2US
)@@G@@              . IS IT LEAD ITEM     @C@@@^          L         A4,LEDITM UT
)@@G@@        . YES     @E@@@^          TNE,U     A1,4              . IS IT MAUU
)@@G@@IN ITEM     @C@@@^          L         A4,MANITM         . YES     @[@@@^UV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@^. IF TYPE RECOGNIZED TELL HIM WHAT KIND WAS FOUND.  IN ALL CUW
)@@G@@ASES  @G@@@^. HOWEVER PUT SOMETHING INTO "NOMORE" TO INHIBIT AUTOMATIC CUX
)@@G@@ONTINUATION.@[@@@^.     @E@@@^          JZ        A4,IIT010         . ISUY
)@@G@@ TYPE RECOGNIZED  @F@@@^          TZ        M$BRIEF           . AND ARE UZ
)@@G@@MESSAGES ALLOWED  @E@@@^          J         IIT020            . NO - SKIVA
)@@G@@P THE PRINT @F@@@^          PRINT     A4                . ELSE PRINT WHAVB
)@@G@@T TYPE FOUND@E@@@^          J         IIT020            . AND STORE THE VC
)@@G@@PCW   @[@@@^.     @C@@@^. PUT "UNKNOWN ITEM" MESSAGE INTO NOMORE ONLY.  VD
)@@G@@@[@@@^.     @]@@@^IIT010    . @F@@@^          L         A4,UNKITM       VE
)@@G@@  . GET UNKNOWN ITEM MESSAGE  @]@@@^IIT020    . @E@@@^          S       VF
)@@G@@  A4,NOMORE         . QUOTH THE RAVEN..   @E@@@^          L,U       A5,0VG
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @F@@@^          L         X11,SUBLNKVH
)@@G@@        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@^          J         0,X11     VI
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@^.     @F@@@^          SYMTAB    1   VJ
)@@G@@              . GENERATE SYMBOL TABLE     @[@@@^.     @B@@@^          ENVK
)@@G@@D                         .   _@@@@@    FDGET   >@@@@^@]@@@#@@@@@@.     VL
)@@G@@>@@@@]@#@@@#@@@@@@MFDGET*   . >@@@@#@F@@@#@@@@@@          S         X11,VM
)@@G@@COMLNK        . SAVE RET*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@-          AXR$                VN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@-          M$APROC                     .   @[@@@-.     VO
)@@G@@@E@@@-DEBUG     EQU       1                 . 1 FOR ON 0 FOR OFF  @B@@@-VP
)@@G@@TRACE     EQU       0                 .   @[@@@-.     @G@@@-. CORE MANAGVQ
)@@G@@EMENT ROUTINE WHOSE BUFFER SIZES ARE THE FIBONACCI NUMBERS  @[@@@-.     VR
)@@G@@@^@@@-.    BY  KERN E. SIBBALD@[@@@-.     @C@@@-.    RIPPED OFF BY BEN CVS
)@@G@@RANSTON FOR CPMD 9/23/75@C@@@-.    DAY ZERO BUG FIXED 10/15/86 (THANKS LVT
)@@G@@OUIE!)@[@@@-.     @[@@@-.     @F@@@-. MIN AND MAX SIZ ARE THE SIZE OF DEVU
)@@G@@SIRED USER BUFFERS IN WORDS   @[@@@-.     @H@@@-MINSIZ    EQU       2   VV
)@@G@@              . MINIMUM BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WORDS  @H@<@-MAXSIZ    EQVW
)@@G@@U       900               . MAXIMUM BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WORDS  @H@=@<VX
)@@G@@MAXSIZ    EQU       5000              . MAXIMUM BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WVY
)@@G@@ORDS  @H@>@=MAXSIZ    EQU       900               . MAXIMUM BUFFER REQUEVZ
)@@G@@ST SIZE IN WORDS  @H@@@>MAXSIZ    EQU       5000              . MAXIMUM WA
)@@G@@BUFFER REQUEST SIZE IN WORDS  @[@@@-.     @B@@@-P         PROC          WB
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@-FIB*      NAME                        .   @C@@@-WC
)@@G@@F(0)      EQU       1                 . STARTER @B@@@-F(1)      EQU     WD
)@@G@@  1                 .   @D@@@-C(0)      EQU       2                 . STWE
)@@G@@ART INDEX   @B@@@-LOOP      NAME                        .   @D@@@-F(C(0)WF
)@@G@@)   EQU       F(C(0)-1)+F(C(0)-2) . FIBONACCI   @D@@@-          DO      WG
)@@G@@  F(C(0))<MINSIZ+1 ,S(0) EQU C(0) . @B@@@-C(0)      EQU       C(0)+1    WH
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@-          DO        F(C(0)-1)<MAXSIZ+1 , GO LOOP@B@@@-WI
)@@G@@C(0)      EQU       C(0)-1            .   @B@@@-MININX*   EQU       S(0)WJ
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@-MAXINX*   EQU       C(0)-S(0)+1       . CURRENT-WK
)@@G@@START+1     @C@@@-I         DO        C(0)-S(0) , + F(S(0)+I),0 . @B@@@-WL
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@-/.    @[@@@-.     @B@@@-WM
)@@G@@          VARS                        .   @[@@@-.     @I@@@-M$BUFPOL* FIWN
)@@G@@B                         . GENERATE FIBONACCI NUMBERS AND LINK TABL    WO
)@@G@@@C@@@-          STBE      'BUFPOL',MAXINX,M$BUFPOL .  @[@@@-.     @F@@@-WP
)@@G@@. ADDITIONAL SPACE IS GOTTEN FROM ER MCORE$.  THIS VARIABLE POINTS@E@@@-WQ
)@@G@@. TO THE BEGINNING ADDRESS OF THE NEXT BUFFER TO BE GOTTEN. @[@@@-.     WR
)@@G@@@B@+@-M$PSGNXT* VAR       'PSGNXT',1 M$PSGFST  .@F@@@+M$PSGNXT* VAR     WS
)@@G@@  'PSGNXT',1        . INITIALIZED BY M$INIT     @[@@@-.     @G@@@-FIBSIZWT
)@@G@@    EQUF      M$BUFPOL-MININX,,H1 . BUFFER SIZE IN WORDS (TOTAL)  @H@@@-WU
)@@G@@FRELNK    EQUF      M$BUFPOL-MININX,,H2 . LINK TO FREE BUFFER OF GIVEN SWV
)@@G@@IZE   @[@@@-.     @D@@@-CTLBIT    EQUF      0,,S1             . CONTROL WW
)@@G@@BITS  @D@@@-CTLINX    EQUF      0,,S2             . SIZE INDEX    @H@@@-WX
)@@G@@CTLFRE    EQUF      0,,S3             . SIZE INDEX IF ALLOCATED ELSE ZERWY
)@@G@@O     @[@@@-.     @G@@@-FL        EQUF      1,,H2             . FORWARD WZ
)@@G@@LINK TO NEXT FREE BUFFER@H@@@-BL        EQUF      1,,H1             . BAXA
)@@G@@CK LINK TO PREVIOUS FREE BUFFER     @[@@@-/.    @[@@@-.     @F@@@-. IF PXB
)@@G@@ARAMETER TRACE IS SET TO ONE THESE ROUTINES PRINT OUT THE   @C@@@-. BUFFXC
)@@G@@ERS AS THEY ARE BEING ASSIGNED AND FREED. @[@@@-.     @B@@@-          ONXD
)@@G@@        TRACE             .   @D@@@-TRASAV    VAR       'TRASAV',2      XE
)@@G@@  . A0 A1 SAVE    @C@@@-ALMSG     'REQ AT & WORDS, GOT & AT &'     .    XF
)@@G@@@A@@@-RELMSG    'REL AT & WORDS AT &'     @B@@@-EDPKT     E$PKT     22,LXG
)@@G@@INE           .   @B@@@-LINE      RES       22                .   @B@@@-XH
)@@G@@EDPCW     +         0126,LINE         .   @D@@@-          OFF       TRACXI
)@@G@@E             . ***** DEBUG   @[@@@-.     @B@@@-. PROCS TO TRACE ALLOCATXJ
)@@G@@ION AND RELEASING @D@@@-. THE CODE IS PUT INTO PROCS TO PREVENT ADDITIONXK
)@@G@@AL    @ @@@-. OBSCURRING OF THE REAL CODE @[@@@-.     @B@@@-P         PRXL
)@@G@@OC                        .   @B@@@-GETTRACE* NAME                      XM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@-          ON        TRACE             .   @D@@@-          DSXN
)@@G@@        A0,TRASAV         . SAVE REGISTERS@B@@@-          E$DIT     EDPKXO
)@@G@@T             .   @B@@@-          E$MSG     ALMSG             .   @E@@@-XP
)@@G@@          E$OCTV    PSGLNK            . EDIT CALL ADDRESS   @B@@@-      XQ
)@@G@@    E$SKIP    1                 .   @E@@@-          E$OCTV    TRASAV    XR
)@@G@@        . EDIT REQUEST SIZE   @B@@@-          E$MSGR                    XS
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@-          E$OCTV    TRASAV+1,,H1      . EDIT GOT SIZE @B@@@-XT
)@@G@@          E$MSGR                      .   @E@@@-          E$OCTV    TRASXU
)@@G@@AV+1,,H2      . EDIT BUFFER ADDRESS @C@@@-          E$DITX              XV
)@@G@@        . END EDIT@E@@@-          L         A0,EDPCW          . GET CONTXW
)@@G@@ROL WORD    @D@@@-          ER        PRINT$            . PRINT MESSAGE XX
)@@G@@@C@@@-          DL        A0,TRASAV         . RESTORE @B@@@-          OFXY
)@@G@@F       TRACE             .   @B@@@-          END                       XZ
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@-.     @B@@@-P         PROC                        .   @B@@@-YA
)@@G@@RELTRACE* NAME                        .   @B@@@-          ON        TRACYB
)@@G@@E             .   @D@@@-          DS        A0,TRASAV         . SAVE REGYC
)@@G@@ISTERS@C@@@-          E$DIT     EDPKT             . EDIT    @C@@@-      YD
)@@G@@    E$MSG     RELMSG            . RELEASE @D@@@-          E$OCTV    PSGLYE
)@@G@@NK            . EDIT ADDRESS  @B@@@-          E$SKIP    1               YF
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@-          L         A0,TRASAV         . GET BUFFER ADDRESS  YG
)@@G@@@G@@@-          AN,U      A0,1              . DECREMENT TO POINT TO CTL YH
)@@G@@WORD  @D@@@-          L         A0,CTLINX,A0      . GET INDEX     @C@@@-YI
)@@G@@          L         A0,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET SIZE@C@@@-          AN,U    YJ
)@@G@@  A0,1              . DEC     @B@@@-          E$OCTV                    YK
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@-          E$MSGR                      .   @E@@@-          E$YL
)@@G@@OCTV    TRASAV            . EDIT BUFFER ADDRESS @B@@@-          E$DITX  YM
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@-          L         A0,EDPCW          .   YN
)@@G@@@B@@@-          ER        PRINT$            .   @B@@@-          DL      YO
)@@G@@  A0,TRASAV         .   @D@@@-          OFF       TRACE             . **YP
)@@G@@*****DEBUG  @B@@@-          END                         .   @[@@@-/.    YQ
)@@G@@@B@@@-          INSTRS                      .   @[@@@-.     @^@@@-. ALLOYR
)@@G@@CATE A CORE BUFFER@[@@@-.     @ @@@-.         L         A0,SIZE   @B@@@-YS
)@@G@@.         LMJ       X11,M$BPSG        .   @G@@@-.         JNZ       A5,EYT
)@@G@@RROR          . IF ERROR A5 COMES BACK NONZERO  @C@@@-.         A0 - STIYU
)@@G@@LL HAS WORD COUNT REQUESTED   @F@@@-.         A1 - ACCESS WORD FOR BUFFEYV
)@@G@@R GOTTEN (COULD BE BIGGER).   @[@@@-.     @[@@@-.     @^@@@-M$COREPRMGETYW
)@@G@@*       .   @B@@@-.         SLJ       TON$              .   @G@@@-      YX
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,0,A0           . GET NUMBER OF WORDS DESIRED     @F@@@-YY
)@@G@@          L         A0,(1,MININX-1)   . PREPARE TO SEARCH TABLE   @E@@@-YZ
)@@G@@          L,U       R1,MAXINX-MININX+1 . FOR FIB BUFFER KEY @E@@@-      ZA
)@@G@@    L         A5,PSGSZE         . PCW FOR BAD SIZE    @F@@@-          SGZB
)@@G@@        A1,FIBSIZ+1,*A0   . SEARCH FOR BUFFER BIG ENUF@F@@@-          J ZC
)@@G@@        0,X11             . NOPE - CANNOT GET ONE     @E@@@-          LXZD
)@@G@@I,U     A0,0              . CLEAR INCREMENT     @B@@@-          J       ZE
)@@G@@  PSG010            .   @^@@@-M$COREPRMKEY*       .   @B@@@-.         SLZF
)@@G@@J       TON$              .   @E@@@-          TLE,U     A0,MININX       ZG
)@@G@@  . IS BELOW MIN SIZE   @D@@@-          L,U       A0,MININX         . YEZH
)@@G@@S - GET MIN @E@@@-          L         A5,PSGSZE         . GET SIZE ERRORZI
)@@G@@ PCW  @E@@@-          TG,U      A0,MAXINX+1       . IS IT WITHIN RANGE  ZJ
)@@G@@@E@@@-          J         0,X11             . NO - ERROR RETURN   @E@@@-ZK
)@@G@@          L         A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . GET BUFFER SIZE     @[@@@-.     ZL
)@@G@@@C@@@-. SIZE KEY IN A0, NUMBER OF WORDS DESIRED IN A1.@[@@@-.     @]@@@-ZM
)@@G@@PSG010    . @E@@@-          S         X11,PSGLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADZN
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@-          DS        A0,PSGTMP         . SAVE REQUESTED SIZE ZO
)@@G@@@E@@@-          DS        A2,PSGSAV         . SAVE IMPORTANT REGS @[@@@-ZP
)@@G@@.     @C@@@-. SEARCH UPWARDS UNTIL A FREE BUFFER IS FOUND.  @[@@@-.     ZQ
)@@G@@@]@@@-PSG020    . @F@@@-          L         A1,FRELNK,A0      . ARE THERZR
)@@G@@E ANY OF THESE    @F@@@-          JZ        A1,PSG030         . IF NOT TZS
)@@G@@RY NEXT SIZE UP   @F@@@-          LMJ       X11,UNLINK        . IF THEREZT
)@@G@@ IS ONE UNLINK    @F@@@-          J         PSG050            . IT AND EZU
)@@G@@NTER SPLIT LOOP   @]@@@-PSG030    . @E@@@-          A,U       A0,1      ZV
)@@G@@        . MOVE TO NEXT SIZE UP@E@@@-          TLE,U     A0,MAXINX+1     ZW
)@@G@@  . AT MAX SIZE YET     @E@@@-          J         PSG020            . NOZX
)@@G@@ - SEE IF ANY FREE@[@@@-.     @G@@@-. CANNOT SATISFY REQUEST FROM FREE BZY
)@@G@@UFFERS.  GET A MAX SIZE BUFFER FROM @F@@@-. ER MCORE$ AND SETUP DUMMY COZZ
)@@G@@NTROL WORD TO PREVENT RECOMBINATION.@F@@@-. THE BANK MCORED IS DETERMINEAA
)@@G@@D BY THE INITIAL VALUE OF M$PSGNXT. @[@@@-.     @F@@@-.         L       AB
)@@G@@  A0,FIBSIZ+MAXINX  . FIND LAST ADDRESS NEEDED  @F@@@-          L,U     AC
)@@G@@  A0,MAXINX         . RESTORE MAX SIZE BUFFER   @F@@@-          L       AD
)@@G@@  A0,FIBSIZ,A0      . FIND LAST ADDRESS NEEDED  @E@@@-          A       AE
)@@G@@  A0,M$PSGNXT       . GET NEXT AVAIL ADDR @B@@@-.         TSNAP     'MCOAF
)@@G@@RE$',A0       .   @D@@@-          ER        MCORE$            . TRY TO GAG
)@@G@@ET IT @[@@@-.     @E@@@-. NOTE - CONTINGENCY HANDLER SETS A0 TO 0 ON MCOAH
)@@G@@RE$ ERRORS. @[@@@-.     @E@@@-          JNZ       A0,PSG035         . SKAI
)@@G@@IP IF NO ERROR    @F@@@-          L         A5,PSGMCE         . GET MCORAJ
)@@G@@E$ ERROR MESSAGE  @D@@@-          J         PSG999            . AND RETUAK
)@@G@@RN    @]@@@-PSG035    . @[@@@-.     @C@@@-. IF DEBUG SET CLEAR NEWLY ACQAL
)@@G@@UIRED CORE TO -0. @[@@@-.     @B@@@-          ON        DEBUG           AM
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@-          OR,U      A0,0777           . LAST AVAIL ADDRESS IAN
)@@G@@N A1  @F@@@-          LXI,U     A0,1              . POINTER TO CORE TO CAO
)@@G@@LEAR  @E@@@-          LN,U      A3,0              . GET -0 TO STORE     AP
)@@G@@@]@@@-PSG040    . @C@@@-          S         A3,0,A0           . STORE -0AQ
)@@G@@@E@@@-          TLEM,U    A0,0,A1           . OFF THE END YET     @E@@@-AR
)@@G@@          J         PSG040            . NO - STORE AGAIN    @F@@@-.     AS
)@@G@@    L         A0,FIBSIZ+MAXINX  . FIND LAST ADDRESS NEEDED  @F@@@-      AT
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,MAXINX         . RESTORE MAX SIZE BUFFER   @F@@@-      AU
)@@G@@    L         A0,FIBSIZ,A0      . FIND LAST ADDRESS NEEDED  @D@@@-      AV
)@@G@@    A         A0,M$PSGNXT       . RESTORE A0 AS @B@@@-          OFF     AW
)@@G@@  DEBUG             .   @[@@@-.     @B@@@-. SET UP DUMMY CONTROL WORD ASAX
)@@G@@ ASSIGNED.  @[@@@-.     @D@@@-          L,U       R1,1              . SEAY
)@@G@@T CTLFRE    @D@@@-          S         R1,CTLFRE,A0      . IN DUMMY WORD AZ
)@@G@@@D@@@-          A,U       A0,1              . SET NEXT AVAIL@F@@@-      BA
)@@G@@    L         A1,M$PSGNXT       . BUT LOAD NEW BUFFER FIRST @D@@@-      BB
)@@G@@    S         A0,M$PSGNXT       . SAVE NEW AVAIL@F@@@-          SZ      BC
)@@G@@  0,A1              . CLEAR NEW CONTROL WORD    @E@@@-          L,U     BD
)@@G@@  R1,060            . SET CONTROL BITS    @B@@@-          S         R1,CBE
)@@G@@TLBIT,A1      .   @G@@@-          L,U       A0,MAXINX         . SET SIZEBF
)@@G@@ INDEX FOR NEW BUFFER   @[@@@-.     @F@@@-. A0 IS SIZE KEY A1 IS ADDRESSBG
)@@G@@ OF UNLINKED BUFFER.  IF NECESSARY  @F@@@-. SPLIT IT AND RETURN THE UNUSBH
)@@G@@ED PART TO FREE STOREAGE.  CONTINUE @A@@@-. UNTIL WE HAVE ONE OF DESIREDBI
)@@G@@ SIZE.@[@@@-.     @]@@@-PSG050    . @E@@@-          TE        A0,PSGTMP BJ
)@@G@@        . IS THIS RIGHT SIZE  @E@@@-          TNE,U     A0,MININX+1     BK
)@@G@@  . OR NEXT TO SMALLEST @F@@@-          J         PSG060            . YEBL
)@@G@@S - RETURN IT TO CALLER @[@@@-.     @F@@@-. SPLITTING THE BUFFER.  BUILDBM
)@@G@@ BIG (LEFT) BUDDY CONTROL WORD.     @[@@@-.     @D@@@-          AN,U    BN
)@@G@@  A0,1              . NEXT SIZE DOWN@E@@@-          S         A0,CTLINX,BO
)@@G@@A1      . SET CONTROL INDEX   @E@@@-          L         A2,0,A1         BP
)@@G@@  . GET OLD CONTROL BITS@B@@@-          L,U       R1,040            .   BQ
)@@G@@@B@@@-          JP        A2,$+2            .   @B@@@-          L,U     BR
)@@G@@  R1,060            .   @E@@@-          S         R1,CTLBIT,A1      . SEBS
)@@G@@T CONTROL BITS    @[@@@-.     @B@@@-. BUILD LITTLE (RIGHT) BUDDY CONTROLBT
)@@G@@ WORD.@[@@@-.     @F@@@-          A         A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . MOVE TO BU
)@@G@@BUFFER ADDRESS    @F@@@-          SZ        0,A1              . CLEAR BUBV
)@@G@@FFER CONTROL WORD @D@@@-          AN,U      A0,1              . NEXT SIZBW
)@@G@@E DOWN@E@@@-          S         A0,CTLINX,A1      . SET CONTROL INDEX   BX
)@@G@@@D@@@-          LSSL      A2,1              . ISOLATE BIT   @B@@@-      BY
)@@G@@    SSL       A2,31             .   @G@@@-          S         A2,CTLBIT,BZ
)@@G@@A1      . SET LITTLE BUDDY CONTROL BITS   @E@@@-          LMJ       X11,CA
)@@G@@LINK          . LINK LITTLE BUDDY IN@[@@@-.     @F@@@-. POINT AT BIG BUDCB
)@@G@@DY AND LOOP UNTIL WE HAVE ONE THE USER WANTS.   @[@@@-.     @E@@@-      CC
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,1              . BIG BUDDY INDEX     @D@@@-          ANCD
)@@G@@        A1,FIBSIZ,A0      . BUFFER ADDRESS@C@@@-          J         PSG0CE
)@@G@@50            . AND LOOP@[@@@-.     @F@@@-. A0 HAS SIZE KEY AND A1 ADDRECF
)@@G@@SS OF BUFFER TO RETURN TO USER.     @[@@@-.     @]@@@-PSG060    . @B@@@-CG
)@@G@@          ON        DEBUG             .   @F@@@-          L         R1,PCH
)@@G@@SGLNK         . SET ADDRESS OF CALLER     @F@@@-          S,H2      R1,0CI
)@@G@@,A1           . INTO H2 OF CONTROL WORD   @B@@@-          OFF       DEBUCJ
)@@G@@G             .   @[@@@-.     @F@@@-          S         A0,CTLFRE,A1    CK

)@@G@@  . GET ACTUAL BUFFER LENGTH TOO    @F@@@-          AU,U      A1,1      CM

)@@G@@        . SET INCREMENT @H@@@-          AH        A1,(-1,1)         . MACO

)@@G@@A0      . GET BUFFER LENGTH   @G@@@-          AN,U      A3,2            CQ
)@@G@@  . ACCOUNT FOR JGD AND CNTROL WORD @E@@@-          SZ        0,*A2     CR

)@@G@@K ITS BUDDY NOW   @[@@@-/.    @[@@@-.     @E@@@-. THE BUDDY TO THIS BUFFEN
)@@G@@ER IS NOT AVAILABLE.  CLEAR IT.     @[@@@-.     @]@@@-REL040    . @D@@@-EO

)@@G@@        DEBUG             . CLEAR IT@E@@@-          AU,U      A1,1      EQ

)@@G@@    OFF       DEBUG             . CLEAR IT@[@@@-.     @A@@@-. CHAIN IT IEY
)@@G@@N TO FREE STOREAGE POOL.@[@@@-.     @E@@@-          SZ        CTLFRE,A1 EZ
)@@G@@        . MARK BUFFER AS FREE @F@@@-          LMJ       X11,LINK        FA
)@@G@@  . LINK IT INTO FREESTORE    @E@@@-          L,U       A5,0            FB

)@@G@@SGSAV         . RECOVER REGISTERS   @E@@@-          L         X11,PSGLNKFD

)@@G@@  . RETURN TO USER@[@@@-.     @F@@@-. LINK BUFFER IN A1 INTO STORAGE POOFF
)@@G@@L OF A0 SIZE.  DESTROYS A2 A3.@[@@@-.     @]@@@-LINK      . @F@@@-      FG
)@@G@@    L,U       A2,FRELNK-1,A0    . GET ADDRESS FOR BACKLINK  @F@@@-      FH
)@@G@@    L         A3,FRELNK,A0      . GET FORWARD ADDRESS TOO   @H@@@-      FI
)@@G@@    S         A2,BL,A1          . SET BACK LINK TO POINT TO FREE ARRAY  FJ
)@@G@@@G@@@-          S         A3,FL,A1          . SET FORWARD LINK TO OLD FIFK
)@@G@@RST   @F@@@-          S         A1,FL,A2          . SET THIS BUFFER AS FFL

)@@G@@@G@@@-          S         A1,BL,A3          . ELSE SET BACKLINK OF FORWAFN
)@@G@@RD    @D@@@-          J         0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@-FO
)@@G@@.     @E@@@-. UNLINK BUFFER IN A1 FROM ITS CHAIN.  A2 AND A3 DESTROYED. FP
)@@G@@@[@@@-.     @]@@@-UNLINK    . @E@@@-          L         A2,BL,A1        FQ
)@@G@@  . GET PREVIOUS BUFFER @F@@@-          L         A3,FL,A1          . GEFR

)@@G@@        . AND IF NEXT THEN    @E@@@-          S         A2,BL,A3        FU
)@@G@@  . POINT NEXT AT PREV  @D@@@-          J         0,X11             . ANFV
)@@G@@D RETURN    @[@@@-.     @C@@@-PSGLNK    VAR       'PSGLNK',1        . LIFW
)@@G@@NK    @D@@@-PSGSAV    VAR       'PSGSAV',2        . SAVE FOR A2 A3@G@@@-FX

)@@G@@ ATTEMPTED.' .    @B@@@-          ENDPCM                      .   @[@@@-GE

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          M$APROC                     .   @B@@@@      GI
)@@G@@    M$ADESCR                    .   @B@@@@          COMMON              GJ
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THIS MODULE CONTAINS THE DRIVER ROUTINESGK
)@@G@@ FOR DUMPING FROM THE BUFFER  @D@@@@. AND FOR DUMPING AN EXPRESSION IN AGL
)@@G@@RBITRARY FORMAT.  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THE GENERAL FORMAT OF BUFFER DUMPIGM
)@@G@@NG COMMANDS IS:   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         <FORMAT>  <START>,<LENGTH>GN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CONTROL PASSES HERE WITH A1 POINTING TO THE FOLLOWINGO
)@@G@@G FORMAT WORD:    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    -------------------------------GP
)@@G@@------------------------------@F@@@@.    : DBLFLG  : ASCFLG  : NUMPER  :GQ
)@@G@@     FORMATTING ROUTINE      :@F@@@@.    -------------------------------GR
)@@G@@------------------------------@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. DBLFLG - NONZ IF DOUBLGS
)@@G@@E PRECISION (FORCE WORD LENGTH TO BE EVEN).     @G@@@@. ASCFLG - NONZ IFGT
)@@G@@ OUTPUT IS TO BE ASCII (OPEN EDIT$ IN ASCII MODE).    @F@@@@. NUMPER - NGU
)@@G@@UMBER (MINUS ONE) OF ITEMS TO BE EDITED ON EACH LINE. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@GV
)@@G@@. WORD TO BE DUMPED IS PASSED TO FORMATTING ROUTINE IN A0.  @D@@@@. CALLGW
)@@G@@ OF ROUTINE IS ON X11 WITH RETURN TO 0,X11.     @D@@@@. THERE IS *NO* ERGX
)@@G@@ROR RETURN ON FORMATTING ROUTINES.  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DMPBUFGY
)@@G@@*   . @E@@@@          S         X11,DDRLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS GZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         A1,0,A1           . GET FORMAT WORD     @E@@@@HA
)@@G@@          S         A1,DMPFMT         . SET DUMP FORMAT     @G@@@@      HB
)@@G@@    SZ        DMPFLG            . CLEAR DOUBLE PRECISION FLAG     @F@@@@HC
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,M$SCANEXPR    . GET PARAMETERS FOR DUMPING@C@@@@HD
)@@G@@          JNZ       A5,DBF999         . ERROR   @E@@@@          TNE,U   HE
)@@G@@  A0,MODNUL         . BARE DUMP COMMAND   @G@@@@          J         DBF0HF
)@@G@@10            . YES - USE PARAMS FROM LAST TIME @G@@@@          JZ      HG
)@@G@@  A2,DBF010         . NULL VECTOR - USE FROM LAST TIME@E@@@@          L,HH
)@@G@@U       A0,CSDESC         . ELSE GET DESCRIPTOR @E@@@@          LMJ     HI
)@@G@@  X11,M$CONVINT     . CONVERT TO INTEGER  @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,DHJ
)@@G@@BF999         . ERROR   @E@@@@          DL        A0,0,A1           . GEHK
)@@G@@T DUMP PARAMETERS @F@@@@          TLE,U     A2,2              . WERE AT HL
)@@G@@LEAST TWO GIVEN   @F@@@@          L,U       A1,1              . NO - SETHM
)@@G@@ SECOND TO ONE    @F@@@@          AN,U      A0,1              . MAKE FIRHN
)@@G@@ST ZERO-ORIGIN    @F@@@@          DS        A0,DMPARG         . SAVE ARGHO
)@@G@@S FOR NEXT TIME   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF NOTHING GIVEN FOR <START>,<LENGHP
)@@G@@TH> MOST RECENT PARAMETERS ARE@D@@@@. PICKED UP FROM DMPARG HERE.  CHECKHQ
)@@G@@ START AND LENGTH.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@DBF010    . @E@@@@          DL      HR
)@@G@@  A0,DMPARG         . GET ARGS FOR DUMPING@F@@@@          JN        A0,DHS
)@@G@@BF900         . START MUST BE POSITIVE    @G@@@@          TG        A0,BHT
)@@G@@UFWDS         . START MUST BE WITHIN BUFFER     @E@@@@          J       HU
)@@G@@  DBF900            . NOPE, DONT DO IT    @F@@@@          JNB       A1,DHV
)@@G@@BF020         . IF LENGTH EVEN SKIP THIS  @G@@@@          TZ,S1     DMPFHW
)@@G@@MT            . IS IT DOUBLE PRECISION FORMAT   @F@@@@          A,U     HX
)@@G@@  A1,1              . YES - ROUND UP TO DOUBLE  @E@@@@          S       HY
)@@G@@  A1,DMPARG+1       . SET ROUNDED LENGTH  @[@@@@/.    @^@@@@. (NOTE FALLHZ
)@@G@@-THRU).     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DUMP AREA DEFINED BY DMPARG+0 AND DMPARGIA
)@@G@@+1.  IF THIS EXCEEDS THE@G@@@@. CURRENT BUFFER, DUMP THE PART IN THE CURIB
)@@G@@RENT BUFFER AND LOOP BACK.    @D@@@@. IF IT IS ALL IN THE BUFFER, DBF040IC
)@@G@@ DUMPS IT ALL.    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DBF020    . @F@@@@          L       ID
)@@G@@  A1,BUFWDS         . GET NUMBER OF WORDS WE GOT@F@@@@          AN      IE
)@@G@@  A1,DMPARG+0       . SUBTRACT OFF START ADDRES @E@@@@          ANU     IF
)@@G@@  A1,DMPARG+1       . SUBTRACT OFF LENGTH @F@@@@          JP        A2,DIG
)@@G@@BF040         . IF WITHIN BUFFER DUMP IT  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. START-COUNIH
)@@G@@T OVERFLOWS BUFFER.  IF NOT INHIBITED DUMP THE PORTION IN   @G@@@@. THE II
)@@G@@CURRENT BUFFER, THEN READ NEXT BUFFER AND REVERT TO CASE ONE.     @[@@@@IJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@          TZ        NOMORE            . IS READING INHIBITEDIK
)@@G@@?     @E@@@@          J         DBF900            . YES - GIVE ERROR    IL
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A2,DMPARG+1       . SUBTRACT AMOUNT WE ARE    IM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          AN,U      A2,0,A1           . ABOUT TO DO FROM TOTAL    IN
)@@G@@@E@@@@          S         A2,DMPARG+1       . NUMBER TO BE DONE   @G@@@@IO
)@@G@@          L         A0,DMPARG+0       . GET BASE ADDRESS FOR THIS PART  IP
)@@G@@@G@@@@          A         A0,BUFADR         . MAKE CORE ADDRESS FOR DUMPIQ
)@@G@@ER    @H@@@@          SZ        DMPARG+0          . CLEAR BASE ADDRESS FIR
)@@G@@OR NEXT BUFFER    @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,DUMPER        . DUMP PARIS
)@@G@@T IN THIS BUFFER  @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,DBF999         . ERROR   IT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,NEXTSECT      . GET TO NEXT BUIU
)@@G@@FFER  @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,DBF999         . ERROR   @E@@@@      IV
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,GETSECTOR     . READ NEXT BUFFER    @C@@@@          JNIW
)@@G@@Z       A5,DBF999         . ERROR   @E@[@@          TNZ       NOMSG     IX
)@@G@@        . UNLESS INHIBITED    @E@@@[          TNZ       M$BRIEF         IY
)@@G@@  . UNLESS INHIBITED    @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,CWHERE        . PRIZ
)@@G@@INT SECTOR ADDRESS@E@@@@          J         DBF020            . AND CONTJA
)@@G@@INUE DUMPING@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. <START> AND <LENGTH> TOTALLY WITHIN CURRJB
)@@G@@ENT BUFFER. @E@@@@. A SINGLE CALL TO DUMPER SUFFICES TO COMPLETE THE DUMJC
)@@G@@P.    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@DBF040    . @F@@@@          DL        A0,DMPARG JD
)@@G@@        . GET ARGUMENTS TO DUMP     @F@@@@          A         A0,BUFADR JE
)@@G@@        . ADD ADDRESS OF BUFFER     @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,DUMPERJF
)@@G@@        . DUMP THE LAST PORTION     @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,DBF999 JG
)@@G@@        . ERROR   @C@@@@          J         DBF999            . RETURN  JH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. <START> AND <LENGTH> OUTSIDE OF CURRENT BUFFER AND AJI
)@@G@@UTOMATIC    @E@@@@. CONTINUATION READ INHIBITED BY NONZ IN NOMORE.  EDITJJ
)@@G@@ THE  @A@@@@. UBIQUITOUS "OUT OF RANGE" MESSAGE.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@DBF900JK
)@@G@@    . @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,EDOUTR        . EDIT OUT-OF-RANGE MEJL
)@@G@@SSAGE @]@@@@DBF999    . @F@@@@          L         X11,DDRLNK        . REJM
)@@G@@STORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@@          J         0,X11             . REJN
)@@G@@TURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. "VIRTUAL" DUMPING - DUJO
)@@G@@MP EXPRESSION IN ARBITRARY FORMAT.  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         V<FORMATJP
)@@G@@> <EXPRESSION>    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. CONTROL PASSES HERE WITH A1 POINTIJQ
)@@G@@NG TO FORMAT WORD (SEE ABOVE).@[@@@@.     @]@@@@DMPVAR*   . @E@@@@      JR
)@@G@@    S         X11,DDRLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@@          L JS
)@@G@@        A1,0,A1           . PICK UP FORMAT WORD @E@@@@          S       JT
)@@G@@  A1,DMPFMT         . SAVE FORMAT WORD    @G@@@@          SZ        DMPFJU
)@@G@@LG            . CLEAR DOUBLE PRECISION FLAG     @F@@@@          LMJ     JV
)@@G@@  X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN EXPRESSION TO DUMP   @C@@@@          JNZ     JW
)@@G@@  A5,DVA999         . ERROR   @D@@@@          L,U       A0,CSDESC       JX
)@@G@@  . GET DESCRIPTOR@F@@@@          LMJ       X11,M$ITEMLENGTH  . COMPUTE JY
)@@G@@LENGTH IN WORDS   @C@@@@          JNZ       A5,DVA999         . ERROR   JZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DSL       A0,36             . MOVE COUNT TO A1    @E@@@@KA
)@@G@@          JNB       A1,DVA010         . IF EVEN SKIP THIS   @E@@@@      KB
)@@G@@    TZ,S1     DMPFMT            . IF DOUBLE PRECISION @D@@@@          A,KC
)@@G@@U       A1,1              . ROUND IT UP   @]@@@@DVA010    . @F@@@@      KD
)@@G@@    L         A0,CSADDR         . GET ADDRESS OF THE DATA   @E@@@@      KE
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,DUMPER        . CALL THE DUMPER     @]@@@@DVA999    . KF
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         X11,DDRLNK        . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    KG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@KH
)@@G@@/.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. MAIN ROUTINE FOR DUMPING.   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@KI
)@@G@@. DMPFMT CONTAINS FORMAT WORD TO CONTROL THE DUMP.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@KJ
)@@G@@.         L         A0,<COREADDR>     . CORE ADDRESS OF DATA TO DUMP    KK
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         L         A1,<NUMMWRDS>     . NUMBER OF WORDS TO DUMP   KL
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         LMJ       X11,DUMPER        . PERFORM DUMPING     @B@@@@KM
)@@G@@.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>        .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ERROR RETUKN
)@@G@@RN TAKEN IF REMOTE BREAK (@@X C) DETECTED DURING DUMP.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@KO
)@@G@@DUMPER    . @E@@@@          S         X11,DMPLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADKP
)@@G@@DRESS @F@@@@          DS        A6,DMPSAV         . SAVE MAJOR-SET REGISKQ
)@@G@@TERS  @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1              . SET INCREMENT FOR FEKR
)@@G@@TCH   @E@@@@          S         A0,DMPPTR         . SAVE DUMP POINTER   KS
)@@G@@@D@@@@          L,U       A6,0,A1           . GET WORD COUNT@E@@@@      KT
)@@G@@    JZ        A6,DMP100         . IF NONE GET OUT NOW @]@@@@DMP010    . KU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L         A5,M$BREAK        . CHECK REMOTE BREAK FLAG   KV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          JNZ       A5,DMP999         . IF BREAK, GET OUT   @F@@@@KW
)@@G@@          L,S2      A2,DMPFMT         . GET ASCII-OUTPUT FLAG     @F@@@@KX
)@@G@@          E$OPENX   M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDITING FOR DUMPING  @F@@@@KY
)@@G@@          L,S3      A7,DMPFMT         . LOAD NUM WORDS PER LINE   @]@@@@KZ
)@@G@@DMP020    . @E@@@@          DL        A1,DMPPTR         . GET POINTER TOLA
)@@G@@ CORE @F@@@@          L         A0,0,*A1          . GET NEXT WORD TO DUMLB
)@@G@@P     @E@@@@          S,H2      A1,DMPPTR         . SAVE UPDATED POINTERLC
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LMJ       X11,0,A2          . CALL DUMPER   @D@@@@      LD
)@@G@@    E$SKIP    1                 . SKIP ONE SPACE@F@@@@          AN,U    LE
)@@G@@  A6,1              . SUBTRACT FROM TOTAL COUNT @E@@@@          JZ      LF
)@@G@@  A6,$+2            . IF STILL MORE TO DO @E@@@@          JGD       A7,DLG
)@@G@@MP020         . COUNT ITEMS PER LINE@F@@@@          E$PRTX              LH
)@@G@@        . CLOSE EDITING AND PRINT   @E@@@@          JNZ       A6,DMP010 LI
)@@G@@        . IF MORE GO DO THEM  @]@@@@DMP100    . @E@@@@          L,U     LJ
)@@G@@  A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @]@@@@DMP999    . @F@@@@      LK

)@@G@@OF TEMP DATA STACK@[@@@@.     @F@@@@NSLEVL*   EQU       2               RD

)@@G@@              . STRING SUPPORT LEVEL@[@@@@.     @F@@@@LETAT*    EQU     RF

)@@G@@NYTHING ABOVE THIS POINT IS CHANGED THE ENTIRE MACRO  @D@@@@. PACKAGE SHRJ
)@@G@@OULD BE RECOMPILED DUE TO SOME CODE BEING @B@@@@. TURNED OFF OR ON BY THRK
)@@G@@E ABOVE EQUATES.  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF ANYTHING BELOW THIS POINT IS CHRL
)@@G@@ANGED ONLY THE ELEMENT  @ @@@@. M$TABLE NEED BE RECOMPILED. @[@@@@.     RM

)@@G@@CHED  @G@@@@. FOR A MACRO WHICH HAS NO FILENAME ASSOCIATED.  THE 'E' ANDRO

)@@G@@ALLED @C@@@@.                WHEN THE COMMAND IS GIVEN.     @D@@@@.     RY
)@@G@@  PARAM    IS A PARAMETER PASSED TO THE CALLED  @A@@@@.                RRZ

)@@G@@RROR MESSAGE (ERROR RETURN).  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IN THIS CASE THE CURRESF

)@@G@@CALL AND TRACE MACRO    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                 WB
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPILED COMMANDS ARE DEFINED HERE.  THEWC
)@@G@@ TABLE ENTRY FORMAT IS :@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         COM       'NAME  ',RWD
)@@G@@OUTINE,COMPILE  . @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. WHERE 'NAME  ' IS THE NAME OF THE WE
)@@G@@COMMAND     @D@@@@.       ROUTINE  IS A PROCESSING ROUTINE TO BE CALLED WF
)@@G@@@C@@@@.                WHEN THE COMMAND IS GIVEN.     @E@@@@.       COMPWG
)@@G@@ILE  IS A ROUTINE TO BE CALLED WHEN COMPILING   @D@@@@.                AWH
)@@G@@ MACRO WHEN THE COMMAND IS SEEN.    @B@@@@M$CCMP*   PROC                WI
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. THE FOLLOWING COMMANDS ARE PROVIDED BY MWJ
)@@G@@ACRO. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          COM       'ELSE  ',M$COMELSE,M$CMPELSEWK
)@@G@@     .@D@@@@          COM       'ENDIF ',M$COMENDIF,M$CMPENDIF   .@D@@@@WL
)@@G@@          COM       'ENDREP',M$COMLOOP,M$CMPLOOP     .@D@@@@          COWM
)@@G@@M       'IF    ',M$COMIF,M$CMPIF         .@G@@@@          COM       'LOOWN
)@@G@@P  ',M$COMLOOP,M$CMPLOOP     . $$$ TO BE REMOVED@D@@@@          COM     WO
)@@G@@  'MACRO ',M$COMMACRO,M$CMPMACRO   .@D@@@@          COM       'REPEAT',MWP
)@@G@@$COMREPEAT,M$CMPREPEAT .@D@@@@          COM       'UNTIL ',M$COMUNTIL,M$WQ
)@@G@@CMPUNTIL   .@D@@@@          COM       'WHILE ',M$COMWHILE,M$CMPWHILE   .WR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@/.    WS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. OPERATORS TO BE RECOGNIZED BY THE SCANNER ARE CODED WT
)@@G@@HERE.  IF   @G@@@@. A SPECIAL OPERATOR IS NEEDED, IT CAN BE ADDED TO THEWU
)@@G@@SE TABLES AND     @E@@@@. A PROCESSING ROUTINE WRITTED FOR IT.  THE FORMWV
)@@G@@AT IS :     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         OPR       PRIORITY,'SYMBOL',ROUTWW
)@@G@@INE  .@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PRIORITY IS AN INTEGER IN THE RANGE 2-63.  (1 WX
)@@G@@AND 0 ARE USED    @E@@@@. INTERNALLY).  THE HIGHER PRIORITY OPERATIONS AWY
)@@G@@RE EXECUTED @G@@@@. FIRST.  WHEN THE SCANNER'S OPERATOR PRECEDENCE ROUTIWZ
)@@G@@NE DECIDES TO     @E@@@@. PROCESS THE OPERATOR THE ROUTINE WILL RECEIVE XA
)@@G@@CONTROL WITH@E@@@@. STKPTR POINTING TO STACK ENTRIES.  THE DESCRIPTOR 'LXB
)@@G@@ADESC'@G@@@@. WILL CONTAIN A DESCRIPTOR FOR THE LEFTARG AND 'RADESC' WILXC
)@@G@@L CONTAIN   @F@@@@. A DESCRIPTOR FOR THE RIGHTARG.  THE RESULT SHOULD BEXD
)@@G@@ LEFT IN THE@G@@@@. LEFTARG AND THE STACK POPPED TWO.  OPERATOR ROUTINESXE
)@@G@@ ARE RESTRICTED   @F@@@@. TO THE MINOR SET AND X9 AND X10 AT PRESENT.  OXF
)@@G@@PERATORS SHOULD   @E@@@@. RETURN TO 0,X11 WITH A5 EITHER ZERO OR A PRINTXG
)@@G@@ CONTROL    @A@@@@. WORD FOR A FIELDATA ERROR MESSAGE.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@XH
)@@G@@. OPERATORS WITH A SINGLE CHARACTER GRAPHIC GO INTO THIS TABLE.   @[@@@@XI
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@M$ASOP*   PROC                        .   @D@@@@          OPXJ
)@@G@@R       58,'@',M$OPERAT  . CORE DUMPING   @D@@@@          OPR       55,'XK
)@@G@@#',M$OPERREPLIC . REPLICATION @C@@@@          OPR       50,'*',M$OPERMULXL
)@@G@@T . MULTIPLY@C@@@@          OPR       50,'/',M$OPERDIVIDE . DIVIDE@C@@@@XM
)@@G@@          OPR       45,'+',M$OPERADD  . ADD     @C@@@@          OPR     XN
)@@G@@  45,'-',M$OPERSUB  . SUBTRACT@E@@@@          OPR       30,'=',M$OPEREQUXO
)@@G@@ALS . COMPARE EQUALS    @E@@@@          OPR       30,'>',M$OPERGRTR . COXP
)@@G@@MPARE GREATER     @E@@@@          OPR       30,'<',M$OPERLESS . COMPARE XQ
)@@G@@LESS THAN   @D@@@@          OPR       05,',',M$OPERCATEN . CATENATION   XR
)@@G@@@G@@@@          OPR       04,' ',DYFINS     . BLANK OPERATOR IS INSTRUCTXS
)@@G@@ION   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XT
)@@G@@. OPERATORS WITH A DOUBLE CHARACTER GRAPHIC IN THIS TABLE.  @[@@@@.     XU
)@@G@@@B@@@@M$ADOP*   PROC                        .   @D@@@@          OPR     XV
)@@G@@  40,'**',M$OPERBITAND . BITWISE AND@F@@@@          OPR       35,'++',M$XW
)@@G@@OPERBITOR . BITWISE INCLUSIVE OR    @F@@@@          OPR       35,'--',M$XX
)@@G@@OPERBITXOR . BITWISE EXCLUSIVE OR   @F@@@@          OPR       30,'<=',M$XY
)@@G@@OPERLESSEQ . COMPARE LESS OR EQUAL  @G@@@@          OPR       30,'>=',M$XZ
)@@G@@OPERGRTREQ . COMPARE GREATER OR EQUAL     @E@@@@          OPR       30,'YA
)@@G@@<>',M$OPERNOTEQ . COMPARE NOT EQUAL @B@@@@          END                 YB
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. HERE ARE DEFINED ROUTINES TOYC

)@@G@@E.  ANY ROUTINES MUST TAKE SYMBOL NAME IN @G@@@@. A0-A1. IF THE SYMBOL IYE
)@@G@@S FOUND THE DESCRIPTOR FOR THE VALUE SHOULD     @F@@@@. BE PLACED IN A0-YF

)@@G@@@^@[@@@ADD CBC*MACRO.GETPROCS @^@@@[@ADD MACRO.GETPROCS     @]@@@@@COMPICZ

)@@G@@@COLLECT MAP/FILEDIT,FILEDIT  _@@@@@  . COMMON BANK DEFINITIONS   @F@@@@DB
)@@G@@@COPY,R SYS$*RLIB$.FIASG$/UOM         . FILE ASSIGN SUBROUTINE    @E@^@@DC
)@@G@@@COPY,R SYS$*RLIB$.INFOR*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IDD
)@@G@@S CALLED TO DEFINE THOSE MODES WHICH ARE  @F@@@@. DEPENDANT ON SUPPORT LDE
)@@G@@EVEL PARAMETERS.  ALSO DEFINED HERE ARE   @F@@@@. ON/OFF CONTROL PROCEDUDF
)@@G@@RES AND THE CONDITIONAL DOUBLE LOAD/STORE @#@@@@. PROCEDURES.     @[@@@@DG
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          DEF                         .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DH
)@@G@@. THIS KLUGE IS USED TO GET SYMBOL TABLE ENTRIES FOR THE DOUBLE   @F@@@@DI
)@@G@@. LOAD AND STORE AND SINGLE LOAD AND STORE INSTRUCTIONS BUILT SO  @B@@@@DJ
)@@G@@. THAT THE LATER EQUS PERFORM PROPERLY.   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@KLUGE1    EQDK
)@@G@@U       +(LA A0,0)        .   @B@@@@KLUGE2    EQU       +(SA A0,0)      DL
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@KLUGE3    EQU       +(DL A0,0)        .   @B@@@@KLUGE4    EQDM
)@@G@@U       +(DS A0,0)        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@M$AMODES* PROC          DN
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          M$CPAR                    DO
)@@G@@  . GET NSLEVL AND SSLEVL     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NSLEVL*   EQU       NSLEDP
)@@G@@VL            . EXTERNALIZE TO OUR CALLERS@F@@@@SSLEVL*   EQU       SSLEDQ
)@@G@@VL            . EXTERNALIZE TO OUR CALLERS@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. DEPENDING DR
)@@G@@ON THE VALUE OF NSLEVL (NUMERIC SUPPORT LEVEL). @[@@@@.     @H@@@@      DS
)@@G@@    ON        NSLEVL=0          . ONLY INTEGER ARITHMETIC SUPPORTED     DT
)@@G@@@F@@@@DON*      EQU       ON                . DISABLE DOUBLE PRECISION  DU
)@@G@@@B@@@@DOF*      EQU       OFF               .   @F@@@@FON*      EQU     DV
)@@G@@  ON                . DISABLE FLOATING POINT    @B@@@@FOF*      EQU     DW
)@@G@@  OFF               .   @D@@@@XDL*      EQU       LA                . SIDX
)@@G@@NGLE LOAD   @D@@@@XDS*      EQU       SA                . SINGLE STORE  DY
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OFF       NSLEVL=0          .   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@      DZ
)@@G@@    ON        NSLEVL=1          . INTEGER AND FLOATING POINT SUPPORTED  EA
)@@G@@@F@@@@DON*      EQU       ON                . DISABLE DOUBLE PRECISION  EB
)@@G@@@B@@@@DOF*      EQU       OFF               .   @F@@@@FON*      EQU     EC
)@@G@@  RES               . ENABLE FLOATING POINT     @B@@@@FOF*      EQU     ED
)@@G@@  RES               .   @D@@@@XDL*      EQU       LA                . SIEE
)@@G@@NGLE LOAD   @D@@@@XDS*      EQU       SA                . SINGLE STORE  EF
)@@G@@@E@@@@FLPBIT*   EQU       001               . FLOATING POINT BIT  @E@@@@EG
)@@G@@MODSFL*   EQU       FLPBIT            . SINGLE FLOATING MODE@B@@@@      EH
)@@G@@    OFF       NSLEVL=1          .   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          ON      EI
)@@G@@  NSLEVL=2          . INTEGER FLOATING DOUBLE ALL ALLOWED   @D@@@@DON*  EJ
)@@G@@    EQU       RES               . ENABLE DP CODE@B@@@@DOF*      EQU     EK
)@@G@@  RES               .   @D@@@@FON*      EQU       RES               . ENEL
)@@G@@ABLE FP CODE@B@@@@FOF*      EQU       RES               .   @D@@@@XDL*  EM
)@@G@@    EQU       DL                . DOUBLE LOAD   @D@@@@XDS*      EQU     EN
)@@G@@  DS                . SDOUBLE STORE @D@@@@FLPBIT*   EQU       001       EO
)@@G@@        . FLOATING POINT@E@@@@DBLBIT*   EQU       002               . DOEP
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION BIT@E@@@@MODSFL*   EQU       FLPBIT            . MODE SINEQ
)@@G@@GLE FLOATING@E@@@@MODDIN*   EQU       DBLBIT            . MODE DOUBLE INER
)@@G@@TEGER @E@@@@MODDFL*   EQU       FLPBIT++DBLBIT    . MODE DOUBLE FLOATINGES
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OFF       NSLEVL=2          .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. STRIET
)@@G@@NG SUPPORT LEVEL NOT YET DEFINED    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ALPBIT*   EQU     EU
)@@G@@  010               . ALPHA MODE BIT@E@@@@ASCBIT*   EQU       004       EV
)@@G@@        . ASCII STRING FLAG   @E@@@@MODALP*   EQU       ALPBIT          EW
)@@G@@  . MODE FIELDATA STRING@E@@@@MODASC*   EQU       ALPBIT++ASCBIT    . MOEX
)@@G@@DE ASCII STRING   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                       EY
)@@G@@  .   ___ PROC                        .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          M$EZ
)@@G@@CPAR                    *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE DFA
)@@G@@EFINES THE DESCRIPTORS ON THE OPERATOR STACK.   @F@@@@. EXTREME CARE MUSFB
)@@G@@T BE TAKEN TO ENSURE THAT THESE DEFINITIONS     @F@@@@. AGREE WITH THOSEFC
)@@G@@ OF DESCRIPTORS IN ELEMENT M$ADESC.  I WILL NOT @F@@@@. BE RESPONSIBLE IFD
)@@G@@F SOMEBODY CHANGES THEM, AS IN SEVERAL PLACES   @B@@@@. SUBROUTINES ARE FE

)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          M$CPAR                      . GEFG

)@@G@@T     @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. NO FILE NAME GIVEN.  IF ELEMENT NAME GIVEN USEPA
)@@G@@ AS FILE.   @[@@@P.     @F@@@P          L         A0,ENL            . GEPB
)@@G@@T LENGTH OF ELEMENT NAME@F@@@P          JZ        A0,FED050         . IFPC
)@@G@@ NONE, TREAD FOR FILE   @F@@@P          S         A0,FNL            . ELPD
)@@G@@SE SET FILE NAME LENGTH @E@@@P          DL        A0,ENAME          . MOPE
)@@G@@VE ELEMENT TO     @E@@@P          DS        A0,FNAME          . FILE NAMPF
)@@G@@E PORTION   @]@@@PFED010    . @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,GETOPT      PG
)@@G@@  . GET CORRECT OPTIONS @D@@@P          FIASG     ELT$,'RWO' INPUSE . ASPH
)@@G@@SIGN FILE   @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,SETUPIN       . SET UP INPUT FPI
)@@G@@ILE   @C@@@P          JNZ       A5,FED100         . ERROR   @F@@@P      PJ
)@@G@@    JZ        A4,FED050         . IF NO FILE TREAD FOR ONE  @F@@@P      PK
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,FILEREAD      . ELSE READ SECTOR ZERO     @E@@@P      PL
)@@G@@    JNZ       A5,FED100         . IF ERROR PRINT IT   @E@@@P/. ***** THIPM
)@@G@@S CODE OVERLAID WITH BUFFER AFTER SIGNON *****  @[@@@P.     @B@@@P. LOOKPN
)@@G@@ FOR SPEC2 WHICH IS AN OUTPUT FILE. @[@@@P.     @G@@@P          L,U     PO
)@@G@@  A0,02             . SEARCH FOR SPEC 2 (OUTPUT FILE) @D@@@P          LMPP
)@@G@@J       X11,SELT$         . LOOK FOR IT   @D@@@P          J         FED0PQ
)@@G@@60            . NO, CONTINUE  @E@@@P          TZ        ELT$            PR
)@@G@@  . WAS FILE NAME GIVEN @E@@@P          J         FED040            . YEPS
)@@G@@S - ASSIGN IT     @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. NO FILE NAME GIVEN.  IF ELEMENT NAPT
)@@G@@ME GIVEN USE AS FILE.   @[@@@P.     @F@@@P          L         A0,ENL    PU
)@@G@@        . GET LENGTH OF ELEMENT NAME@F@@@P          JZ        A0,FED060 PV
)@@G@@        . IF NONE, NO OUTPUT FILE   @F@@@P          S         A0,FNL    PW
)@@G@@        . ELSE SET FILE NAME LENGTH @E@@@P          DL        A0,ENAME  PX
)@@G@@        . MOVE ELEMENT TO     @E@@@P          DS        A0,FNAME        PY
)@@G@@  . FILE NAME PORTION   @]@@@PFED040    . @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,PZ
)@@G@@GETOPT        . GET CORRECT OPTIONS @D@@@P          FIASG     ELT$,'RWO'QA
)@@G@@ OUTUSE . ASSIGN FILE   @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,SETUPOT       . SEQB
)@@G@@T UP OUTPUT FILE  @E@@@P          J         FED100            . SKIP TREQC
)@@G@@AD CODE     @[@@@P.     @C@@@P. NO FILE NAME ON INFOR - ASK USER VIA TREQD
)@@G@@AD.   @[@@@P.     @]@@@PFED050    . @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,TREADIQE
)@@G@@N       . TREAD$ FILE NAME    @F@@@P          JNZ       A5,FED100       QF
)@@G@@  . IF NONZERO PRINT MESSAGE  @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,FILEREAD    QG
)@@G@@  . READ SECTOR ZERO    @F@@@P          J         FED100            . ANQH
)@@G@@D ENTER EXECUTION LOOP  @]@@@PFED060    . @E@@@P          L,U       A5,0QI
)@@G@@              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @E@@@P          J         FED100    QJ
)@@G@@        . AND ENTER FILEDIT   @[@@@P.     @B@T@PTITLE     'FILEDIT 11.5 QK
)@@G@@[&] &   &'    .   @B@@@TTITLE     'FILEDIT 11.6 [&] &   &'    .   @[@@@PQL
)@@G@@.     @A@@@P. ***** END OF OVERLAID CODE *****  @[@@@P.     @E@@@P      QM
)@@G@@    RES       MAXBUF-($-FEDBUF) . RES REST OF BUFFER  @[@@@P/.    @[@@@PQN
)@@G@@.     @E@@@P          INSTRS                      . INSTRUCTIONS FOLLOW QO
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @E@@@P. THIS IS THE MAIN EXECUTION LOOP.  COMMANDS ARE FETCHQP
)@@G@@ED AND@E@@@P. EXECUTED UNTIL THE USER INDICATES THAT HE WANTS TO STOP.  QQ
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @]@@@PFED100    . @F@@@P          JZ        A5,FED110       QR
)@@G@@  . IF NO ERROR ENTER LOOP    @E@@@P          PRINT     A5              QS
)@@G@@  . ELSE PRINT MESSAGE  @]@@@PFED110    . @D@@@P          LMJ       X11,QT
)@@G@@M$FETCH       . GET IMAGE     @D@@@P          JNZ       A5,FED110       QU
)@@G@@  . ON ERROR LOOP @E@@@P          JZ        A0,FED999         . IF EOF EQV
)@@G@@ND PROGRAM  @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,M$EXECUTE     . ELSE EXECUTE CQW
)@@G@@OMMAND@F@@@P          JNZ       A5,FED110         . IF ERROR PRINT LOCATQX
)@@G@@ION   @C@@@P          JZ        A0,FED110         . AND LOOP@[@@@P.     QY
)@@G@@@E@@@P. COME HERE WHEN END OF FILE ENCOUNTERED IN READ$ OR WHEN   @^@@@PQZ
)@@G@@. HE ASKS TO TERMINATE. @D@@@P. (NOTE FALL-THRU FROM A0<>0 RETURN OF M$ERA
)@@G@@XECUTE).    @[@@@P.     @]@@@PFED999    . @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,RB
)@@G@@FREEIN        . FREE INPUT FILE     @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,FREEOTRC
)@@G@@        . FREE OUTPUT FILE    @C@@@P          PRINT,U   ERRBYE          RD
)@@G@@  . PRINT IT@C@@@P          ER        EXIT$             . GO AWAY @[@@@PRE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@P. GET OPTIONS TO BE USED TO ASSIGN FILE.  @[@@@P.     @]@@@PRF
)@@G@@GETOPT*   . @F@@@P          L         A3,('A     ')     . NORMALLY USE ARG
)@@G@@ OPTION     @F@@@P          TZ        FLGQAS            . BUT IF Q OPTIORH
)@@G@@N FLAG ON   @E@@@P          LXI,U     A3,'AQ '          . USE Q OPTION ARI
)@@G@@LSO   @E@@@P          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    RJ
)@@G@@@[@@@P/.    @[@@@P.     @B@@@P. CHECK IO STATUS AND EDIT ERROR MESSAGE. RK
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @E@@@P.         L,U       A0,<IOPKT>        . PACKET ADDRESSRL
)@@G@@ IN A0@E@@@P.         LMJ       X11,IOCHECK       . CHECK IO STATUS     RM
)@@G@@@E@@@P.         JNZ       A5,<ERROR>        . BAD STATUS MESSAGE  @[@@@PRN
)@@G@@.     @F@@@P. NOTE IOBRIEF FLAG (FLGIOB) CAUSES THIS ROUTINE TO *IGNORE*RO
)@@G@@ BAD  @G@@@P. IO STATUSES, THEREFORE EVEN IF PKT+3,,S1 IS NONZ YOU CANNORP
)@@G@@T ASSUME    @A@@@P. THIS ROUTINE WILL RETURN A5 NONZ! @[@@@P.     @]@@@PRQ
)@@G@@IOCHECK*  . @F@@@P          DSL       A4,72             . CLEAR ERROR ANRR
)@@G@@D EOF FLAGS @E@@@P          TZ        IOSTAT,A0         . IF GOOD IO STARS
)@@G@@TUS   @E@@@P          TZ        FLGIOB            . OR IOBRIEF FLAG ON  RT
)@@G@@@E@@@P          J         IOC999            . DONT SAY ANYTHING   @E@@@PRU
)@@G@@          S         X11,IOCLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@P      RV
)@@G@@    S         X10,IOCSAV        . SAVE X REGISTER     @E@@@P          L,RW
)@@G@@U       X10,0,A0          . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @E@@@P          E$OPEN  RX
)@@G@@  M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . AND EDIT ERROR CODE @E@@@P          E$MSG     MSGIRY
)@@G@@OE            . IO ERROR MESSAGE    @E@@@P          E$OCTF    2,IOSTAT,XRZ
)@@G@@10      . EDIT THE I/O STATUS @D@@@P          E$MSGR                    SA
)@@G@@  . A LITTLE MORE @E@@@P          E$DECV    IOAWT,X10         . EDIT WORSB
)@@G@@DS READ     @B@@@P          E$MSGR                      .   @F@@@P      SC
)@@G@@    TNZ       IOAFC,X10         . IS THERE ABNORMAL FRAMES  @D@@@P      SD
)@@G@@    J         IOC040            . NO - SKIP EDIT@B@@@P          E$MSGR  SE
)@@G@@                    .   @F@@@P          E$DECV    IOAFC,X10         . EDSF
)@@G@@IT ABNORMAL FRAME COUNT @]@@@PIOC040    . @E@@@P          E$AXWX        SG
)@@G@@              . GET ACCESS WORD     @D@@@P          L         X10,IOCSAVSH
)@@G@@        . RESTORE X10   @E@@@P          L         X11,IOCLNK        . GESI
)@@G@@T RETURN ADDRESS  @]@@@PIOC999    . @C@@@P          J         0,X11     SJ
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @[@@@P.     @D@@@PIOCLNK    VAR       'IOCLNK',1      SK
)@@G@@  . RETURN ADDRESS@C@@@PIOCSAV    VAR       'IOCSAV',1        . SAVE X10SL
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @D@@@P. BUILD ERROR MESSAGE FOR WHEN WORD USER ASKS FOR     SM
)@@G@@@B@@@P. IS OUTSIDE OF RANGE OF CURRENT BUFFER.  @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. CASESN
)@@G@@ 1: BUFFER LENGTH ZERO: MESSAGE "BUFFER IS EMPTY".    @D@@@P. CASE 2: BUSO
)@@G@@FFER LENGTH NONZ: MESSAGE "OUT OF RANGE". @[@@@P.     @]@@@PEDOUTR*   . SP

)@@G@@DS            . EDIT # OF WORDS     @E@@@P          E$AXWX              SW

)@@G@@  X11,EORLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @E@@@P          J         0,X1SY

)@@G@@  'EORLNK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS@[@@@P/.    @[@@@P.     @C@@@P. ****TA
)@@G@@******  BEGIN FILEDIT COMMANDS  **********@[@@@P.     @H@@@PCOMLNK    VATB
)@@G@@R       'COMLNK',1        . RETURN ADDRESS FOR COMMAND HANDLERS   @G@@@PTC

)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @C@@@P. ******* ON/OFF COMMAND HANDLING  ********     @[@@@PTE
)@@G@@.     @C@@@P. PROC TO GENERATE TABLE:   ONFN  'NAME',<FLAG> @[@@@P.     TF
)@@G@@@E@@@PP         PROC      *1,2              . 1 FIELD, 2 WORDS    @B@@@PTG

)@@G@@  . INSTRUCTION TO SET FLAG   @D@@@P          END                       TJ
)@@G@@  . PROCEDURE ONFN@[@@@P.     @C@@@P. ******** THE ON-OFF NAME TABLE ***TK
)@@G@@*******     @[@@@P.     @]@@@PONFTAB    . @G@@@P          ONFN      'BRITL
)@@G@@EF ',M$BRIEF  . INHIBIT NORMAL INFO MESSAGES    @H@@@P          ONFN    TM

)@@G@@.     @E@@@PONFCTL    +         ($-ONFTAB)/2,ONFTAB . TABLE ACCESS WORD TQ
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @A@@@P. HANDLERS FOR ON AND OFF COMMANDS. @[@@@P.     @ @@@PTR
)@@G@@.         ON        <NAME>    @[@@@P.     @ @@@P.         OFF       <NAMTS
)@@G@@E>    @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. CONTROL PASSES HERE WITH (A1=0) FOR OFF AND (ATT
)@@G@@1=1) FOR ON.@[@@@P.     @]@@@PONOFF*    . @E@@@P          S         X11,TU
)@@G@@COMLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@P          S         A1,COMTMP TV

)@@G@@  . CALL SCANNER  @E@@@P          JNZ       A5,ONF999         . TAKE ERRTX
)@@G@@OR RETURN   @[@@@P.     @F@@@P          L         A5,ERRONF         . GETY
)@@G@@T MESSAGE IN CASE ERROR @D@@@P          TE,U      A0,MODNAM         . WATZ
)@@G@@S NAME LABEL@D@@@P          J         ONF999            . NO, ERROR     UA
)@@G@@@C@@@P          L         A0,0,A1           . GET WORD@F@@@P          TGUB
)@@G@@,U      A2,6+1            . LENGTH GREATER THAN SIX?  @G@@@P          L,UC
)@@G@@U       A2,6              . YES, USE FIRST SIX CHARS ONLY   @F@@@P      UD
)@@G@@    MTSE      A0,ONFCTL,2,0,A3 MSKTAB-1,A2 . SEARCH TABLE   @F@@@P      UE
)@@G@@    J         ONF999            . NOFIND - RETURN ERROR     @[@@@P.     UF
)@@G@@@C@@@P. A3 POINTS TO INSTRUCTION TO SET/CLEAR FLAG.   @[@@@P.     @F@@@PUG
)@@G@@          L         A4,COMTMP         . GET ONE OR ZERO TO SET    @E@@@PUH

)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@P/.    @[@@@PUL
)@@G@@.     @A@@@P. COMMAND TO PRINT OUT WHERE WE ARE.@D@@@P. (ALSO CALLED AS UM
)@@G@@SUBROUTINE BY MANY MANY PEOPLE).    @[@@@P.     @#@@@P.         WHERE   UN
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @G@@@P. IF NOMORE IS NONZ, IT IS PCW THAT DESCRIBES SPECIAL UO
)@@G@@BUFFER CONTENTS.  @F@@@P. ELSE IF INPUT FILE IS TAPE, FILE AND RECORD NUUP
)@@G@@MBERS ARE PRINTED.@E@@@P. ELSE (DISK FILE) SECTOR AND TRACK ADDRESS ARE UQ
)@@G@@PRINTED.    @[@@@P.     @]@@@PCWHERE*   . @E@@@P          S         X11,UR
)@@G@@WHELNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @F@@@P          L         A5,NOMORE US
)@@G@@        . DO WE HAVE SPECIAL PCW?   @E@@@P          JNZ       A5,WHE080 UT
)@@G@@        . YES, GO PRINT IT    @D@@@P          E$OPEN    M$EPKT M$IMAGE  UU
)@@G@@  . OPEN EDIT$    @D@@@P          TZ        INTAPE            . EDITING UV
)@@G@@TAPE? @E@@@P          J         WHE010            . YES, TELL ABOUT TAPEUW
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @B@@@P. DISK FILE: EDIT MASS-STORAGE ADDRESS.   @[@@@P.     UX
)@@G@@@E@@@P          E$MSG     MSGADR            . EDIT SECTOR ADDRESS @E@@@PUY
)@@G@@          E$DECV    INDADD            . EDIT DRUM ADDRESS   @B@@@P      UZ
)@@G@@    E$MSGR                      .   @E@@@P          L         A0,INDADD VA
)@@G@@        . GET SECTOR ADDRESS  @E@@@P          SSL       A0,6            VB
)@@G@@  . DIVIDE BY 64 = TRACK@E@@@P          E$DECV                      . EDVC
)@@G@@IT TRACK ADDRESS  @D@@@P          E$MSGR                      . MORE MESVD
)@@G@@SAGE  @D@@@P          J         WHE070            . AND CONTINUE  @[@@@PVE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@P. TAPE FILE: EDIT FILE AND RECORD NUMBERS.@[@@@P.     @]@@@PVF
)@@G@@WHE010    . @G@@@P          E$MSG     MSGTFR            . 'FILE X, RECORVG
)@@G@@D X, WORDS READ X'@E@@@P          E$DECV    FILNUM            . EDIT FILVH
)@@G@@ENUMBER     @B@@@P          E$MSGR                      .   @D@@@P      VI
)@@G@@    E$DECV    RECNUM            . RECORD NUMBER @B@@@P          E$MSGR  VJ
)@@G@@                    .   @E@@@P          E$DECV    BUFWDS            . NUVK

)@@G@@SAGE  @]@@@PWHE070    . @F@@@P          E$AXWX                      . MAVM
)@@G@@TERIALIZE ACCESS WORD   @]@@@PWHE080    . @E@@@P          PRINT     A5  VN
)@@G@@              . PRINT ACCESS WORD   @E@@@P          L,U       A5,0      VO
)@@G@@        . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @F@@@P          L         X11,WHELNK      VP
)@@G@@  . RESTORE RETURN ADDRESS    @E@@@P          J         0,X11           VQ
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@P.     @H@@@PWHELNK    VAR       'WHELNK',1VR
)@@G@@        . RETURN ADDRESS FOR 'WHERE' ROUTINE    @[@@@P/.    @[@@@P.     VS
)@@G@@@C@@@P. (SHUDDER) RELEASE CURRENT TRACK FROM FILE.    @[@@@P.     @#@@@PVT
)@@G@@.         REL     @[@@@P.     @E@@@P. REQUIRES VERIFICATION UNLESS RELBRVU
)@@G@@ FLAG HAS BEEN SET.     @[@@@P.     @]@@@PRELEASE*  . @E@@@P          S VV
)@@G@@        X11,COMLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @[@@@P.     @F@@@P. IF RVW

)@@G@@@F@@@P          TZ        FLGRLB            . IF REL BRIEF MODE IS ON   VY
)@@G@@@G@@@P          J         REL030            . SKIP VERIFICATION AND GO RVZ
)@@G@@ELEASE@[@@@P.     @C@@@P. ASK FOR VERIFICATION BEFORE RELEASING TRACK.  WA
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @D@@@P          E$OPEN    M$EPKT M$IMAGE    . OPEN EDIT$    WB

)@@G@@Z       A5,BCH999         . ERROR   @F@@@P          L         A4,2,A1   XZ

)@@G@@        . ERROR   @F@@@P          TG        A0,BUFWDS         . MUST BE YD
)@@G@@WITHIN BUFFER     @C@@@P          J         BCH900            . ERROR   YE
)@@G@@@G@@@P          L         A2,BUFWDS         . GET NUMBER OF WORDS WE HAVYF
)@@G@@E     @F@@@P          AN        A2,A1             . SUBTRACT LENGTH WE WYG
)@@G@@ILL DO@F@@@P          AN        A2,A0             . SUBTRACT ADDRESS WE YH
)@@G@@START @G@@@P          JN        A2,BCH900         . IF NEGATIVE IS OUT OYI
)@@G@@F RANGE     @E@@@P          A         A0,BUFADR         . GET CORE ADDREYJ
)@@G@@SS    @F@@@P          LXI,U     A0,1              . SET INCREMENT FOR STYK
)@@G@@ORE   @D@@@P          J         BCH020            . ENTER LOOP    @]@@@PYL
)@@G@@BCH010    . @D@@@P          S         A4,0,*A0          . SET NEW WORD  YM
)@@G@@@C@@@PBCH020    JGD       A1,BCH010         . AND LOOP@E@@@P          L,YN
)@@G@@U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @D@@@P          J       YO
)@@G@@  BCH999            . AND RETURN    @]@@@PBCH900    . @F@@@P          LMYP
)@@G@@J       X11,EDOUTR        . EDIT OUT-OF-RANGE MESSAGE @B@@@P          J YQ
)@@G@@        BCH999            .   @]@@@PBCH910    . @E@@@P          L       YR
)@@G@@  A5,ERRCHG         . GET ERROR MESSAGE   @]@@@PBCH999    . @E@@@P      YS
)@@G@@    L         X11,COMLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@P          J YT
)@@G@@        0,X11             . AND RETURN    @[@@@P/.    @[@@@P.     @C@@@PYU
)@@G@@. SET LENGTH OF FILE (FOR SEARCH COMMAND ONLY). @[@@@P.     @ @@@P.     YV
)@@G@@    LENGTH    <NTRACKS> @[@@@P.     @]@@@PLENGTH*   . @E@@@P          S YW
)@@G@@        X11,COMLNK        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@P          LMJ     YX
)@@G@@  X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCAN FOR ARGUMENT   @C@@@P          JNZ       A5,LYY
)@@G@@EN999         . ERROR   @D@@@P          JZ        A2,LEN900         . IFYZ
)@@G@@ NULL ERROR @C@@@P          TNE,U     A0,MODNUL         . IF NULL @C@@@PZA
)@@G@@          J         LEN900            . ERROR   @E@@@P          L,U     ZB
)@@G@@  A0,CSDESC         . GET DATA DESCRIPTOR @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,ZC
)@@G@@M$CONVINT     . CONVERT TO INTEGER  @C@@@P          JNZ       A5,LEN999 ZD
)@@G@@        . ERROR   @D@@@P          L         A0,0,A1           . GET DATAZE
)@@G@@ VALUE@E@@@P          JN        A0,LEN900         . IF NEGATIVE IS ERRORZF

)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,6              . TIMES 64 GIVES SECTOR ADDRESS   ZH
)@@G@@@D@@@P          S         A0,SEFLEN         . SAVE AS SIZE  @E@@@P      ZI
)@@G@@    L,U       A5,0              . CLEAR ERROR CODE    @E@@@P          J ZJ
)@@G@@        LEN999            . RETURN TO CALLER    @]@@@PLEN900    . @E@@@PZK

)@@G@@SS    @E@@@P          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    ZN
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @[@@@P.     @F@@@P. SET DESIRED RECORD LENGTH (AND ALSO CURRZO
)@@G@@ENT RECORD LENGTH!).    @[@@@P.     @ @@@P.         RLEN      <NWORDS>  ZP

)@@G@@  . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,M$SCANEXPR    . SCZR
)@@G@@AN FOR ARGUMENT   @C@@@P          JNZ       A5,SRL999         . ERROR   ZS
)@@G@@@D@@@P          JZ        A2,SRL900         . IF NULL ERROR @C@@@P      ZT
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,MODNUL         . IF NULL @C@@@P          J         SRL9ZU
)@@G@@00            . ERROR   @E@@@P          L,U       A0,CSDESC         . GEZV

)@@G@@TO INTEGER  @C@@@P          JNZ       A5,SRL999         . ERROR   @D@@@PZX
)@@G@@          L         A0,0,A1           . GET DATA VALUE@E@@@P          ANZY

)@@G@@  A1,SRL900         . IF NEG OR ZERO IS ERROR   @E@@@P          TG      AA

)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@0A@4BC2@O@@@@ 0)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)FR
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)FS
)@@G@@^@)^@0A@4BC2@O@@@@ 0) K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K%FT
)@@G@@ K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K% K%^@)^@0A@4BC2@O@@@@FU
)@@G@@ 0)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)FV
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@0A@4BC2_@@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)FW
)@@G@@^@)^@)^@)^@0A@4BC2@O@@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^- D1^^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)FX
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURES TO CALL FIASG$ AND FIFREE$ ROFY
)@@G@@UTINES.     @A@@@@. FIBITS WRITTEN BY MIKE MCAMIS     @A@@@@. FIASG  WRIFZ
)@@G@@TTEN BY ALAN STEBBENS   @A@@@@. FIFREE WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@GA
)@@G@@. FIPFIL WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPELT WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTGB
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. FIASG UPDATED TO WORK IN ASCII OR FIELDATA - 2GC
)@@G@@/11/76, AKS.@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         DEFINE BITS FOR FIASG$    @[@@@@GD
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          DEF                         .   @D@@@@FBIT      EQGE
)@@G@@U       001               . FORCE USE NAME@D@@@@UBIT      EQU       002 GF
)@@G@@              . USE NAME GIVEN@D@@@@XBIT      EQU       004             GG
)@@G@@  . GET ASG,AX    @E@@@@RBIT      EQU       010               . GET READGH
)@@G@@ PERMISSION @E@@@@WBIT      EQU       020               . GET WRITE PERMGI
)@@G@@ISSION@D@@@@OBIT      EQU       040               . OPTIONS IN A3 @B@@@@GJ
)@@G@@FIBITS*   PROC      0,0               .   @B@@@@          END           GK
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. TO ASSIGN A FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@GL
)@@G@@.         FIASG,'OPTS' PACKET,BITS NAME   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PRGM
)@@G@@OC      *2                .   @B@@@@FIASG*    NAME                      GN
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@N         EQU       6+3*(' '=040)     . # OF BITS PER CHAR  GO
)@@G@@@E@@@@C         EQU       077+0700*(N=9)    . SET PROPER MASK     @D@@@@GP
)@@G@@          ON        P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@GQ
)@@G@@. FUNCTION TO GET BIT FOR 'BITS' LETTER.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@F         FUGR
)@@G@@NC      *                 .   @B@@@@PBIT*     NAME                      GS
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@I         DO      6 , DO M(0)*/(N-N*I)**C=F(1) , END F(2)   GT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          END       +0                . STRANGE BITS  @[@@@@.     GU
)@@G@@@E@@@@M(0)      EQU       P(1,2)+0D         . PICK UP MODE LETTERS@F@@@@GV
)@@G@@B(0)      EQU       PBIT('F',1)+PBIT('U',2)+PBIT('X',4)+; F,U,X   @F@@@@GW
)@@G@@                    PBIT('R',8)+PBIT('W',16)+PBIT('O',32)++; R,W,O@G@@@@GX
)@@G@@                    2*(P(2)>0)+32*(P(0)>1) . FORCE BITS IF NECESSARY    GY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. NOW GENERATE CODE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LAGZ
)@@G@@,U      A0,P(1,1)         .   @B@@@@          DO (B(0)=0)=0 , LXI,U A0,BHA
)@@G@@(0) . @D@@@@          OFF       P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@HB
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , DL A1,P(2,1),P(2,2)      . GET FILENAME  @[@@@@HC
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          ON        P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @E@@@@HD
)@@G@@          ON        P(0,1)=0=0        . SOMETHING THERE?    @E@@@@      HE
)@@G@@    ON        N=9               . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@F         FUHF
)@@G@@NC      *                 . ASCII TO FIELDATA MAPPING FUNC  @B@@@@ATOF* HG
)@@G@@    NAME                        .   @D@@@@        DO (F(1)=' ')++(F(1)=0HH
)@@G@@) , END +0 . ABLANK     @F@@@@          DO        (F(1)<'A')++(F(1)>'Z')HI
)@@G@@ , END +09) . BAD NEWS  @F@@@@          END       F(1)-'A'+6        . CHHJ
)@@G@@ANGE TO FIELDATA   A    @E@@@@I         DO        6 ,;                MAHK
)@@G@@XIMUM OF 6 CHARS  @I@@@@P(0,1)    EQU       (P(0,1)**-(C*/(I*9-9)))+ATOFHL
)@@G@@(P(0,1)*/(9-9*I)**C)*/(I*6-6) .     @E@@@@          OFF       N=9       HM
)@@G@@        . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@I DO 6 , DO P(0,1)**C*/30=0 ,P(0,1) HN
)@@G@@EQU P(0,1)*/6+5 . FILL THE FIELDATA @F@@@@G         FORM      36        HO
)@@G@@        . WE WANT ONLY ONE WORD     @D@@@@          L         A3,(G P(0,HP
)@@G@@1))       . LOAD LITERAL@B@@@@          OFF       P(0,1)=0=0        .   HQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        P(0,1)=0 , LA,U   A3,0 . CLEAR OPTIONS REG    HR
)@@G@@@D@@@@          OFF       P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @[@@@@.     HS
)@@G@@@ @@@@. FINALLY, CALL SUBROUTINE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LMJ     HT
)@@G@@  X11,FIASG$        . ASSIGN FILE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END     HU
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS USED TO CAHV
)@@G@@LL THE DIAGNOSTIC ROUTINE FIDIAG$   @F@@@@. IF A CSF$ ERROR IS DETECTED HW
)@@G@@THE ERROR$ REP IS CALLED.  IF THE   @D@@@@. ERROR IS PERMISSIONS FIDIAG HX
)@@G@@PRINTS THE MESSAGE.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0,1      HY
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@FIDIAG*   NAME      FIDIAG$           .   @D@@@@      HZ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL ROUTINE  @B@@@@          END     IA
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO IB
)@@G@@FREE A FILE WHICH HAS BEEN ASSIGNED @ @@@@. VIA FIASG$. THE CALL IS:    IC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         FIFREE    NAME FREECODE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@ID
)@@G@@P         PROC      *2                .   @D@@@@FIFREE*   NAME      FIFRIE
)@@G@@EE$           . NORMAL FREE   @E@@@@FIFRIM*   NAME      FIFRIM$         IF
)@@G@@  . RETURN FREE IMAGE   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , DL A1,P(1,1),P(1,IG
)@@G@@2)      . GET FILE NAME @E@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , L  A0,P(2,1),P(2,2),P(2,3) . IH
)@@G@@GET FREE CODE     @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL SELII
)@@G@@ECTED ROUTINE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                       IJ
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. GENERATE FIASG$ PACKET.  THE CALLS ARE: @[@@@@IK
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.         FIPFIL    'Q','QUAL' 'F','FILE' ....  @[@@@@.     IL
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THE FIRST SUBFIELD OF EACH FIELD IS A CODE LETTER, IN QUOTES :  IM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'Q' - QUALIFIER     @^@@@@.         'F' - FIIN
)@@G@@LENAME@^@@@@.         'R' - READKEY @^@@@@.         'W' - WRITEKEY@ @@@@IO
)@@G@@.         'C' - FILECYCLE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE PROCEDURE FIPELIP
)@@G@@T IS CALLED THE FULL 14 WORD ELT$ PACKET  @F@@@@. IS GENERATED AND THE FIQ
)@@G@@OLLOWING ADDITION FIELDS ARE ALLOWED.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'EIR
)@@G@@' - ELEMENT NAME  @ @@@@.         'V' - VERSION NAME  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IS
)@@G@@. THE SECOND SUBFIELD OF EACH FIELD IS A STRING OF NOT MORE THAN  @F@@@@IT
)@@G@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGTH OF THAT FIELD)  @ @@@@IU
)@@G@@. ENCLOSED IN QUOTATION MARKS.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *8  IV
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@FIPFIL*   NAME      0                 . ONLY FILIW
)@@G@@E PORTION   @G@@@@FIPELT*   NAME      1                 . BOTH FILE AND IX
)@@G@@ELEMENT PORTIONS  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@B(1)      EQU       0D              IY
)@@G@@  . PRESENCE BITS (2 WORDS)   @D@@@@Q(1)      EQU       0D              IZ
)@@G@@  . QUALIFIER (2) @D@@@@F(1)      EQU       0D                . FILENAMEJA
)@@G@@ (2)  @D@@@@R(1)      EQU       0                 . READKEY (1)   @D@@@@JB
)@@G@@W(1)      EQU       0                 . WRITEKEY (1)  @D@@@@C(1)      EQJC
)@@G@@U       0                 . CYCLE (1)     @E@@@@E(1)      EQU       0D  JD
)@@G@@              . ELEMENT NAME (2)    @E@@@@V(1)      EQU       0D        JE
)@@G@@        . VERSION NAME(2)     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@I DO P-1 , FISCAN   .   JF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          +         B(1)              .   @B@@@@      JG
)@@G@@    +         Q(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         F(1)      JH
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         C(1)              .   @B@@@@      JI
)@@G@@    +         R(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         W(1)      JJ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ON        P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@      JK
)@@G@@    +         E(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         V(1)      JL
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         0                 .   @B@@@@      JM
)@@G@@    OFF       P(0,0)            .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          END     JN
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. PROCEDURE TO PROCESS EACH FIELD.  @[@@@@.     JO
)@@G@@@F@@@@FISCAN*   PROC      *0,0              . SECOND GLOBAL PASS ONLY   JP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='Q' ,Q*(1) FIW2 66 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='JQ
)@@G@@F' ,F*(1) FIW2 60 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='C' ,C*(1) FIW1 54 .     @A@@@@JR
)@@G@@ DO P(I,1)='R' ,R*(1) FIW1 48 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='W' ,W*(1) FIW1 42 JS
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          ON        P(0,0)            .   @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='JT
)@@G@@E' ,E*(1) FIW2 30 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='V' ,V*(1) FIW2 24 .     @B@@@@JU
)@@G@@          OFF       P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@ DO FOUND(1)=0 , +09    JV
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@JW
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURE TO LEFT JUSTIFY AND STORE THE COMPONENT.  @[@@@@JX
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@Z         PROC      *1,0              .   @B@@@@FIW2*     NAJY
)@@G@@ME                        .   @B@@@@P**(I,2)  EQU       P(I,2)++0D      JZ
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@ DO 12 , DO (P(I,2)*/-66)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 KA
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@FIW1*     NAME                        .   @F@@@@ DO 06 , DO KB
)@@G@@(P(I,2)*/-30)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@*         EQKC
)@@G@@U       P(I,2)            .   @B@@@@B**(1)    EQU       B(1)++1D*/Z(1,1)KD
)@@G@@   .  @B@@@@FOUND*(1) EQU       1                 .   @^@@@@          ENKE
)@@G@@D       .   _@@@@@@F@@@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGTKF
)@@G@@)@@[MK^@K@EK@]@@@@/K@@@H1@G@@@G8@@@@;*@@@]C^H@@[[^@@@ICCH@@[C^K@@@9*@@@>KG
)@@G@@@@@@@@AA@@@@)@E[ME]^@E@]@)C@@@;*@@@]C^@K@J[@)@@$9*@@@>@@@@@@/K@@@@9?@@@>KH
